E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('50','18','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p><strong><span style=\\\\\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\\\\\">&nbsp;百元投资 月赚六千</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>这是&mdash;个无需文化、无需经验的赚钱术，不做商品买卖、不与旅客交谈阔论、不语不言，仅需投资100-300元，每天最少可赚200元(不需租用任何场地)。可以一辈子从事，合理合法，只要你地有汽车站或到外地汽车站都可以做。这个生意只有你能做，因为你有了这份资料，百分之百赚钱。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\\\\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\\\\\">5封信拿下10万元在家中照样能赚钱</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>辽宁有位62岁的赵老头子，偶然的机会他从一本杂志上发现了一个绝密的生财之道，马上从每个月仅有的几百元的退休金中拿出100元作投资，然后写了5封信，不出一个月，汇款单象雪花一样飞来。5个月之后，创利l0万元，轰动了整个新闻界。</p>\r\n<p>这是一个&ldquo;别人没有的、先人发现的、与人不同的、强人之处的&rdquo;优秀的生财之道。如今虽然一些人知道后都仿效他的方法去做这个独门生意，而这个赵老头子依然保持他独领的风骚，每个月收入2万元，而仿效他的人也同样达到这个境界，生意一点也不受影响，赵老头说，这个生意市场太大了，整个中国人人需要，是做不完的生意。看了资料必定热血沸腾，仅需按照资料，百元不到的投资，5封信就可以拿下人生第一个10万元。资料在手人人可行，可做，人人能致富。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\\\\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\\\\\">新财富商机：一次投入几十元，天天有钱赚</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>本项目无需设备，不用场地，一次投入40元，利用空余时间（不论白天或晚上，2-5个小时的时间)，每天赚上几十元、几百元不是难事，单枪匹马一人即可操作，没有任何约束。&ldquo;致富秘密武器&rdquo;是国家重点推广项目，人人能致富的金牌项目，只要你按资料运作，你一定能脱贫致富(资料一百年内不过期)。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\\\\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\\\\\">这样的东西白给你要不要</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>惊世的&ldquo;免费午餐创大业&rdquo;计划不收你的费用，所有免费发送的商品东西由厂家、个人赞助，目前已有总价值三十万的东西准备发送，全世界包括TOM、盛大、肯德基、麦当劳、当当、中国洗车用品在线等百家企业参与了赠送。&ldquo;免费午餐创大业&rdquo;行动永久开展，现在已在部份大城市陆续建立物品发放领取点。你家附近没有领取点的人可以从邮局收到邮寄的东西。更重要的是&ldquo;免费午餐创大业&rdquo;更是一项个人创业的良机。许多朋友已经从中有了可观的收入，这是一个人生的最好机会。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\\\\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\\\\\">动动笔，年赚6万元，就这么容易</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>他不是书法家，也不是作家，不会写文章，也不会写小说，做专题。不是写信或者搞信息，他只是有一个办公台，就这样坐着写字，结果一年也能赚到6万元。现在他还在做，并且生意越来越好。他的方法很简单，会写字的人都能做，也一定都会做。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\\\\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\\\\\">你想买房买车，就凭&mdash;10元生财小项目</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>投资10元的生财小项目，不用做任何准备，原料易购，产品易做，全中国每个家庭家家需要，从10元开始投资，你家就是一个生财小工厂，项目发明人仅在1-2小时内挣150元。《科学投资》杂志还做了专门的报道，10元圆了一个工厂梦。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\\\\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\\\\\">马上拥有2000元现钞的方法</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>相信我，可以让你马上拥有2000元现钞。而你仅需要汇来15元人民币。2000元现钞就是你的了，同时还教会你如何把这2000元现钞再去生钱，这样让钱生钱，以钱生钱，用钱养钱，让你口袋里的钱越生越多，直到你成为一个有钱人，成为一个很有钱的人。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\\\\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\\\\\">做别人不做的亏本生意一样可以赚大钱</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>这个方法可以让别人一而再，再而三的购买你的商品，并且一定到你的店里去购买商品不可。你不需要怎样的付出，也不必想方设法的去怎样做，只要你按资料介绍的方法去做，很快你的生意就会兴隆起来。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\\\\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\\\\\">1元年赚4万元的秘密</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>说出来谁也不会相信，湖南的黄礼荣用1元钱，去&times;&times;地做了一件事，结果1元钱有了大的用处，1年赚了四万元，这不是吹牛吗？可是黄礼荣，却实实在在做到了。有人效仿他，也赚到了钱，这真是一门投资小，利润大的好项目。只要有小学文化以上的人都可以操作。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\\\\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\\\\\">奇谋&mdash;不用分文投资，月收入六千元的秘法</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>一个瘦弱的小伙子，在没有任何背景，没有分文投资的情况下，偶然的发现使他拥有一个奇谋秘法，凭着这个秘法，让他每月轻松收入六千余元，几个月后，迅即成为月收入一万元。中国最著名创富杂志《创富指南》67期以《我在北京每月白捡1万元》为题报道河北一个农民以此秘技每月收入一万元的报道。&ldquo;发明&rdquo;这&mdash;&mdash;全新赚钱门道的郭新源肯定的对记者说&ldquo;做了一定赚钱&rdquo;。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\\\\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\\\\\">一小时赚50元的秘密</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>这是一个连小学都没有机会念完的广安少年独创的赚钱方法。当他只身来到重庆，在这个每天都能产生奇迹的城市里，发现了一种生存方式，一个简单的诀窍，凭着这一个诀窍，使他能够每天只花两小时的时间，就能赚上一百元。神奇的是，掌握了资料中的诀窍，人人能赚钱，天天都可以从事。看了资料就懂，得到资料之后，该是你出去赚钱的时候了。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\\\\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\\\\\">人人能干的赚钱奇技</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>一项人人能干的&ldquo;奇技&rdquo;+投资5元=1种人见人爱的产品，成本仅0．5元。项目发明人零卖90元，批发50元，有人成千上万的批发，仅2年时间就收入了500万元。《大众投资指南》杂志等几十家媒体都有报道和介绍。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;。。。。。。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\\\\\"font-size: medium; text-indent: 28px; font-family: 宋体;\\\\\">《创富金财路》共</span><span lang=\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\" style=\\\\\"font-family: Simsun; font-size: medium; text-indent: 28px;\\\\\">42</span><span style=\\\\\"font-size: medium; text-indent: 28px; font-family: 宋体;\\\\\">项，</span><span lang=\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\" style=\\\\\"font-family: Simsun; font-size: medium; text-indent: 28px;\\\\\"><o:p><strong><font face=\\\\\"宋体\\\\\">全套特价36元。</font></strong></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('20','19','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>&nbsp;一、就寝前和外出前应做那些检查？&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>　　 检查电气、瓦斯有否关闭、炉火有否熄灭。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二、居家逃生计划应怎么做？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）应先熟悉所住楼层的各逃生路线，并随时做好迅速撤离的准备。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）平日应与家人预先模拟火灾一旦发生时，应循什么途径逃生，以及到约定会合地点。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）应熟悉所住楼层内的消防设备及其使用方法。</div>\r\n<div>三、在厨房中应注意那些消防安全？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）烹饪时宜着短袖或合宜的长袖，避免炉火延烧衣物。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）烹煮食物时，勿任意离开，离开前须将炉火关闭。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）不要让小孩进入厨房玩耍。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>四、何种公共场所尽可能不要前往消费？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）只有单一出入口之场所。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）位于地下层之场所。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）用易燃物装修之场所。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）消防安全设备不合格之场所。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）防火区划受破坏之场所。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五、下列是常见影响逃生之重要原因，切勿前往是类公共场所消费？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）安全门上锁。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）平常应保持关闭之安全门却是随时打开。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）通往屋顶平台之安全门上锁。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）安全梯、通道（例如走廊）、楼梯等阻塞。</div>\r\n<div>六、为了自身安全，进入陌生场所应该先了解什么？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）避难逃生方向。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）安全门、梯位置，及是否未关闭、是否上锁。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）查看消防栓、缓降机、救助袋等各项灭火、避难器具位置。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七、灾害发生后应如何报案？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）应保持镇定，拨报119电话。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）述明详细灾害地点或附近目标。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）简述灾情状况。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）留下电话及地址以便进一步联系。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）119若拨不通可110、或政府消防局。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八、发生火灾时你应注意的事项？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）切忌慌乱，判断火势来源，采取火源相反方向逃生。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）切勿使用升降设备（电梯）逃生。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）切勿返入屋内取回贵重物品。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）切勿用水试图扑救通电中之电器火灾或油类的火灾。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）夜间发生火灾时，应先叫醒熟睡的人，不要只顾自己逃生，并且尽量大声喊叫，以提醒其他人逃生。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九、烹饪时油锅起火应如何处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）不可以用水来灭火。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）可用灭火器灭火。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）可盖上锅盖后再用湿毛巾覆盖，阻绝空气来灭火。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）速关闭瓦斯来源开关。</div>\r\n<div>十、消防栓使用方法？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）打开消防栓箱。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）延伸水带。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）转开止水阀。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十一、干粉灭火器使用方法？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）将安全梢拉开。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）将皮管朝向火点。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）用力压下把手，选择上风位置接近火点，将干粉射入火焰基部。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）熄灭后并以水冷却余燃。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十二、缓降机使用要领？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）自盒中取出缓降机。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）打开挂勾接头。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）挂在固定架。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）安全索套在腋下，束环束在胸口。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）拉紧调解器下两条绳索。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （六）攀出窗外面向墙壁。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （七）放开双手张开双臂，并注意身体下降时勿撞击壁面。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （八）下降后立刻拿开安全索。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （九）顺势下拉绳索到顶，以便下一位使用。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十三、逃生中如何避免火、烟之危害？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）以湿毛巾掩住口鼻呼吸，降低姿势，以减少吸入浓烟。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）于无浓烟的地方，将透明塑胶袋充满空气套住头，以避免吸入有毒烟雾或气体。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）若逃生途中经过火焰区，应先弄湿衣物或以湿棉被，毛毯裹住身体着火。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）烟雾彌漫中，一般离地面三十公分仍有残存空气可以利用，可采低姿势逃生，爬行时将手心、手肘、膝盖紧靠地面，并延墙壁边缘逃生，以免错失方向。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）火场逃生过程中，要一路关闭所有背后的门，它能减低火和浓烟的蔓延速度。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十四、火灾生后如何防止烟流从门缝进来？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 利用胶布或沾湿毛巾，床单、衣服等塞住门缝。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十五、当衣物着火时如何处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 最好脱下或就地卧倒，用手覆盖住脸部并翻滚压熄火焰，或跳入就近的水池，将火熄灭。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十六、火灾时如果你被困在室内如何待救？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）至易获救处待救（如靠近大马路之窗口附近，或与入口较近之房间等）。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）设法告知外面的人（用电话、大哥大通知119你受困的位置，或直接以衣物、灯光于窗口呼叫）。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）防阻烟流穿进来。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>[老年急救信息]《防灾救命100招》(用电安全篇)</div>\r\n<div>十七、旧有建筑物原设计配电设备从未检修更新，家电用品陆续增购，将造成什么后果？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 用电量随之增加，起负载使用，容易发生电线过载发生，引起火灾。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十八、房子的电线多久检查一次？找谁检查？如何检查？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 根据电业法规定每三年要检查一次；向当地电营业处或领有合格证照之专业人员申请；利用高阻计检查。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十九、电线困绑将造成什么后果？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 电线遭因绑，可能造成电线部分折断，产生高阻抗，使电线发生，进而造成电线走火。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二十、电线为什么要避免重物压住？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 如果电线被重物压住，可能造成电线部份折断，产生高阻抗使电线发热；及绝缘外表破损，而造成电线短路。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二十一、最常发生电线短路的位置是什么地方？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 插座及插头接触部位，电线外露受外力损坏或电器过热，造成内部短路。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二十二、家庭配电之配线老旧、外部绝缘破损及无熔丝开关故障将造成什么后果？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 易引起火灾。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二十三、拉拔插头习惯性仅拉电线，将造成什么后果？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 造成电线松脱引起火灾。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二十四、家庭电器的使用，最常引起的危险是什么？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 长时间使用，配线或马达过热而破坏绝缘，造成电线短路引起火灾。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二十五、家中常见发生火灾的电器设备有那些？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 鱼缸马达过热、回带机卡死空转、神明桌上的灯长期使用而短路、浴室抽风马达、及插头从未检查积碳引起等。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二十六、电器插头为什么要时常擦拭？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 电器插头不常擦拭，就会在插头两极逐渐堆积灰尘、毛发、或产生铜缘，增加阻抗，进而产生火灾。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二十七、家庭电器外壳，通常连接一条接地线，其目的何在？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 万一漏电时，可将外漏之电流由接地线导入地面，以免人体触电（接地线通常为绿色）。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二十八、身体潮湿时，为什么人体容易触电？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 因水为导体，电流容易经由水通过人体而造成触电。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二十九、家里保险丝熔断表示什么信号？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 用电超负载，或其他危险讯号，请专业人员检查。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>三十、用其他金属代替保险丝，会造成什么危险？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 用电过载，无法跳脱引起火灾。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>三十一、不能充电之干电池拿来充电，会造成那些危险？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 有爆炸的危险。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>三十二、变压器爆炸或电线掉落地面，应如何处理？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 请立即通知电力公司（或区营业外）并打119派员处理，并代为看守现场不要让行人或车辆靠近（通行），以免发生触电危险。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>三十三、电表外壳或水管用手碰触有一点麻麻漏电的现象，如何处理？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 请立即通知电力公司（或区营业处）或委托电器承装业，尽速派员处理。</div>\r\n<div>[老年急救信息]《防灾救命100招》（瓦斯安全篇）</div>\r\n<div>三十四、使用瓦斯前应注意什么？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 使用瓦斯必须注意是否有臭味，确认无漏气时再开火使用，并注意通风要良好。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>三十五、使用瓦斯钢瓶应注意什么？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）钢瓶请注意检验期限，并附有检验合格标志。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）钢瓶请直立，且避免受猛烈震动。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）放置于通风良好且避免日晒之处。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）不可将钢瓶放倒</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）钢瓶上不可放置物品，以免引燃。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>三十六、瓦斯管线是否漏气如何查知？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 怀疑家中瓦斯配管（管线）有漏气时，不可用火柴或打火机点火测试验，应以肥皂泡沫检查有无泄漏。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>三十七、瓦斯热水器应装何处最安全？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 应装在室外通风良好之地方，可避免产生一氧化碳中毒之意外。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>三十八、瓦斯炉火呈现红色火焰状是什么现象？有何危险性？应如何处理？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 瓦斯火焰正常呈淡蓝色，如发现呈红色，即表示不完全燃烧现象。会产生一氧化碳中毒之危险，应立即请瓦斯专业人员检修、调整炉具。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>三十九、你如何知道瓦斯外泄吗？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）嗅觉&mdash;&mdash;家用瓦斯掺有臭剂，漏出时会有臭味。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）视觉&mdash;&mdash;瓦斯外泄，会造成空气中形成雾状白烟。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）听觉&mdash;&mdash;会有&ldquo;嘶嘶&rdquo;的声音。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）触觉&mdash;&mdash;手接近外泄的漏洞，会有凉凉的感觉。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>四十、瓦斯漏气时应如何处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）立即关闭瓦斯开关。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）千万不可开启或关闭任何电器开关。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）轻轻的打开所有门窗并迅速逃出户外。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）打119派员处理。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>四十一、瓦斯会使人丧命吗？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）瓦斯本身并无毒性，但有麻醉及窒息性，使生物反应能力降低。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）瓦斯使用不当时，会产生大量一氧化碳，一氧化碳易与血液中之血红素结合，使血液运气能力大为低，而造成缺氧状态（一氧化碳中毒，导致死亡）。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>四十二、使用瓦斯空气不足，而产生一氧化碳中毒应该怎么办？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）关闭瓦斯开关。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）打开门窗通风。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）提供伤者新鲜空气。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）解开束缚、畅通呼吸道。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）视情况需要施行人工呼吸或心肺复苏术。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （六）瓦斯异味散去之前，勿开启或关闭任何电源开关，以免产生火花引起火灾。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>四十三、一氧化碳中毒有那些症状？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）会头痛、头晕、恶心、呕吐。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）会强烈虚脱感、呼吸及脉搏加速、意识模糊，身体无法自主移动。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）脸色潮红、意识丧失、呼吸停止、痉挛，导致心跳停止而死。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>四十四、如因污水管线施工不慎挖断瓦斯管线时，怎么办？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 如因污水管线施工不慎挖断瓦斯管线时,请市民立即关闭家里火源,如管线起火勿冒然灭火，划定警戒线，并尽快通知119或本府卫生下水道工程处，管线挖断处附近居民或经过行人应避免吸烟、或发动汽、机车引擎及各种电源开关以免产生爆炸或燃烧，人员则尽可能远离现场，在处理人员未达现场前，请民众先以绳子将现场圈围，并写上瓦斯外泄危险等标语，以提醒过往之人员及车辆。</div>\r\n<div>[老年急救信息]《防灾救命100招》（紧急救护篇）</div>\r\n<div>四十五、119救护车紧急救护之对象是那些？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）因灾害或意外事故急待救护者。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）路倒、伤病无法行动者。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）孕妇待产生。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）其他紧急伤病需要紧急就医者。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>四十六、什么病的病人可以给予实施CPR？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 实施CPR并无特定的疾病对象，任何人只要处于呼吸与心跳停止的状态之下，便需要CPR的急救处置，例如：溺水、心脏病发作或呼吸衰竭所引起的呼吸与心跳停止。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>四十七、是否可以在健康的人身上练习CPR？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 对于一个有脉搏、呼吸的正常人，绝对不能随意练习CPR，因为会造成不必要的危险，如骨折、肝脾脏裂伤、心律不整等等。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>四十八、CPR的施行步骤？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）呼叫患者，评估意识。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）请人打119报案求救。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）打开呼吸道。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）人工呼吸。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）心外按摩。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>四十九、单人CPR施救方法？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）胸外按摩与人工呼吸之比率是15：2。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）胸外按摩之速率是每分钟80&mdash;100次。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）每做完十五次心脏按摩后，给予患者人工呼吸二次。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五十、吃东西哽住怎么办（哈姆立克法）？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）询问：你哽到了吗？（协助拍打背部使异物咳出）。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）实行腹部挤压（假如病人怀孕或过肥胖，则实施胸部压挤）。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）持续第二步骤之动作，直到到异物排出或病意识发生变化。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）如病患无法站立，将病患平放在坚固的平面上，跨坐在病患大腿上双手合握，在肚脐上方用力推挤五次，再检查病患有无将异物咳出。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）送医求救。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （六）将舌头及下巴抓住抬高，然后用另一侧之手指清除口腔异物（不可盲目掏挖）。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （七）畅通呼吸道。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （八）如果呼吸道阻塞，则重复腹部压挤五次。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （九）重复五到七之动作，直至异物清除。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五十一、呼吸道哽塞之急救要点？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）实行腹部挤压（假如病人怀孕或过肥胖，则实施胸部压挤）。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）如病患无法站立，将病患平放在坚固的平面上，跨坐在病患腿上作腹部推挤五次，再检查病患有无将异物咳出。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）如用手指掏挖异物时，只在看得到异物才掏挖，不可盲目掏挖。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五十二、哈姆立克法（一岁以下小孩呼吸道哽塞）之急救。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）先拍背，将婴儿翻转，使面朝下，让婴儿趴在手臂上，以手掌抓住婴儿脸部，以掌根叩击两肩胛中间五次。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）将婴儿翻转成面朝上，于CPR位置用两指压，也是压五下。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）用小指掏挖异物时，只在看到异物和掏挖。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五十三、出血处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）直接加压止血：用手（敷料）直接对伤口施以压力。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）间接压迫法：压迫特定的止血点，分别位于手臂上的肱动脉，及大腿上的股动脉。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五十四、耳朵出血处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）伤者以头倾向患侧躺下，使血液流出，不要用任何东西去塞住耳朵，血液流出后用消毒纱布擦掉。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）每隔十分钟检查呼吸、脉搏及意识程度。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）若无呼吸无心跳则马上进行人工心肺复苏术。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五十五、鼻出血处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）头向前倾之姿势坐下，并宽松颈部及胸部衣物。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）在鼻骨两侧冰敷。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）将骨翼捏住止血。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）可在上唇内放置一块纱布，施予压迫帮忙控制出血。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五十六、脸部出血处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）不论大小伤口，宜采直接加压止血法止血。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）虽是小伤口，亦须送医治疗，以免影响愈后脸部容貌问题。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五十七、颈部出血处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）采直接加压止血法，当可止血。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）每隔十分钟放松一次，看看是否止血。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）注意呼吸心跳若停止，则立刻施行心肺复苏术。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）送医治疗。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五十八、胸部出血处置（开放性伤口）？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）明显胸部外伤，不论伤有否穿透胸廓是入胸腔，采用直接加压止血法。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）勿将异物拔除。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）随时注意呼吸、脉搏及意识状，若停止则马上施行人工心肺复苏术。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）迅速送医治疗。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五十九、腹部出血之处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）直接加压止血。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）切勿将脱出之器官塞回腹腔，用生理盐水保持湿润后立即送医。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）不要将留在身上的穿刺物拔除。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六十、四肢创伤急救之处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）直接加压止血、抬高止血。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）若有异物，不可随意拔除。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）移动患者要非常谨慎，伤处不可过度移动。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六十一、骨折的处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）不可随便移动患者。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）让患者保持最舒适的姿势。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）以原姿势固定骨折处送医。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六十二、扭伤之处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）立即让患部休息，不要过度移动患部。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）对患部施用冰敷以降低肿胀及疼痛。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）抬高患部。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）二十四小时后对患部施以温湿敷。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六十三、眼部之异物处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）可用生理食盐水由鼻侧向外侧冲洗，以免冲出来的异物进入另一只眼睛。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）若异物刺入眼球中，一定要由医师移除，不可随意拔除。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六十四、颜面器官、断肢保护处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）以生理食盐水纱布好好裹住，整包放进塑料胶袋中，加以密封，再放入冰中与病患一起送。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）如果器官并未完全掉落时，要把它摆回原来位置，不可以有旋转、压迫等情形，以避免血液循环断而坏死。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六十五、糖尿病患者之处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 若已知患者为糖尿病患者，应给予糖分的补充；若患者意识清醒，可以给予方糖；若患者意识不清，则在舌下给予糖水后送医。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六十六、癫痫抽搐发作时之处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）不要强制约束病人，应保护患者，避免受到外伤。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）勿硬塞任何东西让病患咬住。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）抽搐停止后若无呼吸及心跳时，应实施人工呼吸与心外按摩。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）清醒后，再决定是否送医。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六十七、晕厥的处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）让患者平躺于床上，将脚端抬高于头部，帮助血液流入脑部。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）宜松开一切紧身衣物和其他束缚。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）头部转向一侧，且在病人意识恢复之前不可让病人摄食。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六十八、中暑之处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）将患者移到阴凉通风处，脱掉衣服，并使患者躺下。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）迅速降低体温，可以微湿的毛巾擦拭全身，再用风扇吹，以加强散热。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六十九、中毒的处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）以大量清水或生理食盐清洗去毒，受污染之衣物须除去。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）服用大量药物之送医，须将相关瓶罐携往急诊处。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）意识不清、吞食腐蚀物质不可催吐。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七十、烧烫伤处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）冲、脱、泡、盖、送。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）衣服着火应立即灭火及脱去衣服，立刻卧倒打滚、冲水。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）要以干净的冷水冲洗十五分钟以上，降低温度避免烧伤继续进行，但要注意持续冲冷水可能造成失温。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）送医。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七十一、化学烧伤的立即处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）应马上除去化学品并以大量的水冲洗二十至三十分钟，洗去化学物质。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）送医。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七十二、溺水处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）尽速打开呼吸道，同时保护颈椎。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）检查呼吸与心跳，必要时施行心肺复苏术。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）溺水者一旦开始自行呼吸，则将其姿势更换为复苏姿势。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）保持溺水者身体的温暖。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）所有溺水者身体获救都应送医治疗。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七十三、昆虫蟄伤及咬伤之处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）用水和肥皂清洗伤口。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）用冷敷以减少肿胀，不可直接冰敷。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七十四、毒蛇咬伤之处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）保持冷静。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）包扎伤口使伤口低于心脏下方。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）记住毒蛇特征，以提供医师决定注射何种血清。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七十五、发生车祸受伤时如何处理？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）打119电话求救。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）向旁人求救。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）放置警告标志。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）勿移动伤者。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）留在现场等警察及119到来。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七十六、面对有人要自杀的情况下怎么处理较为恰当？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）安抚其情绪。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）请周旁人员打119电话求救。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）拿开危险物品。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）避开危险场所。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）自杀现场残留之药丸、药罐、杀虫剂、农药等物品，应小心收集带到医院，以利后续的诊断治疗。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （六）病人送到医院，最好协助寻找亲人照顾。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七十七、一氧化碳中毒缺氧处置？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）有瓦斯味时，关闭瓦斯开关及不可开、关电源。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）打开所有门窗，让新鲜空气流通。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）将昏迷者移至通风良好的安全场所。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）检查呼吸及脉搏必要时进行CPR。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>[老年急救信息]《防灾救命100招》（风、水灾篇）</div>\r\n<div>七十八、气象服务可拨什么电话？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 166或167&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七十九、气象局发布海上、陆上台风的时机为何？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 在二十四小时以内台风侵犯100海里之海面，则发布海上台风警报。而十八小时内侵犯本岛陆地，则发布陆上台风警报。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八十、台风来临前应如何应变？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）随时注意台风动向，紧急危险事故可打119电话请求协助。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）住所位处低洼地区时，应暂迁至较高所</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）准备手电筒、收音机、食物及饮水，检查电路注意炉火瓦斯。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）不可贸然外出，使用火烛注意防范火灾。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）检查门窗是否坚固，各种悬吊物应取下。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （六）清扫排水沟以防积水、花木事先用支架保护，并修剪枝干。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （七）将屋外的动、植物及物品移置安全处所。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （八）断落的电线，勿自行处理，应通知电力公司。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八十一、台风来临时风热突然减弱，可否外出？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 可能处于台风眼经过时刻，不可冒然外出，以免受伤。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八十二、台风来临时住在山坡地的居民如何应变？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 提高警觉防止山崩或道路坍方，山坡下和山区公路不宜停留或停车。为了生命的安全，应该要及早离开。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八十三、水灾后低洼地区及地下室淹水该如何处理？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）应设警告标志。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）应迅速抽干复原，避免有人陷溺。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八十四、溪边露营戏水如何警觉山洪暴发？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 露营切勿于河床旁扎营，不可于天候不定时刻到河床边戏水，如发现溪水突然混浊有大量枯叶及小枯枝流下时，系为山洪暴发之前兆，应立即远离河域以维安全。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八十五、灾害后如发现自来水混浊应如何处理？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）重大灾情发生后若自来水混浊，应以自行储存之瓶装水或至指定处取水以为饮用水源，至于该混浊水在节约用水原则仍可为其他生活用水，必要时可以下述方法处理：加入适量之明矾（市面贩售），待溶解后快速搅拌五分钟，接着慢速搅拌二十分钟，再静置三十分钟后取上层液煮沸饮用。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>明矾添加量计算公式如下：&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>明矾添加量（公克）=饮用水量公升数&times;○&middot;○二公克/公升。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 例如：你饮用水处理量为一○○公升&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 一○○公升&times;○&middot;○二公克/公升=二公克&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 则一○○公升饮用水需加入=二公克之明矾。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）至于一般事故，可径洽自来水事业处或各分处派员处理。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八十六、因台风、暴雨或其他灾变，位于水库或水坝下游居民应如何注意？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 预知台风、暴雨将来临时应避免到低洼地区，尤其于知道水库或水坝管理单位宣导泄洪时，更应即时离开溪床及低地。另外于发生有感****后，水库或水坝下游居民应即搬离，无安全顾虑后再返回，以免因坝体受损而遭受生命财产损失。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八十七、灾后自来水、瓦斯及电力供应中断，必需饮用地下水、消防用水等贮留水时，如何确保饮用水安全？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）灾后如自来水供应中断以饮用瓶装水为优先考量，或至指定地点取水煮沸后方可饮用。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）必要时取用前述贮留水时可以下述方法处理、惟仍需煮沸方可饮用：加入适量漂白水，搅拌后放置十分钟。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>[老年急救信息]《防灾救命100招》（防震篇）</div>\r\n<div>八十八、****发生时应随手关闭那些开关，防止火灾发生？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 电源、火源及瓦斯开关。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八十九、居家如何做好防震措施？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）家中应准备急救箱及灭火器，并告知家人所储放的地方，了解使用方法。</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）知道瓦斯、自来水及电源安全阀如何开关。</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）家中高悬的物品应绑牢，橱柜门宜锁紧。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）重物不要置于高架上，栓牢笨重家具。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）事先找好家中安全避难处。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九十、 学校之防震措施？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 教师（尤其是中、小学校）应经常在课堂宣导防震常识，并教导学生避难事宜，举行防城演习。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）教室的照明灯具、实验室的橱柜及图书馆的书架应加以固定。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）****时避于桌下，背向窗户，并用书包保护头部。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）****时切忌慌乱冲出教室，并避免慌张地上下楼梯。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）****时如在室外，远离建筑物。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）****时如在行驶中之校车，应留在座位上勿动，直至车辆停妥。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九十一、办公室及公共场所之防震措施？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）经常检验防火和消防设备。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）规划有关紧急计划，并分别告知紧急情况时各人的任务以及应采取的行动。</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）****时注意天花板上的物品（如灯具）掉落下来。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）****时躲在办公桌或坚固的家具下或靠支柱站立，远离窗户。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）****时公共场所中，应小心选择出口，避免人群推挤。</div>\r\n<div>　　 （六）****时切忌急着冲出，请勿使用电梯。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九十二、****时在室内如何应对？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）保持镇定并迅速关闭电源、瓦斯、自来水开关。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）打开出入的门，随手抓个垫子等保护头部，尽速躲在坚固家具、桌子下，或靠建筑物中央的墙站着。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）切勿靠近窗户，以防玻璃震破。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）切记！不要慌张地往室外跑。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九十三、****时在室外如何应对？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）站立于空旷处，不要慌张地往室内冲。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）注意上方可能有如招牌、盆景等掉落物。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）远离与建中的建筑物、电线杆、围墙、未经固定的贩卖机等。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）行驶中的车辆，勿紧急刹车，应减低车速，靠边停放。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）若行驶于高速公路或高架桥上，应小心迅速驶离。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （六）若在郊外，远离崖边、河边、海边，找空旷的地方避难。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九十四、****后如何紧急处理，以减少灾害损失？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）察看周围的人是否受伤，如有必要，予以急救。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）检查家中水、电、瓦斯管线有无损害、轻轻将门、窗打开，立即离开并向有关权责单位报告。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （三）打开收音机、收听紧急情况指示及灾情报导。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （四）检查房屋结构受损情况，尽快离开受损建筑物，疏散时请使用楼梯。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （五）尽可能穿着皮鞋、以防震碎的玻璃及碎物弄伤。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （六）保持救灾道路畅通，徒步避难。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （七）听从紧急计划人员的指疏散，并注意余震之发生。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （八）远离海滩、港口以防海啸之侵袭。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （九）****灾区，除非特准，请勿进入，并应严防歹徒趁机掠夺。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九十五、我家房子经过九二一大****后严重损坏，经工务局会同专业技师勘估，并评为危险且无法补强，如何处理？</div>\r\n<div>　　 经勘估评为危险（张贴红色警告标示）且无法补强之建筑物，应由所有权人于收到工务局拆除通知之日起三个月内得免申请除执照，自行拆除完毕，拆除后以书面向本府工务局办理报备；拆除后之重建，得以原建蔽率、原容积率申请建造。所有权人如有异议，应在收到通知书起五日内向本府工务局申请缓拆，并自行委托开业建筑师或专业技师办理鉴定存证，缓拆期日以三十日为限。此类危险建筑物应于期限内拆除完毕。过期未拆除者，本府工务局得依规定强制拆除。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九十六、因九二一大****损坏严重之建筑物，经勘估评为危险，但得以补强者，所有权人后续应如何处理？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 此类建筑物应由所有权人，委托专业技师公会制作鉴定报告书建议补强方式，并拟具补强计划，依据补强计划施工完成，再经原鉴定公会鉴定符合安全要求，并报本府工务局备查，上开补强应于工务局通知之日起三个月内完成。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 又所有权人如不愿意以补强方式办理，得比照危险且无法补强者之方式，免申请拆除执照，由所有权人自行拆除后，以书面向工务局报备，其拆除后之重建，亦得以原建蔽率、原容积率申请建造。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九十七、房子因为九二一大****损坏，经勘估评为需注意并被张贴黄色警告标示，如何处理？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 经勘估评为需注意并张贴黄色警告之建筑物，应由建筑物所有权人自行委托专业技师或公会制作补强计划，并依补强计划施行完毕，再经原委托专业技师或公会确认后，向工务局办理报备，上开补强应于收到工务局补强通知之日起三个月内完成。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九十八、房屋危险分红、黄、绿三级意义为何？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）红色危险标示：指建筑物整体塌陷或结构体严重损坏、明显倾斜，坠落物及维生管随时有塌落危险，禁止进入者。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 黄色应注意标示：指建筑物部分损坏应注意者。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 绿色安全标示：指建筑物安全，无明显结构及基础损坏，住户可安心居住者。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）房屋使用者可依上述定义，在技师未到达前自行检查。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九十九、危楼拆除应注意事项为何？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （一）民众自行拆除者，应注意公共安全及不要损及他人权益。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 （二）强制拆除者应注重程度合法。对于民众财产之冲击有争议者，应与检方共同完成证，且应以影响救灾动线或危及邻居者为优先。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>一○○、 强烈****后你了解居家附近避难场所位置吗？&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　 请各位市民同胞多留意你居家信所邻居近之防灾公园避难场所之位置。</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('21','19','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>&nbsp;1.当石灰飞入眼睛，热辣难忍时，只要滴少许糖水。就可解除痛苦。&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　2.浴室镜子上的水雾干湿毛巾都很难清理。可先在镜子上涂一层香皂，再用干抹布抹干，镜子很容易恢复清晰。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　3.冬天因干燥感到浑身发痒的，切不可用手抓，否则易抓破皮肤引起继发感染，可多饮水，多吃水果防治。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　4.喝咖啡可以缓解压力，放松心情，同时也可刺激肠蠕动。产生通便作用，为便秘所苦的人可以在早餐的时候喝咖啡。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　5.抽屉，壁橱衣箱里有霉味的时候，在里面放块肥皂，即可去除。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　6.买礼盒送人的时候，价格标签很难撕掉，可用吹风机吹热在撕，会很轻松的撕下来，不留一点痕迹。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　7.柚子皮煮水可治冻疮。用柚子皮煮水擦洗患处，每天洗1－2次，几次即可见效。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　8.牛奶可以强身健体，每天饮用250毫升牛奶可以降低患结肠癌的几率。但喝太多可能导致前列腺疾病。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　9.生姜能提神醒脑，冬季可适当多吃姜，专家认为吃生姜可舒解类风湿性关节炎所引起的疼痛，改善关节的活动能力。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　10.冬天忌将头蒙在被窝里，因为二氧化碳和不洁气体越积越多，会让人醒后感到昏昏沉沉，疲乏无力。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　11.绿豆退烧治感冒的窍门，可先煮绿豆，煮烂后在加姜丝和可乐，趁热喝下即可退烧治流感。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　12.喝牛奶前一小时不宜吃橘子,因为牛奶得蛋白质与橘子中得果酸相遇会发生凝固,不利于牛奶得吸收。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　13.香蕉皮能有效治冻伤,用香蕉皮得内面轻轻磨擦冻伤处,直至发热,几次即可见效.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　14.生吃花生米可治老花眼.每日吃花生米25克左右,每日一次,长期坚持对老花眼得恢复有帮助.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　15.橘皮水洗脸可润肤.用开水浸泡几片橘皮,待温度适宜后,用橘皮水洗脸,能润肤.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　16.衣服沾上鸡蛋清,可先用冷水泡,然后用茶水浸泡,最后再用清水漂洗,即可除去蛋清渍.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　17.游泳憋气能锻炼身体,对治疗耳鸣也有帮助,需长期坚持.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　18.茶叶中得儿茶素具有抑制流感病毒活性得作用,坚持用茶水漱口,可以有效预防流感.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　19.香蕉冰糖合蒸止咳.香蕉3根,冰糖5克,装入碗内上锅,文火蒸15分钟食用,止咳效果很好.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　20.花椒叶水泡脚治脚跟痛.将新鲜花椒叶水煮沸,趁热泡脚,连泡几天每次半小时,很快会痊愈.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　21.猪油蜂蜜膏能除冻疮.取猪油20克,蜂蜜80克,放在一起调匀成膏,敷于患处每日3次,数日克痊愈.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　22.姜汁饮料可治头晕恶心,用调味得姜粉配制饮料,乘车前半小时饮用,能防止头晕恶心.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　23.大枣治手脚裂,把数枚大枣去掉皮核,加水煮成糊状,涂抹于裂口处,一天两次,几天后可痊愈.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　24.酱油汗漱可治咽喉疼痛.咽喉疼痛时,用一调羹酱油漱口,1分钟左右吐出,连续3至4次,效果很好.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　25.若是木制家具裂了缝,可把旧报纸剪碎加明矾,米汤煮成糊状.将其嵌入裂缝,干燥后就很牢固了&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　26.将梨捣烂加冰糖调服,可治声音嘶哑.雪花梨加1克麻黄放入锅中煮熟,每天吃2次,可治百日咳.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　27.洗澡时身上若有伤口,可在伤口涂抹油质物,如面霜,与水隔离,就不会发炎,也不会痛了.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　28.报纸油墨可驱虫,在放衣服得箱子底下放一层报纸,在放入衣物,这样可使2衣物免遭虫咬.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　29.将适量鲜藕洗净,捣碎榨250克汁,加蜂蜜52克调匀,分5次服,连用数日,可治感冒咳嗽.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　30.巧克力不宜放在冰箱中,易发霉变质失去原味.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　31.蒸东西时,蒸锅水不宜放得太多,一般以蒸好后锅内剩半碗水为宜.这样做,可最大程度节约煤气.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　33.将花椒放入锅内炒糊,碾成面状,每晚睡前用适量白糖水冲服一汤匙花椒粉,常用可瘦身.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　34.慢性咽炎患者应多吃大白菜,勿食辛辣刺激食品,慢慢就可缓解这种病症.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　35.衣服上占了油垢后,稍挤牙膏涂于污染处,轻轻揉搓,然后用清水清洗,油渍即可除去.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　36.身体被磕碰后,即可用小磨香油涂抹患处,并轻轻揉一揉,患处便不会起肿块和出现青斑.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　37.白糖豆腐蒸食能治感冒.在豆腐上撒点白糖,用蒸锅熟后食用,一日3次,数日即可治愈感冒.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　38.用油炸食物,有时油烧沸后会从锅里溢出,可立即放进几粒花椒,沸油就好消下去.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　39.藤器弄脏了,可用水浸湿刷净,然后用点燃得硫黄熏,就会光洁如新.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　40.刚买回得陶瓷餐具,用4%得食醋水浸泡煮沸,可去除大部分有毒物质.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　41.丝绸衣物烫黄时,可用少许苏打粉加水调成糊状,涂在焦迹处,待水蒸发后,在垫湿布熨烫,焦黄即可消除.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　42.在西红柿底部划个小十字,放入沸水中烫5秒钟,立即取出浸入冷水中,可轻易将皮剥掉.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　43.将150克枸杞放入适量白酒中浸泡,十几天后饮用,每日一次,长期饮用可有效治疗腰痛.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　44.每天晚饭后或临睡前,吃两瓣大蒜,一段时间后可治失眠,使睡眠恢复正常.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　45.艾草塞鼻可治鼻塞,将艾草揉好后塞入鼻中,会使鼻子呼吸通畅.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　46.用盐水泡脚可解乏提神,精力大增.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　47.把蘸有甘油和蛋黄得布料盖在污渍表面放置片刻,用清水洗净即可去除污渍.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　48.开水服醋可防晕车,取少许醋,用开水饮用后然后乘车,可防晕车.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　49.专家建议冬天可多吃红辣椒,胡萝卜,山楂等食品,或每天喝一倍3酸奶,一碗鸡汤,都可有效预防感冒.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　50.冬季装修时,木材要注意保湿,以免变形,水工制品要及时封油,以防收缩,木地板要流出2毫米左右得伸缩缝.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　51.低温季节每天坚持搓耳,搓手,然后对这些部分用吹风机吹暖片刻,即可有效防治冻伤.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　52.秋冬季节,每日煮食白萝卜,胡萝卜,连汤带菜早晚各服一小碗.长期坚持,可有效治疗慢性支气管炎.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　53.毛衣穿久了,有些部位会磨得发亮,用醋,水各半得混合液喷撒一下,在洗涤.就好恢复原样.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　54.秋天眼中有红血丝,可吃杞菊地黄丸(河南宛西,兰州佛慈).&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　55.熬粥放入橘皮,不仅芳香可口,而且还能起到开胃作用,对于胸腹胀满或咳嗽痰多得人,有治疗作用.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　56.秋冬季节手脚干裂,可将剩茶水兑血热水泡洗手脚约10分钟,坚持一周,皮肤即可光滑如初.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　57.白色毛衣穿久会发黑,将毛衣清洗后放入冰箱冷冻一小时,取出在晾干,即可洁白如新.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　58.抽油烟机上得油盒很难清洗,可在干净得油盒上先放点水,让油滴在水上,快清洗时一倒,油很快久倒出来了.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　59.在皴裂得手脚上涂些牙膏,就能止血止痛,很快痊愈.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　60.多吃菠菜能起到排毒瘦腿,保护视网膜得作用.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　61.棉质衣服出现霉斑,用几根绿豆牙在霉斑得地方反复揉搓,然后用清水漂洗干净,霉斑即可去除.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　 62.冬天吃萝卜得妙处:可解毒,治小便不利等症状.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　63.冬天忌睡前洗头,冷天用热水洗完头之后.大量水分蒸发时带走很多热量,这时候睡觉,易患感冒.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　64.花生米可治风寒胃疼,受冷风刺激之后常会引起胃疼,可吃些煮熟炒熟的花生米,胃疼即可减轻.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　65.将鸡蛋磕破,分离蛋黄和蛋白,将蛋黄到入鲜牛奶中同煮,饮后可起到镇脑安神的功效.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　66.碘酒外抹患处能除手藓,在患处每天抹碘酒4到5次,患处皮肤逐渐干而脱落,手藓随之治愈.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　67.在玻璃伤先涂点石膏粉和粉笔灰水,干后再用干布擦可轻易将玻璃擦亮.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　68.啤酒漱口可去尘消霉.用啤酒漱口可以冲掉喉咙里的微尘,并有消毒的作用,可以使喉咙更舒畅.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　69.白酒治汗脚臭脚.每晚洗脚后用白酒少许揉搓脚部,并自然风干.坚持一个月.可治愈脚臭.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　70.巧刷翻毛皮鞋.用酒精和黄米面调成糊状涂于鞋面.晾干后把黄米面刷掉,脏东西就会随之除掉.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　71.多吃水煮鱼易产生皮肤问题,水煮鱼中的辣椒刺激性强,一些餐馆用海鱼做源料,部分食客会有过敏反应.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　72.巧洗羊毛衫:洗涤时放在温水中加适量干洗剂和氨水,漂洗时在加几滴醋,可帮助恢复毛织物原有的光泽及柔软度.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　73.豆腐放冰箱中保鲜的窍门:豆腐直接放入冰箱,水分会溢出,风味也差,可泡在水中存放冰箱内.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　74.煮可乐可治伤风感冒.伤风感冒初起时,可用可乐加几片姜和一个柠檬同煮,然后饮之,既有显著疗效.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　75.用热米汤泡发木耳,半小时后捞出,用此法泡发的木耳不仅外观肥大柔软,而且炒后味道鲜嫩.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　76.鸡蛋富含硫,每周吃4个蛋可使头发亮泽.常吃高蛋白食物和新鲜蔬菜,可使头发浓密.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　77.醋可消除冰箱臭味,将一些食醋到入敞口玻璃瓶中放近冰箱内,有除臭杀毒的作用.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　78.甘草绿豆汤解药物中毒.药物中毒时,用甘草15克,绿豆80克煎汤,一日一剂,分3次服下.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　79.饭后吃糖姜片可治胃酸胃疼.每次饭后吃三,四片闽姜(即糖姜片),长期坚持,可治胃酸过多,胃疼病.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　80.醉酒不宜合喝汽水解酒,酒与汽水同饮后会使酒精很快在全身挥发产生大量二氧化碳,对肠胃,肝肾器官有严重损坏.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　81.冬天如能常喝凉白开可预防感冒,尤其食早晨起床喝杯凉白开水,能使肝脏解毒能力和肾脏排洗能力增强.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　82.来苏水泡脚可治冻疮。每晚用放有2－3滴的医用来苏水的温热水泡脚，几次后冻疮可好。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　83.白萝卜治鼻塞。取白萝卜3－4个，放入锅中加清水煮，沸后即用鼻戏蒸汽，数分钟后鼻子即可通气。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　84.吃酸的食物过多，牙会感觉发酸，俗称&ldquo;倒牙&rdquo;。只要吃两个核桃仁，就可立即使牙恢复正常。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　85.使牙迅速变白土方:用食盐,小苏打等量,加水调匀,每日刷牙一次,4天可除牙齿表面色斑.使牙齿洁白.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　86.吞食韭菜治鱼刺卡喉,将一把已切碎的韭菜炒熟,然后吞咽下去,能去除卡喉鱼刺.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　87.治疗贫血土方,取乌鸡鲜血流在一张白纸上,晒干将干血揉成粉,用红酒调服,一次半匙粉,一日两次.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　88.盐水除鸡眼,用一匙食盐加水煮沸,待稍凉后烫脚,烫脚后擦干即可,每次半小时,一周左右鸡眼可自行脱落.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　89.煮熟的白菜如隔夜食用,菜里的硝酸盐会还原成亚硝酸盐,使人体因缺氧产生疾病,因此白菜一定要现作现吃.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　90.吃火锅时汤中倒入适量啤酒有降火作用.吃火锅配饮啤酒,酒中二氧化碳可帮助散热,防止食物烫伤口腔.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　91.脚枕枕头治抽筋.每晚睡觉时在脚下垫一个枕头,可防治抽筋症状在睡觉时发生.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　92.涂抹肥皂可消肿止痛.不论是被开水或火烫伤后,立刻在伤处涂抹些肥皂,可暂时消肿止痛.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　93.海带泥掺蜂蜜治口疮,将海带(或茄子皮)烤焦倒碎,掺入蜂蜜后涂抹在患处,效果很好.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　94.空腹吃核桃仁可治风湿,每天空腹吃5-6个核桃,坚持几个月后,风湿症状可消失.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　95.如果毛衣袖口或下摆失去了弹性,可在热水中浸泡20分钟,通风干燥处晾干后即可恢复弹性.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　96.要清除冰箱霉菌.可用干布蘸肥皂水擦拭,如擦不掉.可用干布蘸上少量酒精擦拭.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　97.按摩眼眶治鼻炎,双手食指按在两眼下的眼眶骨,每天两次揉二百下,一段时间后可见效.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　98.嚼吃花生有效治倒牙,嚼几粒花生或一段生葱,牙齿立即恢复如初,就可以继续嚼东西了.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　99.牛奶能使鱼汤鲜美.在家炖鱼汤时可在锅里滴几滴牛奶,这样不仅可使鱼肉白嫩,鱼汤也会很美味.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　100.用完的香水瓶，化妆水瓶不要立即扔掉，把他们的盖打开，放在衣箱或衣柜里会使衣物变得香气袭人.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　101.抽烟或长时间使用深色指甲油会使指甲变色,每天用半个新鲜柠檬擦拭,擦上两周即可除去污渍.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　102.液态奶包装的主要成分聚乙烯再高温时会分解,有毒物渗到牛奶里会危害健康,所以牛奶不要连袋热.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　103.胃寒疼痛,可用生姜少许,加水煮沸,趁热服.对胃口不好,消化不良的患者,此方法也有效.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　104.柚子中含有柚皮苷,可降低血液的黏稠度,减少血栓形成,适合中老年人食用.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　105.秋季皮肤比夏天更易晒黑,秋天离子层浓度比夏天稀,紫外线更强,更需防晒.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　106.做鱼时应多放姜,姜可缓和鱼的寒性,解腥,帮助消化,烧肉时宜多放花椒,花椒有助暖作用.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　107.中药汤在37度时舌头感觉最苦,所以药汤煎好后最好先凉一下再服.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　108.烹调蟹,虾等水产品时,先用1%的食醋液浸泡一个小时,可防止嗜盐杆菌引起的食物中毒.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　109.喝茶不宜过浓,过浓的茶会使胃黏膜收缩,蛋白质凝固,并冲淡胃液,影响消化个人对铁质的吸收.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　110.做豆腐时不可放葱,葱中的草酸容易和豆腐的钙质结合成草酸钙,会破坏豆腐的营养成分.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　111.久坐电脑前的人应常吃苹果,它能与体内的放射性元素结合并排出体外,具有防癌及养生的功效.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　112.新的瓷器餐具放在10%的醋水内煮三个小时后再用可出去新瓷器所含微量铝,避免铝毒危害身体.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　113.干燥的秋季应慎用泡沫型洗面奶,否则会使皮肤角质层失去水分,导致皮肤搔痒问题.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　114.如果觉得苦瓜太苦.烧时可放点醋, 可减少苦味.适当的苦味有助于调节人体阴阳平衡,具有提神醒脑的作用.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　115.板栗含多种维生素及磷.钙等,对人体滋补功能几乎可与人参当归等媲美,尤其对肾虚者有显著疗效.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　116.少量饮酒可舒经活血,松弛精神,但是有高血压,心血管疾病,消化道溃疡等疾病的病人都不适宜饮酒.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　117.鱼肝油治手藓,把鱼肝油丸挤破,取少许外敷如无不良反应,可放心涂敷,每周3次,一周即可痊愈.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　118.涮火锅之前最好先喝半杯新鲜果汁,接着吃蔬菜,然后是肉,这样可以合理利用食物营养,减少肠胃负担.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　119.每天饮用8杯水可预防膀胱癌.否则体内血液过于粘稠,有毒垃圾无法清除,还会加重肾,肝等的负担.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　120.巧除沐浴喷头水垢,取一个大碗,倒入米醋,把喷头泡在醋里,数小时后取出,用清水冲净即可.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　121.茶叶与糖果不宜一起存放,放在一起会易使茶叶因受潮而发霉.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　122.在炒鸡蛋时,如果在下锅之前往搅拌的鸡蛋中滴几滴白酒,炒出的鸡蛋会更加鲜嫩.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　123.运动前喝咖啡可帮助人们缓解运动过量造成的肌肉酸痛.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　124.用葡萄汁代替白开水服降压药效果好,能使血压降的平稳,而且不会出现血压忽高忽低的现象.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　125.对眼睛冷敷有助于消除熬夜后双眼的血丝,将冰块装在冰袋里包上纱布,冷敷皮肤,每次15分钟.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　126.识别病猪肉妙招,买猪肉时拔一根或数根猪毛,仔细看其毛根,如毛根发红,则是病猪.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　127.坚持每餐餐后嚼食绿茶.可治牙龈出血和口腔异味.嚼茶时要让茶叶在口中磨嚼成细粉末再服下.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　 128.天然水晶透明度高,内部有棉絮状结晶体,天然水晶触感凉爽,硬度较高,用力划玻璃会有明显的划痕.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　129.猕猴桃富含丰富维生素C,每天早晚一个,有助于血液循环,冬天常吃猕猴桃可以调节人体机能,增强抵抗力.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　130.牙痛或者咽喉感染时可把一至两根丁香花放到嘴里咀嚼,几分钟就能起到杀菌止痛的作用.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　131.芹菜叶降压效果相当明显,用水烫一下,剁碎,拌上蒜泥,几乎相当于服一片降压药.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　132.防止毛衣缩水,在温水中倒入洗涤剂,毛衣洗后用网兜控干水,半干时在取出摊平阴干.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　133.喝完牛奶必须喝水,细菌会分解口中残留的牛奶,产生含硫化物臭味的气体,导致口味不佳.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　134.冬季当人体缺乏维生素A时,皮肤会变得干燥,富含维生素A的食物有,蛋,猪肝.黄豆.花生等.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　135.豆浆蜂蜜不宜一起冲饮,豆浆蛋白质含量很高,蜂蜜含葡萄糖和有机酸,两者一起冲饮时易产生变性沉淀.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　136.剁肉前,把菜刀放进热水里泡3分钟-5分钟.剁肉时,肉末就不在粘刀.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　137.将冰箱垫高3-6厘米.使箱体底部空气对流空间增大,这样可减少从冰箱两侧及上部出来的噪音.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　138.山楂桂皮治胃痛,将10克山楂肉用水煎20分钟,然后加入5克桂皮,稍煮片刻取汁加红糖服用.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　139.购买柠檬,橙子时应选表面光滑的,因橘类采摘后存放时间过长会脱水,表皮会起皱&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　140.果汁和羊肉不适合一起吃,吃羊肉的时候最好喝碳酸饮料,因为碳酸饮料可更好的消化胃里的羊肉.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　141.西梅果实营养丰富,富含维生素,抗氧化剂及善事纤维.不含脂肪和胆固醇,是现代人的最佳零食.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　142.蜂蜜是一种比较好的冬季保养品,但是不可以与豆腐同食,豆腐性寒,能清热散血.与蜂蜜同食易导致腹泻.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　143.买香肠要注意色泽,质量好的腌腊制品色泽呈暗红色.脂肪透明或呈乳白色,肉食干爽结实.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　144.上班族因应酬推迟晚饭,在下午4-6点时如果嚼上2片钙片,就能够加倍保护胃肠道.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　145.吃完鸡蛋不要立即饮茶.茶叶中的鞣酸会与蛋白质合成鞣酸蛋白质,使肠蠕动减慢,易造成便秘.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　146.取1汤匙枸杞,用开水冲泡.20分钟后当茶喝,并吃掉枸杞,长期饮用,有利于肌肤柔嫩.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　147.加湿器最好每周清洗一次.专家介绍加湿器的水箱是个藏污垢的地方,如果不及时清洗,容易滋生细菌.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　148.睡前不宜食用巧克力及可乐,因为其中含有咖啡因,会影响睡眠质量.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　149.对于青少年和20岁左右的年轻人来说，经常运动有助于预防高血压。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　150.最新调查结果显示，每天维生素C摄取量达到200毫升的人患白内障风险可降低35％。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　151.中老年单吃钙片无效，应多吃牛奶和海产品，多晒太阳使皮肤中维生素D增加，有利于钙的吸收。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　152.用水浸泡药用小米草或母菊花，将毛巾浸湿，敷于眼部15分钟，可有效舒缓眼部疲劳。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　153.巧选茶叶：看茶叶松紧，紧而重实的质量好，看净度，茶叶中有较多茶梗。叶柄及杂质的质量差。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　154.有人吃药总是把药掰开来吃，以为药片小的利于吞咽。其实药片掰开后变尖，易划伤食道。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　155.每天早晨选1－2个新鲜的西红柿空腹蘸白糖吃，降压效果明显。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　156.失眠时可将一汤匙食醋倒入冷开水中，在加蜂蜜搅匀喝下，对帮助入睡效果很好。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　157.白醋是宝：在加了适量白醋的水中浸泡衣服能使之更白亮，在花瓶中加点糖，白醋能使鲜花保鲜。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　158.常吃芦笋能加快人体的新城代谢，促进人体内热量的消耗，因此多次新鲜芦笋能使人变得苗条。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　159.海参的储藏：将海参晒的干透，装入双层食品塑料袋中，加几颗蒜，然后扎紧袋口，悬挂在高处。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　160.巧煮面条：煮面时在水里加一汤匙油，面条就不会粘了，还能防止面汤起泡沫往外溢。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　161.鲜蛋与生姜，洋葱不能混放，生姜和洋葱有强烈的气味，易透进蛋壳上的小气孔，使鲜蛋变质。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　162.个儿使用毛巾数量最低标准为男二女三，每周消毒一次，凉挂通风处。毛巾使用期限一般为三个月。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　163.毛料衣裤穿久了会起很多小球，很不美观，可用电动剃须刀象剃胡须一样将衣服剃一遍。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　164.报纸油墨味可驱虫，在箱子底部铺一层报纸，在放入衣物，可使衣物免遭虫咬，报纸每半年换一次。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　165.煮面时不要用沸水下锅，当锅底有气泡往上冒时就可下面，搅几下盖锅煮沸，加水，在盖锅煮沸即可。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　166.塑料瓶盖拧的太紧打不开时，可将瓶子放入冰箱中冷冻一会，这样拧开就很容易了。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　167.办公室瘦身：午饭后半小时至1小时内，喝杯浓郁的不加糖咖啡，可促进脂肪燃烧。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　168.家庭急救注意:胃肠病人不可喝水进食，烧伤病人不宜喝水，昏迷病人不可强灌饮料否则易引起窒息。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　169.实验表明，在催眠效果方面，摇篮曲竟使安眠葯甘拜下风，人们在摇篮曲陪伴下会睡得特别香甜。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　170.识别色素葡萄酒，将酒摇晃后倒在餐巾纸上，如红色分布不均匀或有沉淀物，则酒是用色素兑成的。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　171.巨石内放一盆吸毒之物如吊兰，文竹等，能有效吸收二氧化碳，甲醛等有害物体，减少空气污染。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　172.炒菜时觉得辣味太重可放入一鸡蛋同炒，用铁锅炒出来的辣椒咖喱汁可防止贫血症。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　173.泡温泉每次不宜超过15分钟，每天最多不超过3次，饭后1小时内，剧烈运动后都不宜泡温泉。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　174.蔬菜防毒：竹笋食用前应用沸水煮20分钟，可去除丸成毒素，白果勿生吃，每次进食不应超过十粒。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　175.一项最新研究显示，打太极拳有助于提高糖尿病患者的免功能，能改善其对血糖的控制能力。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　176.洗枕套时可用洗发水代替洗衣粉，洗发水含有专门的去除头发污垢的成分，比用洗衣粉洗的更干净。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　177.喝白酒应先烫后饮，白酒含醛，对人的损害比酒精大，醛的沸点低，把酒烫热可使大部分醛挥发。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　178.煮水时应注意不要煮沸，冒泡即可，这样既可以将水中的细菌杀死，又不至于产生氯化物等有害物质。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　179.德国神经学家日前发表的研究报告显示，闻着玫瑰香入睡。有助于增强记忆力。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　180.在植物油类中，营养价值和健康价值较高的橄榄油，也是说发现的油脂中最适合人体的营养的油脂。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　181.在制作糖醋鱼时，应先放糖后放盐，否则食盐的脱水作用会使蛋白质凝固难将糖味吃透，造成外甜里淡。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　182.南瓜有润肺益气，化痰，止喘利尿，美容等功能，可预防和治疗动脉硬化，胃粘膜溃疡等疾病。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　183.不要长时间使用裕霸，耀眼的灯光会干扰人体大脑的中枢神经功能，让人头晕目眩，食欲下降。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　184.洗衣机洗完衣服后应开着盖，关上盖子不利于残留水分的蒸发，易滋生霉菌，危害健康。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　185.核桃富含多种维生素及胡萝卜素，每天吃3个核桃能使低密度胆固醇数值降低5％，可有效预防心脏病。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　186.巧去竹笋有涩味，竹笋连皮放在淘米水中加去籽红辣椒一个，中火煮，自然冷却后在取出冲洗，剥皮。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　187.炒土豆时加醋，又可分解土豆中的毒素，炒鸡蛋时加几滴醋，炒出的鸡蛋松软味香。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　188.巧克力含有多种丰富的抗氧化物，如可可多酚，类黄酮，适量摄取对皮肤有益。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　189.喝绿茶或使用含绿茶成分保养品，可使日晒导致皮肤晒伤，松弛和粗糙的过氧化物减少约三分之一。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　190.用糖凉拌西红柿时，放少许盐会更甜，因为盐能改变其酸糖比。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　191.西瓜汁对预防醉酒十分有效，因为西瓜汁会对酒精产生竞争性抑制，减少酒精进入血液的数量&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　192.每天嚼口香糖十分钟，可使面部鱼尾纹减少，因为咀嚼能锻炼面部肌肉改善面部的血液循环。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　193.在感冒发烧的时候喝上一杯鲜榨的菠萝汁，有助于退烧，还能有效降低患支气管炎的风险。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　194.把橘皮放入热水中浸泡。用此水洗脸沐浴，能滋润和改善皮肤粗糙状况。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　195.葱有清除血管内淤血块的作用，能降低血液中胆固醇含量，防止血液黏稠，从而防治动脉硬化。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　196.夏天茶叶若生霉，切忌在阳光下晒，放在锅中干培10分钟左右，味道即可恢复，但火不宜过大。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　197.铁锅忌煮绿豆汤，杨梅，山楂，海棠等酸性果品 ，忌盛食物过夜，还不宜煮汤。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　198.眼科专家提醒，树脂镜片表面磨损，如果&ldquo;超期服役&rdquo;很可能加速眼睛近视。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　199.夏天，酱油容易变质，剥几瓣生大蒜放入瓶里，酱油既不发霉也不会有怪味。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　200.西瓜皮含维他命C，冰敷在皮肤晒红的皮肤上，可以镇定，温润皮肤，芦荟也有同样的功效。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　201.空腹吃冷饮，对胃粘膜有刺激，会导致胃炎，而刚吃饱饭吃冷饮，会造成胃内环境紊乱，影响消化。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　202.每天四次短距离散步降压效果好，每天进行4次10分钟散步，降压效果能持续11个小时。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　203.居室内切忌摆放月季花，因为月季花的香味会使人闻后突然感到胸闷不适，憋气。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　204.太阳镜不宜镜面过大，镜面弧度越大折射率变化越大，长期佩戴易使眼睛疲劳，干涩，损伤视力。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　205.牛奶的酸性对皮肤有消炎收敛的作用，用冷牛奶外敷，可以修复晒伤的皮肤。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　207.樱桃的铁含量高，常吃可提高血红蛋白含量，让人面色红润。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　208.忌空腹吃菠萝，菠萝里含有强嘋素，空腹吃会伤肠胃，饭后吃才能更好的吸收其营养。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　209.芒果含有丰富的水分，多次芒果会让皮肤变得细腻红润，另外，芒果富含维生素，有明目的作用。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　210.烧菜时不可用白酒代替料酒，料酒加热能与溶解脂肪产生醋化作用，增鲜提味，白酒无此作用。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　211.炖牛肉想炖的快，炖的烂，可用纱布把茶叶包起来入锅同煮，肉很快就烂且味道鲜美。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　212.新衣服必须用食盐浸泡后洗洗再穿，因为新衣服做防皱处理后可能会残留致癌化学药品甲醛。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　213.黄瓜肉质脆嫩，汁多味甘，富含维生素，能美白肌肤，保持肌肤弹性，抑制黑色素形成。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　214.就餐时可听听优雅的音乐，优雅的音乐能提高副交感神经作用，促进消化和吸收。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　215.汽水与酒同饮，会加强对胃黏膜的刺激，减少胃酸及消化酶的分泌，导致急性肠胃炎。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　216.水火烫伤时，迅速把清凉油涂抹再伤面上，有止痛和防止起泡的功效。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　217.豆腐或豆腐干等豆制品往往有股泔水味，若在烹制前用盐开水浸泡，可去除异味。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　218.莴笋能刺激消化液的分泌，促进食欲，莴笋还具有镇静的作用，经常食用有助于消除紧张，帮助睡眠。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　219.猪肉上沾上粘土或脏污物，用清水很难洗净，若用淘米水浸泡数分钟再洗，赃物即可洗净。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　220.科学家称，鸡蛋中的不饱和脂肪酸可降低胆固醇，对心血管系统有特殊的保护作用。</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('22','19','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>&nbsp;1，对方全责提出私了1500，你死活不干，要求走保险，又是吵又是闹又是折腾，定损2200，修理厂要求2400，自掏200.</p>\r\n<div>如果你同意私了，拿1500，报保险自己全责，车照样修好一文不掏白赚1500，第二年保费增加800，赚了700</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 2.撞伤一人，送医院，被家属打骂，垫医药费8000。回家洗洗脸上的血痕。回头家属要求加10000私了，否则不给你医药发票，保险公司说没发票不给你报销，哦或。悲剧。其实你可以不去医院，现场等待交警出具处理意见。垫医药费就说炒股亏了，现在还欠起外债，等家属告你，告完保险公司全赔，皆大欢喜，你甚至不用出现。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 3.撞车了，后面堵起一排车狂按喇叭，对方说我全责，我们退到路边处理，于是停到路边，结果对方马上变脸，说你丫的全责，这时候才想起应该先手机照相。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 4.老公指挥倒车，自己一激动，油门当刹车，把老公双腿撞断，打电话给保险公司老老实实的上报，保险公司告诉你，老公不陪。。。。。其实你可以换个朋友的车撞。。你懂&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 5.车子在4s保养，保养完了，高高兴兴去取车，哦或，倒车时油门又当刹车（为什么是又=。=！），撞的稀里哗啦，造成损失4000+，你郁闷的找保险公司，人家礼貌的告诉你，在修理厂发生的事故，俺们不陪。。。。其实你可以换个地方发生事故，比如小区内和某小树发生亲密接触，你懂。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 6.大雨天，早上去happy的去车库取车，发现车库被淹了，顿时泪流满面，赶快上车发动，让自己的车车逃离苦海，一点火，哦或，发动机打不燃。车没逃离苦海，你也进了苦海，4s店告知，发动机进水，报销，损失5w，你兴冲冲的去找保险公司，别个怜悯的看着你，小姐，驾驶员强行打火导致发动机进水，俺们不陪。&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;你不点火，发动机是不会进水的哦亲。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 7，在车上放了好多好多玩具，什么宝塔啊，香水瓶啊，小熊啊小猪啊。有一天差点撞到一个老太，一脚急刹车，香水瓶飞起来干到玻璃又弹到俺额头上。缝8针，玻璃费误工费医药费精神损失费共计3800，保险公司的接线员笑眯眯的告诉你，被车上物品撞坏不赔：如果车辆被车厢内或车顶装载的物品击伤，俺们还是不陪。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 8,周末天气好爽，正在happy的飙车，左方一大货车突然一盘子甩到你道上和你kiss了一下，你只有一盘子打到花坛上，你小心肝扑通扑通的隔了5分钟才安静下来，一看大货车早没影了，马上打电话给保险员把大货车狂决一顿，并表示想要修车，保险员遗憾的告诉你把负全责的肇事人放跑了不赔：当与其他车辆发生碰撞时，责任在对方，如果放弃向第三方追偿的权利，也就放弃了向保险公司要求赔偿的权利哦亲。&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;其实你可以说，太阳晃花了我的眼，让我上了花坛，什么大货车？没看到~没注意。。。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 9，路上爆胎，左转右转稳住方向，不用打电话给保险公司了，别个不陪。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 10，停在楼下，上楼看了一集康熙来了，下楼一看，4个轮子没了，几块板砖给俺垫着，不用打电话给保险了，别个不陪。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>教你榨干保险公司最后一滴血</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>前言：相信还有许多车主对汽车保险了解不深，只有出了事故才会和汽车保险打交道，而作为外行的车主们根本不能摸清楚汽车保险的水究竟有多深，该如何处理才能成为最大程度的受益人呢？别着急，已经有许多身经百战、经验丰富的车主们为我们总结了他们的心得，我们只要阅读收藏以备不时之需就可以了，况且这是一份普通车主们就能读懂的汽车保险条文，保证能让你更深入地了解汽车保险和理赔，&ldquo;榨干&rdquo;保险公司的最后一滴血！谁说不是呢？买保险就图的省钱和省心！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>保险条款精解（一）车损险 VS 第三者责任险</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>咱们先说说最主要的车损险和三责险。车损险和三责险是车辆保险的基本险，主要赔偿被保险车辆的损失以及由被保险车辆在使用中给第三者带来的损失！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>您大概觉得即使是自然灾害造成的车辆损失，保险公司也照赔不误！这话对了一半，大部分的自然灾害造成的损失都赔，惟独一样除外&mdash;&mdash;地震！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例1：如果您的车有幸在地震中被建筑物砸到的话，哈哈&hellip;&hellip;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应对方法：不要在地震一结束就急于申请赔偿，等地震过后几天再申请赔偿。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>出险陈述：大概由于地震造成墙体松动，终于在某一天倒下了，砸坏了您的爱车，切记：千万不要提及地震时出险。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例2：如果您的爱车在一次急刹车中，车里的东西飞到了风挡上造成玻璃破裂，您该怎么说呢？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>假如您老老实实的对保险公司说：&ldquo;我的纸巾盒飞起来打中了玻璃&hellip;&hellip;&rdquo;（哗！内功够高啊，呵呵，本人只是以纸巾盒举个例子开个玩笑。）&rdquo;那么你惨了！那个理赔员会指着自己的嘴对您说：&ldquo;请看我的口型&mdash;&mdash;NO！&rdquo;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应对方法：小小的改变一下事实&hellip;&hellip;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>出险陈述：我的一个练过铁头功的朋友在刹车时撞碎了风挡，OK！记住：受车内&ldquo;物品&rdquo;的撞击所受损失，保险公司不赔的！但是人撞坏的就另当别论。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例3：如果您的车在拖车时与别的车发生了碰撞，怎么办？</div>\r\n<div>应对方法：忽略一些事实存在的东西&hellip;&hellip;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>出险陈述：别提你在拖带车辆或者被别人拖带，否则不管你有没有事故责任，保险公司一律不赔。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例4：如果你在事故时，打破了自己的玻璃又没有上玻璃险时，你会向保险公司索赔吗？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>没上玻璃险找人家索赔能行吗？行，绝对行！玻璃险的全称是：玻璃单独破碎险，是指停车和使用时造成的玻璃损坏，而事故造成的玻璃损坏应由车损险来负责赔付。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>如果您没上玻璃险，当您早上起来发现自己的汽车玻璃不知道被哪个混蛋打破了，怎么办呢？？呵呵，老招法：开车时急刹车造成的，又是脑袋惹的祸！（记得找一个身高差不多的朋友来当挡箭牌啊），如果是侧面的玻璃破了，就说侧滑时脑袋撞的好了，呵呵！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例5：如果您的车在撞车时，打破了一个小灯，您该怎么办呢？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>找保险公司，他绝对不敢不赔您，那么您以为是赚到了吗？不是的，实际上您大概要赔了，亏本了。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>没听明白？告诉您，每辆车的全险大概在2500-5000之间（更高档的车会更贵），如果您在一年的保险期内没有索赔，那么您将在下一年投保时获得10%的无赔款优待，这笔帐您自己算算，如果索赔数额太小，哎，就这样算了吧，不如10%的折扣来的实在。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>------------------------------华丽分割--------------------------------</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>保险条款精解(二) 丢车&mdash;&mdash;如何将损失降到最低点？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>车辆在停放和使用的过程中难免会让人有烦心的事，其中，丢车是最倒霉的事了，不过，如果你按照我说的去做，您的损失会降到最低点。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>记得啊，一旦丢车，要做的第一件事情是什么？报警？错！车已经丢了，哪那么容易立刻找到啊，您也未免太高估中国警察的能力了，还是想想怎么减少损失吧！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>减少损失？哪那么容易啊，车都丢了，怎么减啊？别忘了，有我呢！！！！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>首先记得先看看自己的保险单里有没有上车辆盗抢险。什么，没有？那你认倒霉吧，找我也没用了，再买一辆吧！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>如果你上了盗抢险，首先，我要恭喜你，你的损失可以降到最低了，不过，也要小心啊！这时你要做的是闭紧你的嘴，踏踏实实的看完我的帖子，否则你一定会后悔的！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例1：盗抢险中规定，被保险人丢失行驶证、购车原始发票、车辆购置附加费凭证每一项增加0.5%的绝对免赔。丢失车钥匙增加5%的绝对免赔。这些规定在保险单中用颜色最浅的字体印刷，不信，您可以拿出单子仔细看看，肯定在某个不显眼的角落里能发现这段话。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>所以不管你是否有一把备用钥匙曾经丢失过，或者是在您被开跑了的车里有一把钥匙，请您记住一定要忘记这件事，否则&hellip;&hellip;5%的损失您自己扛定了！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例2：如果您的车在收费停车场或营业性修理厂中被盗，保险公司负责赔偿吗？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>答案是：不赔！！因为上述场所对车辆有保管的责任，在保管期间，因保管人保管不善造成车辆损毁、丢失的，保管人应承担责任。保险公司不负责赔偿。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>所以正确的方式是找停车场去索赔，所以，每次停车时记得收好停车费收据啊，虽然上面印着丢失不管，但根据我国合同法中关于格式合同的规定，这属于单方面推卸自己应负的责任！你尽管放心大胆的告他好了，呵呵，给您一个好消息，已经有人打赢了这样的官司，所以根据案件推溯的原则，以后的案件审判可以依照这个案例来判决，哈哈！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例3：如果，停车场是您的朋友开的，或者您从侧面打听到这个停车场根本无力赔付您的爱车，您是否可以考虑改变一下丢车的地点呢？哈哈，我可什么都没说啊！您自己琢磨去吧。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例4：再有，如果您是一位老板，因为一些账目上的问题和朋友闹翻，而您的朋友又是一位小人，他偷偷把您的车偷走了，您猜到会是他干的，您会找保险公司赔偿吗？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>告诉您，保险公司可不负责赔偿。因为条款规定：被保险人因与他人的民事、经济纠纷而致车辆被抢、被盗为责任免除。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>所以，您大可忘记您的经济纠纷，直接到公安局和法院报案，记住，千万别说出您的怀疑对象，否则就会把经济问题扯进来了，以中国法院的工作效率，您大概半年之内得打车出门了！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例5：如果您刚买了一辆新车，上了全险，但没有来得及领牌照（现在的交管规定：验车后的15个工作日后方可领牌证），出险后保险公司负责赔偿吗？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>不负责赔偿。因为在出险时，保险车辆必须具备两个条件，一是保险车辆须有公安交通管理部门核发的行驶证或号牌，二是在规定期间内经公安交通管理部门检验合格。但一般经特别约定对公安部门规定需先保险后检验核发号牌的新入户车辆可负责车损险和三责险。所以负责丢车赔偿的盗抢险并没有生效，自然，您也得不到赔偿。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>看来如果您不是仗着胆子改一下丢失的时间，新买的车就算送人了！我可又什么都没说啊！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例6：如果您的车失而复得，保险公司如何处理赔款？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>被盗抢的保险车辆找回后，如果保险公司尚未赔款的，应将该车辆归还给您，但是全车被盗抢期间，车辆受到的损坏或车上零部件、附属设备丢失需要修复的合理费用，保险公司负责赔偿。如果保险公司已经赔偿，应将车辆归还您，同时收回相应赔款。若您不愿收回原车，则车辆的所有权益归保险公司。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>--------------------------华丽分割------------------------------</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>保险条款精解（三） 撞车</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>只要是撞车，保险公司全赔吗？当然不是你只要认真看看手里的保单赔偿免责条款就知道了，保险公司有一大堆不赔的东西呢，想把损失降到最低，还是来找我吧，哈哈！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例1：假设你是一个新手，刚借了一辆车（当然也没准是租的车），在路上练车的时候，把你弟弟给撞了，你知道这辆车有三责险，你会找保险公司索赔吗？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>答案：如果你去了，你就是神经病，保险公司会一脚把你踢出去，为什么？？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>首先，你要知道什么是三责险，全称：第三者责任险。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>那什么是第三者呢？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>第三者指除保险人与被保险人之外的，因保险车辆的意外事故致使保险车辆下的人员或财产遭受损害的在车下的受害人。通俗的讲第三者就是排除四种人：即保险人、被保险人、本车发生事故时的驾驶员及其家庭成员、被保险人的家庭成员。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>现在明白了，你作为当时的驾驶员，撞伤你的家人，保险公司是不赔的，好了，你知道该怎么办了！什么？还不知道？气死我了，换个驾驶员撞的不就完了嘛，真是的，害我什么都说出来了。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例2：如果您有幸开车撞人了，而且全是您的责任，法院判您赔偿您包赔对方的经济损失、精神损失费、伤残损失费&hellip;&hellip;你该如何处理呢？？还能怎么样，给钱就是了！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>错！大错特错！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>你应该和对方家人商量，加大经济损失赔偿和伤残损失赔偿，尽量把精神赔偿降到最低，没有当然就更好了。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>为什么？你问我为什么？这不是五马换六羊嘛。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>老兄，你又错了，保险公司不是无条件地完全承担&ldquo;被保险人依法应当支付的赔偿金额&rdquo;，而是依照《道路交通事故处理办法》及保险合同的规定给予赔偿。而条款明确规定，因保险事故引起的任何有关精神损害赔偿为责任免除。所以无论法院判决被保险人是否应赔偿精神损失，保险公司均不负责赔偿。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>明白了？？别的保险公司都替你赔，精神损失可不管，所以，宁可多给对方点钱，也别答应精神赔偿，总之，慷保险公司之慨呗，呵呵！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例3：如果你又有幸撞车了，这回不是您的责任，而对方又不想赔钱，您可以找保险公司索赔吗？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>答案：可以，不过您必须先向第三方索赔，才有可能获得保险公司的赔偿。如果您放弃了向第三方索赔的权利，而直接向保险公司索赔，保险公司不赔。因为您放弃了向第三方追偿的权利，同时也就放弃了向保险公司要求赔偿的权利。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>所以，切记，切记，一定要先找对方赔，最好是有法庭的强制执行未果的证明，然后您就可以理直气壮的找保险公司了，剩下的烂摊子尽管让它们收拾去吧，谁让它们每年收了您那么多的保险费呢！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例4：记得以前有个倒霉的司机在警察的指挥下，帮助警察拦截正在逃窜的罪犯，撞向了罪犯，结果两车相撞，那叫一个惨啊，保险公司会赔他吗？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>当然不会啦，保险条款写的明明白白，驾驶员的&ldquo;故意行为&rdquo;不在赔偿之列，所以只能自己修车了：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>所以，如果您没有足够的经济能力，在当英雄之前要考虑一下噢！！！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>---------------------------华丽分割----------------------------</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>保险条款精解（四）索赔&mdash;&mdash;不可不看，因为您以前可能没听说过</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>★保险案例一：一位朋友丢失爱车，已上全险，找保险公司索赔，未果，保险公司拒赔理由：到车管所查询，此车未年检。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例分析：保险公司所做所为，十分合理，于保险合同条文也有根据：保险只对合格车辆生效，对于未年检的车辆只能视为不合格车辆，就算您保养的再好也没用，结果只能是丢了白丢，保险也上了白上，顶多退回保险现金价值。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例结论：您的爱车，千万要按时年检，切不可后延，否则，罚款事小，拒赔事大，此时即使发生交通事故造成第三者损失，也将由您自己承担，保险白买了！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>案例解决办法：按时年检，即使是一天，也不要晚；如果真的发生不幸，也要记住千万不要立即报案，尽快花银子把验车手续补齐后再办理报案索赔手续！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>不好意思，刚才一阵头晕，我什么也没说吧？说了也是胡话。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>★保险案例二：与上类似，驾驶员年审未做的请注意了，您在驾驶中发生的一切问题，保险公司不负责赔偿，理由与上例相似，恕不赘述。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>★保险案例三：这是一个经常被问到的问题：我的车刚买，还没有上牌照，保险是否生效？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>解释：车辆在出险时，保险车辆必须具备两个条件，一是保险车辆须有公安交通管理部门核发的行驶证或号牌，二是在规定期间内经公安交通管理部门检验合格。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>但一般经特别约定对规定需先保险后检验核发号牌的新车辆可负责车损险和三责险，所以，这时您的车丢了就算倒霉了，撞了人啥的还算凑合有保险公司给您顶着，现在清楚了吧！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>★保险索赔证明材料原则：（因为这个问题有N人问起，所以在此一并解答）</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>保险索赔时分几种情况：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>1，事故经交通队出面解决的：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>由交通队出具处罚单或调解书，经法院判决的，用判决书即可。这些材料绝对好使，在保险公司肯定一路绿灯。放心索赔好了</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>2，在小区内发生事故的：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>重大事故：即车损严重的，还是要到交通队开证明，很麻烦；</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>一般剐蹭：到小区物业开证明，因为经常受怀疑，一般也很麻烦；</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>所以，最好报案时报在城市道路上，否则&hellip;&hellip;累死你！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>3，在道路上发生小事故的，包括停车时的剐蹭</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>此类需要证明的原则是：是否涉及第三方？如涉及第三方赔付的，还是需要交通队证明。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>如事故双方自行了断的，可以在索赔时注明：事故第三方自修，然后按车损险中的自责索赔，保险公司要是让您到交通队开证明，您一定得咬住了别松口，就说没地儿开去，保险公司一般也不会太较真。您要答应去开证明，别怪我没提醒您，您就跑去吧，赔的钱不定够不够油钱呢！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>4，最背的人：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>如果被别的车撞到后，肇事车逃逸，无法查找。情况严重的就比较麻烦，要通过交通队解决，可以由保险公司代为追偿。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>不严重的话，最好也是以自责来解决索赔问题，而且要在索赔时注意到车身是否粘有对方车油漆，以及撞的方向，一定得自圆其说，否则你惨了！</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('23','19','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>&nbsp;当你被疾病困扰的时候，当你看到这篇博文的时候，眼睛一定会为之一亮。世界上一切东西分为有用与无用，民间验方、秘方是最有用的非物质文化遗产，这是咱们老祖宗留给我们的经验终结、是无价国宝。这用数字能量治病是否管用？实践是检验偏方的唯一标准， 冀公搜集整理应用民间偏方四十余载，第一次看到如此神奇的治病方法，希望网友们实践后在网上留言，以辨真伪，造福广大网友。具体做法：可以出声念，也可以默念，还可以自己为别人或别人为自己代念，站、坐、躺、卧皆可，念的时候尽量排除杂念，念法&ldquo;260&rdquo;应念&ldquo;二六零&rdquo;，&ldquo;80&rdquo;应念&ldquo;八零&rdquo;。</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;&ldquo;前段时间认识一位大师，他能从你的名字和手机号码中看出很多你的个人信息，包括财务、健康、人际关系以及感情婚姻等等，最令我惊讶的是，他居然说出了我最近破财的事情......当他得知我的睡眠质量不大高的时候，告诉我只要临睡前默念260和80这两组数字就可以了。回去后我得到一个令人惊讶的结果 --- 我很快就睡着了而且晚上不再做梦，白天精神非常好！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp;我把这个事情告诉了我的几个亲戚朋友，试用了之后都说很神奇，有个表妹还用这两组数字治好了困扰多时的失眠症（因为工作压力大），真是太好了！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp;当然，这是咱们老祖宗留给我们的遗产、国宝，不敢独享，希望有更多有缘人能学会这个既简单又实用又高效的好梦秘诀。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>例如，人民大学金一女士自述说： &ldquo;1999年下半年，我的腰腿疼发展到生活不能自理，连睡觉翻身都困难。医院检查认为主要是骨刺、椎管狭窄和椎间盘膨出压迫坐骨神经所致。为了缓解病痛，做了一个月的按摩，未见明显好转；又到轻工医院做小针刀治疗，前后开了13刀，也未见好转。无奈之际，朋友送给我一本李山玉、李建民合著的《中国八卦象教疗法》，由于对传统文化知之甚少，对八卦有误解，不太相信，没有立即采用。后来痛得没有办法，一日深夜把这本书找出来，从中选了一个和自己腰腿痛相似的病例处方650．00700，认真念起来，没想到奇迹很快出现了，早晨起床时疼痛减轻，这增加了念数治病的信心和决心。于是天天念此方，每天至少念二、三小时，二十多天便可到操场散步了，每日能走一千六至二千米，无任何不适。更令人高兴的是，至今将近十年了，腰腿疼没有犯过一次。就这样未用一分钱，未受一点皮肉之苦，轻而易举地把病根治了。念数时，心态、形态自然，随时随地地进行，不受时间、地点、方位的限制，也不需他人暗示和诱导，更不需要特殊的气场，想念就念，想停就停。只要轻松自如地默念一组适合自己病情的数字，便可治病疗疾。如风寒感冒只要念80．60．50，或其他治此病的处方，不但可以治而且可以防。它不仅能治疗一般身心疾病，也可治愈包括癌症在内的疑难杂症。如北京海淀区一位患胰头癌的病人，确诊后未去医院治疗，单凭默念山玉大夫给的处方，不到半年时间使肿瘤消失得无影无踪，连医生都惊呼不可思议! 象数疗法还可以一方治多病，即异病同治，如折磨我二十多年的胆囊炎和胆结石，学用象数疗法之前天天吃&lsquo;消炎利胆&rsquo;，有时还控制不好，曾两次患胆心综合症到医院急诊。学了象数疗法之后，未专门配方治疗它，却在不知不觉中彻底好了，已有七、八年没有病状，也无需用药了。象数疗法不但可以治疗慢性病，也可治急症，效果快得惊人。我的足踝有旧伤，时常走路时突然疼痛起来，这时只要念0004000，不过五分钟就好了。再如2007年3月27日，吃过中饭之后，突然恶心呕吐起来，过了一会，又开始腹泻。我深信象数疗法，胸中有数，心里不慌，加之上吐下泻去医院很不方便，便决定自我治疗。我躺在沙发上，开始念650．30．820，并大量饮水。开始吐、泻的是食物，后来便全是清水。令人欣喜的是到下午四点，吐泻骤然停止了，前后只有3小时。我本以为这么严重的肠胃病，肯定要卧床休息几天才能恢复体力，令人惊奇的是，当时站起来行走，自感腿脚有力，全身轻松自如，像没有病过一样。自己做了晚饭，饭后还外出散步近一小时。更令我欣慰的是象数疗法还治愈了我的脑梗。2003年之前，时常头晕头痛，嘴唇发麻，手指尖抽搐，经北大医院神经内科确诊为腔隙性脑梗，当时打了吊针，症状消失。同年秋季又出现同样症状，又打了吊针。从2004年开始，决定用象数疗法治疗，一旦出现症状便在第一时间念数治疗，根据身体情况，开始念的是0001000．260．4450．380，后来改念0001000，260．40．70，多则几天，少则几个小时，甚至一个小时，便可消除症状。几年来未曾去医院，都是自行解决的。这说明只要自己契而不舍地坚持念数治疗，就能取得满意的效果。去年七月之后未再犯病，四年半中未去医院，不仅省时省事，也为国家节约了相当数量的医药费，还避免了交叉感染和药物的副作用。&rdquo;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>治肺病数字配方 820</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;这个配方非常简单，按中医来论就是，肺金有病，找其母，所以&ldquo;培土生金&rdquo;。默念 820</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>腰痛数字配方 &nbsp;650 38000</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;因寒湿而腰痛，可用此数字配方。默念 650 38000</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>数字能量治病：牙痛数字配方 &nbsp;70 &nbsp;00200</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>数字：70 &nbsp;00200</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>头晕数字配方 710 &nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>这组数字可用于晕车。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>眼睛发热红肿或有炎症 003</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>如果熬夜，或其它原因导致肝阳上亢，引起眼睛热气不舒服，可用数字配方：003</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>痛经数字配方 &nbsp;720 &nbsp;60</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>不通则痛。先通气，再利水路。有痛经的女生快点抄下来啊。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>咳嗽数字配方 70 260 50</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>万事万物皆有能量。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>数字也是如此。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>小孩因受风寒咳嗽不止，不能入睡，数字配方：70 260 50。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>大人抱小孩默念五分钟即见效，停止咳嗽入睡。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>亲爱的朋友，看到这里，还不赶快把这数字配方抄下来，没准能帮上你的忙哦。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>这组数字对一般的风寒咳嗽都有效果。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>口腔溃疡、喉咙痛数字配方 &nbsp;002 &nbsp;050 &nbsp;070</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>春天木旺，肝阳上升，易上火，有许多人易患口腔溃疡、喉咙痛等疾，配以数字配方： &nbsp;002 &nbsp;050 &nbsp;070</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>颈椎病的治疗&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　用药药方：2650&middot;380</div>\r\n<div>　　适用病症：因长期从事伏案工作、长期从事电脑工作、受凉以及劳损等原因造成的颈椎突出等病疼。</div>\r\n<div>　　服药方式：默念(嘴要动)，中间顿点表示默念时稍停顿。</div>\r\n<div>　　服药时间：随时随地均可默念，但要集中精神，睡觉前效果最好。</div>\r\n<div>　　验证特征：坚持十五天痛感消失。如法坚持则还你一个健康的颈椎。</div>\r\n<div>　　注意事项：若默念上述数字时，出现心慌、头痛或出虚汗等症状之一，则马上停止默念即可。</div>\r\n<div>　　用药原理：颈椎号称&ldquo;小腰&rdquo;，全力支撑人的头部，血液、神经等集束必经之地，颈椎出了毛病，将会影响血液和神经的畅通，必酿严重后患！俗话说&ldquo;四十颈椎五十瘫，六十难免上西天&rdquo;正是此意。本方秉持&ldquo;君臣佐使，辩证施治&rdquo;之用药原则，结合《中医藏象学说》、《阴阳五行学说》和《周易八卦理论》配制而成：2&mdash;&mdash;兑卦，属金，相肺，主肃降、体表和毛发等;6&mdash;&mdash;坎卦，属水，相肾，主吸纳、润下等;5&mdash;&mdash;巽卦，属阳木，相胆，主疏泻、条达等;3&mdash;&mdash;离卦，属火，相心，主温热、炎上和血液等;8&mdash;&mdash;坤卦，属阴土，相脾，主运输、营运全身等;各加一个零，属奇数，振奋疏通对应阳气;2650&mdash;&mdash;呈金生水、水生木之势，肝胆相照、肝肾同源，木是阳木，力为奇数，肃降和吸纳相结合，振奋肾阳力度适中;380&mdash;&mdash;呈火生土之势，增强气血、强化运化密布全身的能力。剂量适中，火候老到，综合施力，重点突出，达到重新调理阴阳平衡、重点施治之功效。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　胃疼的治疗&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　用药药方：70&middot;40</div>\r\n<div>　　适用病症：因长期精神紧张、思虑过多、压力过大、饮食无规律等原因造成的胃痛病。</div>\r\n<div>　　服药方式：默念(嘴要动)：七零四零，中间顿点表示默念时稍停顿。</div>\r\n<div>　　服药时间：随时随地均可默念，但要集中精神，睡觉前效果最好。</div>\r\n<div>　　验证特征：如果胃痛发作，集中精力默念该数字，三分钟内痛感消失。如法坚持则还你一个健康的胃。</div>\r\n<div>　　注意事项：若默念上述数字时，出现心慌、头痛或出虚汗等症状之一，则马上停止默念即可。</div>\r\n<div>　　用药原理：秉持&ldquo;君臣佐使，辩证施治&rdquo;之用药原则，结合《中医藏象学说》、《阴阳五行学说》和《周易八卦理论》配制而成：7&mdash;&mdash;八卦数为艮，为土，为阳土，为胃。后加一个零，为奇数零，目的是振奋胃阳，增加胃蠕动;4&mdash;&mdash;八卦数为震，为木，为阴木，为肝，肝有疏泻、条达之功能。后加一个奇数零，强化肝之功能，达到&ldquo;变则通&rdquo;的效果，使胃健康有序的工作起来。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　 &nbsp;亚健康的治疗</div>\r\n<div>　　用药药方：20&middot;650&middot;380</div>\r\n<div>　　适用病症：高血脂、肥胖;不明原因乏力、头痛、失眠、晕眩、胸闷、心悸、自汗、盗汗、阳痿、多梦、出虚汗、多关节痛、月经不调、黄褐斑;舌尖发红，舌苔细腻，口苦、咽干，大便干燥、小便短赤;面色无华，憔悴;双目周围特别是眼下灰暗发青;晨起或劳累后足踝及小腿肿胀、下眼皮肿胀、下垂;胸腹胀满、大便粘结不畅、肛门湿热之感，口中粘滞不爽，吐之为快;突感视力下降等。</div>\r\n<div>　　服药方式：默念(嘴要动)：二零六五零三八零，中间顿点表示默念时稍停顿。</div>\r\n<div>　　服药时间：随时随地均可默念，但要集中精神，睡觉前效果最好。</div>\r\n<div>　　验证特征：快则十天即有明显效果：精神有力、睡眠质量提高等各项症状不同程度的缓解;宜于长期坚持，直至症状消失。</div>\r\n<div>　　注意事项：若默念上述数字时，出现心慌、头痛或出虚汗等症状之一，则马上停止默念即可。</div>\r\n<div>　　用药原理：秉持&ldquo;君臣佐使，辩证施治&rdquo;之用药原则，结合《中医藏象学说》、《阴阳五行学说》和《周易八卦理论》配制而成：2&mdash;&mdash;兑卦，属金，相肺，主肃降、体表和毛发等;6&mdash;&mdash;坎卦，属水，相肾，主吸纳、润下等;5&mdash;&mdash;巽卦，属阳木，相胆，主疏泻、条达等;3&mdash;&mdash;离卦，属火，相心，主温热、炎上和血液等;8&mdash;&mdash;坤卦，属阴土，相脾，主运输、营运全身和肚腹等;各加一个零，属奇数，振奋疏通对应阳气;650&mdash;&mdash;呈水生木之势，肝胆相照、肝肾同源，木是阳木，力为奇数，振奋肾阳适中;380&mdash;&mdash;呈火生土之势，增强气血、强化运化密布全身的能力。剂量适中，火候老到，综合施力，达到重新调理阴阳平衡之功效。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>1、失眠配方</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　一、心功能障碍，失眠，多梦，健忘。配方：30, 80。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　二、心脾两虚，失眠，心悸健忘，身倦乏力，食少无味，舌苔白，脉细弱。配方：1）80,260。2）030,70。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　三、心肾不交，虚烦不眠，心悸健忘，头晕耳鸣，咽干，腰酸遗精，或骨蒸盗汗，手足心热，舌红苔少，脉细弱，尺浮。配方：400。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　四、肝郁火旺，失眠，心悸，头晕，耳鸣，急燥易怒，精神抑郁，舌红苔黄，脉弦数。配方：1）400，60。2）600，700。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　五、肝阳上亢，高血压，头重脚轻，失眠{多为老人}。配方：1）160,40,70。2）640,70,010。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　六、肾阴虚;贫血，心烦失眠，或易怒，口干少津，胃纳不佳，或盗汗，舌红苔少，脉弦细。配方：1）640，030。 2）400，80，60。如耳鸣，憋闷，头晕头痛：004300，82000，60。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　七、肾虚阳亢，失眠，头晕目眩，五心烦热，盗汗。配方：640。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　八、阴虚失眠，口干，失眠，心烦，记忆力减退{多为老年}。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：1）260。2）260，40，780。3）640，780，20。4）60，450，70。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　九、肾精亏少;失眠，头晕，健忘，思维迟钝;配方：20，650，30，80。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　十、气血两亏;失眠，头晕头痛;配方：1）200，60。2）650。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　十一、阴阳两虚;体弱多病，失眠，{多为老年}。配方：1）640，380。2）260，4380。3）640，720。4）40，820。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　注意：选用配方时一定要对症选方，一症多方的要注意试方，选对心、头、胃没有副作用的配方持念。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>2、诸伤止痛方</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　一、肤外伤，或挫伤，或术后伤口痛。配方：2000/80，20/82000，6000，7000/650，30，720。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　二、刀伤止血：7000/003，7000/2000，70/7000，6000。三、烫伤：003，700，050/002，005，007。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　四、犬咬伤：0002000，80。五、岔气：4000/4000，260。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　六、骨折，锁骨骨折：720，650，380 /4440，7770，80。腰椎压缩性骨折：6660，70 / 7000，20，60。脊椎骨砸伤：0001000。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　 3、腰部止痛方</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　一、寒湿腰痛;多由于久居冷湿之地，或冒雨涉水，劳汗当风，衣着冷湿都可感受寒湿之邪，寒邪凝滞收引，湿邪粘聚不化，致腰腿经脉收阻，气血运行不畅，因而发生腰痛。遇阴雨天加重。治法：散寒祛湿，温经通络。配方：6000，38000 / 650，30，80 / 660，550，380</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　二、湿热腰痛;多为外感湿热之邪，或素体阳盛感受湿邪，郁久化热，阻遏经脉，引起腰痛。痛处有热感，热天或阴雨天加重，而活动后可减轻，小便短赤，苔黄腻，脉濡数或弦数。治法;清热利湿，疏筋止痛。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：6660，4000 / 6000，40 / 070，640。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　三、瘀血腰痛;跌扑外伤,损伤气血,或因病气血运行不畅,脉络受阻,瘀血留着腰部,引起腰痛.疼痛如刺,痛有定处,日轻夜重,轻则俯仰不便,重则不能转侧,痛处拒按,舌质紫暗,或有瘀斑,脉涩。治法：活血化瘀,理气止痛。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：650,070 / 60,050,70 /60,00400,70</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　四、肾虚腰痛，多因先天禀赋不足,或劳累过度,强力伤肾.也有因房室不节,以致肾精亏损,无力濡养筋脉而致腰痛.痛感以酸软为主,喜按喜揉,腿膝无力,劳则加重,休息减轻,常反复发作,偏阳虚者,多伴见少腹拘急,面色皎白,手足不温,少气无力,舌淡,脉沉细;偏阴虚者,多伴有心烦失眠,口燥咽干,面色潮红,手足心热,舌红少苔,脉弦数。</div>\r\n<div>　　治法：1、偏阳虚，温补肾阳。配方：650,7000 /6000,5000 / 65000。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　2、偏阴虚，滋补肾阴。配方：6400,7000 / 2600,400,70 / 00600,00400,070。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;4、咽喉止痛方</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　一、紧喉风：此症声音难出，咽喉肿痛，痰症壅塞之声，如似拽锯，初发暴速。治法：清热疏风。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：0070，0050 / 400，500，200 / 2600，500，700。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　二、慢喉风：多见于体虚之人，或因七情所伤或因过食五辛所致。发病缓慢，喉部色淡微肿，咽干微痛，舌滑白苔，大便自利，六脉微细。治法：补中益气，导滞。配方：070，060，050 / 60，820，050 / 400，720。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　三、喉闭痛：由肝肺火盛，复受风寒相搏所致。咽喉肿痛，面赤腮肿，甚则项外漫肿，喉中有块如拳，汤水不能咽下，语言不出，身发寒热。治法;平肝润肺，清火排毒。配方;004，007，002，00600 / 040，050，2600，/0720，60000</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　5、牙部止痛方</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　一、实火牙痛：以胃肠，肝胆邪火为常见，其症疼痛剧烈，牙疼多伴有头痛，发热，目赤，口苦口干，渴喜冷饮，烦躁便秘，舌红苔黄，脉数实等，也会出现牙龈或牙关肿痛，甚或出血或化脓，症见赤肿而出血者，为病在血分，不出血者为病在气分。治法：泄实止痛。配方：050，070 / 00500，00700 / 007,003,600。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　二、虚火牙痛：痛而隐隐绵长，不若实火牙痛之剧，甚或可见牙根松动，或浮露于上，但牙龈并不灼肿，有时兼见咽干，咽痛，心烦不眠，耳鸣目赤，舌质嫩红，脉细数等。治法：滋阴止痛。配方：00700，6400/ 2600，070 / 400，700。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　三、风热牙痛;牙痛而肿，牵连头痛，见风则疼痛加重，故有开口呻风而痛勢益增之说。治法：疏风治痛。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：500，700，20 / 007000 / 500。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　四、牙疳痛：牙龈肿腐作痛，口臭流血。治法：清胃解毒。配方：007，160，040 / 070，600，040 / 820，160，050</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　6、头部止痛配方</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　一、头痛配方</div>\r\n<div>　　1）风寒头痛：是指因风寒袭表，卫阳被遏，脉络受阻，清阳之气不升气血凝滞而发为头痛。主要证候：头痛时作，痛连项背，恶风畏寒，遇风尤剧，常喜裹头，口不渴，苔薄白，脉浮或浮紧。治法：疏风散寒。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：50，000，70/ 80，50，60/ 260，50。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　2）风热头痛：是因风热外袭，肌肤疏泄不畅，火性炎上，邪扰清窍，气血逆乱而致头痛。主要证候：头痛而胀，甚至如裂，发热恶风，面红目赤，口渴欲饮，便秘尿赤，舌苔黄，脉浮数。治法：疏风清热。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：003，006，00500/ 002，006，050。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　3）风湿头痛：风湿外侵，遏阻阳气，蒙蔽清窍，清阳不升而致头痛。主要证候：头痛如裹，肢体困重，胸闷纳呆，小便不利，大便溏薄，苔白腻，脉濡。治法;祛风胜湿。配方：2000，8 0/ 260，40，8 0/ 0005000， 80。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　4）肝阳头痛;由于情志不和，肝失条达，肝气郁结，气郁化火，日久则耗伤津液，肝阴不足，肝失濡养，或房劳伤精，肾水不足，水不涵木，致肝肾阴亏，均能引起肝肾阳上亢，&ldquo;肝为风木之脏&rdquo;火性炎上，风火相煽，上扰清空则为肝阳头痛。主要证候：头痛而眩，时作掣痛，偏于两侧，或连巅顶，心烦易怒，睡眠不宁，面红目赤，口苦或兼胁痛，舌红，苔薄黄，脉弦或弦数。治法：滋水涵木。配方：640 / 60 / 60，400，70，/ 400。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　5）肾虚头痛：为禀赋不足，房劳过度，使肾精亏虚，肾主骨生髓，髓上通于脑，脑为髓海，肾精久亏，则髓海空虚而发生头痛。若肾阴久亏，阴损及阳，则清阳不展而发为头痛。主要证候：头痛且空，每兼眩晕，腰膝酸软，遗精带下，耳鸣少寐，舌苔薄，脉沉细无力。治法：补肾添精。配方：070，260 /650，3820 /640，3820。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　6）痰浊头痛;脾失健运，痰浊中阻，清阳不升，上蒙清窍致头痛。主要证候：头痛昏蒙，胸脘满闷，呕恶痰涎，舌苔腻，脉滑或弦滑。治法：化痰降逆，健脾和胃。配方：820，40，70 /260，4000，70。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　7）淤血头痛;多发生于脑部外伤，或妇女经行不畅，或病久入络，导致气滞血淤，淤血阻于脑络，不通则痛。主要症状：头痛经久不愈，痛处固定不移，痛如锥刺，或有头部外伤史，舌有瘀斑，瘀点，脉细或细涩。治法：活血化淤。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：070，010 /00700，00100 /16000，430。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　8）巅顶痛;痛在巅顶，正当百会穴，为相火偏旺，循督脉上扰而致头痛。治法：滋阴潜阳。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：001600，00700 /640，0070。</div>\r\n<div>　</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;7、乳房止痛方</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　一、腋下结核痛;腋下结核如卵，皮色不变，多因肝气痰浊凝滞而成，俗称痰核，实即瘰疬。治法：疏肝解郁，软坚化痰。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：00400，720 / 400，000，720，/640，720。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　二、乳疖肿痛;乳房局部皮肤潮红，逐渐肿痛，结块高突呈圆形或椭圆形，约二至三天成脓，急宜调治，若延误将成乳痈。治法：清热解毒，化滞行血。配方：720，400，660 / 640，000，720 /400，700，260。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　三、经前两乳胀痛：妇女经前两乳膨胀而痛，并兼有经行不畅，周身不适感。治法：通经宣郁。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：400,00700 / 6400,700 / 060,040,070。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　四、乳多胀痛：40，720 / 0720 / 0007000。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　五、乳头裂痛：00200，00700 / 820，070，040。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp;8、前阴止痛方</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　一、男性前阴肿痛;阴囊或连阴茎包皮肿胀疼痛，甚至通明光泽，多因坐地受湿所致，尤以小儿为多见。有的包皮过紧感染也引起肿痛。治法：除湿助脾肾。配方：650，70，40 / 6000，4000，70。包皮肿痛可用：7000，200，6000。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　二、女性前阴肿痛：妇女阴户肿痛，因心，肝二经火并旺，湿热下流所致。治法：清火除湿。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：003，004，600 / 00200，00600，700。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　三、砂淋胀痛：下焦湿热蕴积，尿液受其煎熬，日积月累，尿中杂质结成砂石，则为石淋。尿中时夹砂石，小便艰涩，或排尿时突然中断，尿道窘迫疼痛，小腹拘急腰腹疼痛难忍，尿中带血。男女均可发生。</div>\r\n<div>　　治法：排石止痛。配方：60，40，0720 / 0720，6000，40 / 720，40</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　四、赤白浊初期作痛：赤白浊症多由性生活传染，男女皆患，患者尿时流秽浊如脓之物，若流出浊物粘液色赤者，谓之赤浊。小便频数，尿道口红肿，热灼且痒，紧张疼痛，排尿点滴不畅，尿色混浊如脓，着裤即成斑点，甚则心烦失眠。</div>\r\n<div>　　治法：清热解毒。配方：00600，00200 / 160，720 / 160，040，720。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; 9、肩背止痛方</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　一、风寒凝滞肩背痛：因汗出或睡眠受风，突然肩部或连肩甲部纯痛不已，牵及项部拘急不舌苔薄白，脉浮或浮紧。</div>\r\n<div>　　治法：疏风散寒，益气和血。配方：5000，820 / 50，720 /650，82000。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　二、湿痰留著肩背痛：初起自觉肩背不适，迅即疼痛，逐渐加重，活动更甚，安静时闷胀酸重，常伴有身倦气短，舌苔淡白，脉搏弦细等。治法：燥湿祛痰，益气养血。配方：80，40， /8000，2000 /820， 30。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　三、气虚痰阻肩背痛：本症多见于中老年人，平时气虚体弱，多一侧或双侧肩关节疼痛，活动不便，日轻夜重，见冷加重，遇热减轻，常伴面色不华，气短神疲，等症状，舌淡苔白，脉细弱或沉迟。治法：益气养血，通络止痛。</div>\r\n<div>　　配方：820，260 / 7000，2000 /382000，070。</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('24','19','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>&nbsp;电吹风是现代家庭的常用电器，最重要的功用是给头发定型，无论使用何种吹风工具，用于吹干湿发时，吹风机出风口离头发要有一定距离，在保证安全的前提下，对头发的伤害也小。很多人不知吹风机除吹干头发外，仍有许多妙用？</p>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　治感冒</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　感冒初期用电吹风对着鼻，口孔吹入热风，持续20分钟左右，可杀灭呼吸道内的感冒病毒，使流涕停止，能减轻和抑制感冒的发作。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　治头痛</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　当头痛或神经性头痛时，可用热毛巾缠住额头，然后用电吹风对准两侧太阳穴吹2至3分钟，头痛即可减轻或解除。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　治胃病</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　发生痉挛性胃痛时，可用电吹风对着胃部热吹片刻，胃痛便能减轻或解除。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　治腰病</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　对扭伤腰痛和肾虚腰痛有作用。患者俯卧在床上暴露腰部，用电吹风沿着两侧腰肌吹热风，每侧吹4-5分钟，每日1次，可减轻痛感。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　治肩周炎</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　用电吹风对准患处吹热风，每次5至10分钟，如能坚持，一般3周可愈。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　防治脚癣</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　有脚汗的人往往鞋内潮湿而易患脚癣，如每次穿鞋前用电吹风向鞋内吹片刻，不但使鞋穿着干燥舒适，而且还能杀灭和抑制霉菌，可防治脚癣。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　治冻疮</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　冻疮初走时，用电吹风直接吹患处，使其局部加热，每次5至10分钟，吹三四次后冻疮即见好转。如冻疮明显红肿，可在患处涂上冻疮膏后用纱布包好，再用电吹风向患处加热，可加速冻疮的治愈。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　伤口止血</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　身体的某一部位如不慎被划破出血，可立即用电吹风向伤口吹热风，短时间内就可使伤口结痂止血，对防止伤口感染和加速伤口愈合很有帮助。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　头发保健</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　每天用电吹风对头部轻轻地吹热风，同时用另一只手由前至后梳理头皮，再加以按摩，可以改善头皮下毛细血管的功能，使血液流畅，增加头皮的营养。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　鞋内干燥器</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　冬天鞋内常潮湿，但又不便干燥，用电吹风向鞋内轮流吹上5分钟，鞋内即可干燥，穿着时温暖舒适。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　瓶内干燥器</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　洗完瓶子后，干燥较慢，如沥干水滴后，将热风吹进去，不一会儿水滴皆蒸发完毕。如是细口长颈瓶，则可用一长颈漏斗把风吹入底部，形成热空气循环。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　潮湿驱赶器</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　家中的电视机、半导体收音机及录音机，在潮湿季节长久搁置不用，为避免漏电打火之弊，可用热风驱潮，延长使用寿命。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　防止镜头霉变</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　如果天气多日阴雨，照相机取出使用后，可用电吹风先将盒内吹干，待冷却后，再将照相机置入，可防止镜头霉变。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　更换电冰箱塑料磁封条套不平整时，可用电吹风在曲折处加热，稍用力拉平，再压在平板玻璃下，冷却后即平整延直。电冰箱在使用一段时间后，须化一次霜。每次化霜需要较长时间，若打开电冰箱冷冻室的小门，用电吹风向里吹热风，则可缩短化霜时间。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　让饼干香脆</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　饼干受潮后，失去了原有的脆松可口之味，假使用热风吹一阵，冷却后即可松脆如新。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　驱潮防霉</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　在梅雨季节，用电吹风对贵重书籍、磁带等物品进行驱潮防霉也是十分有效的。</div>\r\n<div>　　</div>\r\n<div>　　吹风机逐渐成为人们日常生活中的必需品，但是有些人不会使用吹风机，今天禁止偷窥就分享个大家，太实用了，你不学就可惜了。记得分享到自己的博客留着用哦。</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('25','19','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>&nbsp;现在的社会太杂乱，有时候为了保护自己，不得不强大起来。所以本站今天给大家搜集了十四种关键时刻救命的方法！一定要好好看哦！</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　1. 永远记住，你的胳膊肘是你身上最强壮的地方。如果能用，一定要用。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　2. 如果强匪问你要钱包，不要递给他。拿起钱包向远处丢。一般情况下，他会对你的钱包比对你更有兴趣。等他往那个方向转的时候，你要向相反的方向拼命地跑。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 3. 强匪抢包的时候，你不要舍不得。你包里再贵的东西都可以再买一次。但是你的生命买不来。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　4. 强匪入家门抢东西，你最好不要废话罗嗦。保持清醒。不要想和他说话分散他的注意力。他知道你想干什么。往往这样会让他更反感。也不要言语刺激，不要很多眼神接触。总的来说，一般强匪入室抢劫，他只是求财，而且越快越好。可是如果你言语刺激或者不合作，那么他就会用&rdquo;他的方式&rdquo;告诉你，现在是谁有主动权。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　5. 但是！如果你可以到你的阳台，或者一切可以和外界联系的地方， 或者听见门口有人等等，请你拿上所有能发声的东西，大声呼救。一般如果强匪发现有别人知道了他的行为，会匆忙离去。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 6. 如果有这个可能，你被丢进了后车厢。那么你要使劲踢后车灯的地方。等后车灯被踢掉以后，把你的胳膊从那个洞伸出去挥舞。开车人看不到你，但是别的车能看到。这个挽救过生命。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　7. 如果你喜欢买东西，吃饭，下班以后回你车里坐那算账，记事，等等，请你改掉这个习惯。这是罪犯最完美的时刻跳进附驾驶的位子或者后座，拿枪对着你的脑袋让你开车去他方便犯罪的地方。所以请你上车以后就锁上车门离开。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　8. 如果有人已经跳进你的车子拿枪对着你，不要开车去他叫你去的地方。千万不要。你应该发动你的车子，然后以最快的速度开向离你最近的任何墙，树，等等。你的气囊袋会救你。如果罪犯是在后座，那他会伤的很惨。如果可以，车撞了以后离开你的车子然后呼救。如果不能离开，相信你也已经引来了足够的视线。记住，你宁可撞死，也不要多天以后，赤身裸体的被发现在某处荒无人烟的地方的草堆里。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 9. 几条关于停车场的忠告：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　a. 记住上车前观察你的车子周围，附驾驶座以及后座。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　b. 如果你的车子是停在一个大的面包车边上，而且面包车是停在驾驶座这边的，那么请你从附驾驶这一边上车。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　c. 小心停在你车两边的车。如果有男性一人坐在靠你车的这一面。请你务必小心。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　10.记住坐电梯。特别是晚上。楼梯道在早上和晚上都不是什么有趣的地方。(这里给一个和这个没什么关系的小tip: 如果坐电梯的时候电梯突然下坠，立刻把你这层下面的所有楼层全部按一遍。一般情况下如果突然下坠是电路问题，那么如果到哪层电路工作正常了，电梯会停下。如果电梯持续下坠，请背靠电梯墙壁站好(作为脊椎支撑)，手扶紧扶手，半弯你的膝盖(电梯突然着地可以稍微缓冲你的惯性，让你不要直直的从电梯地上穿下去）我开玩笑，但是可以缓冲你的惯性是真的。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 11.如果有人拿枪指着你，拔腿就跑。奔跑中的点被击中的可能性是4%。就算击中，一般也不会是重要内脏。如果可以，以梯子形左右跑。除非他追你，那你就什么也别管了，撒开腿往人多的地方跑吧。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　12.不要什么人都可怜。时刻保持警惕。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　13. 门口听见婴儿哭声，不要开门，直接报警。大多是录音带和一个强奸犯。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 14. 买完东西以后，数清楚你的钱。有这样的案子。女人在加油站加油以后付过钱回到车上。这时有个男人走过来敲打她的玻璃窗，手里一张5元钱，说她掉的。这个女人就感谢他，开窗/开门，然后发生的事情就我们无法想象的了！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　现在的这个社会，危险真的很多，可以说是无处不在了。亲爱的朋友们，为了自己和关心的人的个人安全，动动手指把本页网址分享给你的亲朋好友吧！相信会使你受益的！</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('26','19','','1','0','0','0','','','','<div>前言&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>药功之术在当今气功流传甚广，此种无符无咒无决只有单一配方的&ldquo;药法门&rdquo;崐称为&ldquo;药功小术&rdquo;。如本部传授的《中华药功秘笈》，《绝世药经秘宝》为最全面崐最系统，而真正的上乘药功是需要结合设坛，配药、秘制、念咒，书符和特定的使崐用密法才能成功。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>但此类古代药功正法是濒临失传，我部有幸获得《太乙奇门药功崐正法秘笈》，并承蒙高师指点迷津开启真决，才得以将此绝密奥旨机理通谷化地奉崐献功友。通过精研检验，发现其效果宏大，非一般药功小术可比。&ldquo;绝世奇门药功崐正法&rdquo;全部皆为流世救人，度人度已难求珍宝，&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>修习者不可存一丝一毫的邪毒恶贪崐，不法之徒若想借此行凶作恶，亦属杠然，徒费心机。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>此次将&ldquo;药功正法&rdquo;之玄机奥旨予以泄露，志在使诚心修行的有德之士得以解崐难救苦，治恶扬善，造福苍生。因考虑到请多因素，故只以手术整理影印；希望有崐缘得此奇法者慎重守之，不可轻泄，更不可对外翻传。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>第一章 益智术&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>一、聪明汤&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取白茯神１０克，远志１０克，石菖蒲１０克。水煎２次，合并煎液。崐&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童智力发育差，易忘事。吐痰多，舌苔白厚等。每日一剂，煎液分２崐次服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二、读书丸&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取石草菖蒲３０克，菟丝子３０克，远志３０克，地骨皮６０克，五味崐子３０克，生地黄３０克，川芎３０克。共研细未，调水糊丸如梧桐子大。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童学习用脑过度出现记忆力减退，头痛、睡眠不安等，每日报５０－崐８０克，临睡前温开水送服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>三、益智强记方&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取官桂３克，远志４克，人参１克，马戟天１２克，草蒲４克，地骨皮崐４克，茯苓６克，水煎２次，合半煎液。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童学习用脑过度出现记忆力下降，面色发白，精神萎靡，四肢不温。崐每日一剂，煎液分３次服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取熟地黄１０克，麦冬１０克，枣仁５克，远志４克。水煎２次，合并崐煎液。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童后或用脑过度出现记忆力减退，头晕心慌，口干等，每日１次，煎崐液分２次服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五、芡实粥&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取芡实３０克煮熟去壳，加入粳米２０克，文火熬至烂熟。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童病后或学习用脑过度出现注意力不集中，疲倦无力等，每日晨食。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六、准山芡实粥&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取淮山药３０克，芡实３０克，粳米２０克，同煮为粥，根据口味加盐崐或糖调味。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童体质虚弱，注意力不集中，易疲倦等。每日晨食。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七、龙眼肉粥&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取龙眼肉（桂园肉）１０克，粳米２０克，同煮为粥。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：用于小儿记忆力差或消瘦、盆血等。每日一次，温食。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八、核桃仁粥&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取核桃肉３０克，捣碎，加粳米３０克，同煮为粥。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童学习用脑过度记忆力减退。每日１次，温食。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九、龙骨远志末&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：白龙骨，远志各等分，共研细未。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童记忆力差，每顿饭后温开水送服２－３克。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十、莲肉远志粥&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：先将远志泡去心皮，捣为细末，加粳米，莲肉（捣碎）适量，同煮为粥崐。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童健忘，厌食。每日一餐。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十一、桂园参蜜膏</div>\r\n<div>制作：取党参２５克，沙参１２５克，桂园肉１２０克，先以适量水浸泡发透崐发，加热煎煮，２０分钟后滤出煎液，加水再煎，连续三次，合并煎液，小火浓缩崐至稠粘如膏，加入等量蜂蜜，至沸后停火，放冷装瓶备用。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童学习用脑过度出现神情恍惚，注意力不集中容易疲劳等。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十二、神仙富贵饼&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取白述２５克，菖莆２５０克，用火泔水浸泡，刮去黑皮，如石灰一小崐块同煮除去苦水，熟后晒干，加山药１０００克，共研细末，和面粉适量，作饼蒸崐食，或作馒头，面条等，可加入白糖调味。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童体胖痰多，注意力分散等，每日作辅食用１－２次。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十三：远志散&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取远志１５克，人参３克，石菖蒲１２克，白茯苓１２克，决明子１２崐克，山药１２克，桂心９克，熟地黄１２克，共研末。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童病后或学习用脑过度出现神思恍惚，注意力不集中，健忘等。每次崐１克，米汤或温开水送下。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十四、定志丸&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取炙黄芪、党参、桂枝、生龙骨、生牡蛎，茯苓、白术、炒扁豆、炒米、崐龙眼肉各适量，共研细末，炼蜜为丸，每丸３克。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童多动症，症见多动不安，注意不集中，面色萎靡，容易疲劳，每次崐１－２丸，１日２次。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十五、清脑益智合剂&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取鹿角粉１０克（冲），熟地黄１０克，生龙骨３０克，炙龟肱１２克，崐石菖蒲９克，远志３克，枸杞子９克，益智仁６克，丹参１５克，砂仁4.5克（捣崐拌） 。除鹿角粉外，余皆取饮片，用清水５００毫升，先煎生龙骨，炙龟版２０崐分钟，再入其他药同煎，过滤约得１５０毫升。再加水４００毫升，煎取汁约１０崐０毫升。将二次药液混合调匀，装瓶冷藏保存。</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童轻度脑功能障碍，症风症力较同龄者差，瓜应较迟钝等。每次２０崐毫升。１日２－３次。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十六益智丸&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制作：取益智仁９克，何首乌３０克，合欢花９克，石菖蒲９克，女贞子９克，崐炒杜仲９克，牛膝９克，莲子心９克，竹叶９克，楮实子９克，旱莲草９克，瓦松崐９克，黄精９克，神内９克，共研细末，炼蜜为丸，每丸约重1.6克。</div>\r\n<div>应用：儿童各种脑病引起的注意力，记忆力障碍神情呆滞，瓜应迟钝等。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>第二章 医治术&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>一、偏瘫绝方&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>病症：中风急症出现半身不遂，肢体麻木，言语蹇塞，喉中痰呜，唇舌紫暗，崐苔滑腻，脉弦。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：当时９克，川芎６克，红花６克，桃仁９克，竹沥９克，半夏９克，胆崐星９克，稀莶草３０克，伸筋草１０克。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>神疲倦怠，加黄芪１５克；舌红苔剥，加生地１２克，麦冬１２克，面白唇淡，崐脉弦细，加制首乌１５克，丹参１５克，面红烦躁加之脉弦有力，加石决明３０克，崐羚羊角３克（另煎兑服）；血脂高，加泽泻１２克，苡仁１５克；血压高，加地龙崐１２克，夏枯草１２克；上肢偏重，加桑枝１克，桂枝９克，片姜黄１２克；下肢崐偏重，加牛膝１５克，木瓜１２克，语言蹇涩，加石菖蒲１２克，远志９克；便秘，崐加火麻仁１２克，大黄９克；便溏，加扁豆１５克，苡仁１５克，苍术６克，白术崐９克；全身浮肿，加车前子１２克；全身麻木，加僵蚕６克，指迷茯苓丸６克；面崐部麻木，加白附子６克；口眼歪斜，加全蝎３克，蜈蚣３克；头晕，加珍珠母３０崐克，天麻１０克，钩藤１２克；全身疼痛，加鸡血藤１５克，秦艽１２克。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>服法：每日一剂，水煎２次，分服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二、灵犀丹&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>病症：中风急症出现昏不知人，半身不遂，肢休麻木，言塞等。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：水牛角屠９０克，天麻３０克，防风３０克，川活３０克，木香３０克，崐白芷３０克，甘菊花３０克，白僵蚕（炒）３０克，天南星（牛胆制）３０克，甘崐草３０克，地骨皮３０克，山药３０克，薄菏叶３０克，川芎３０克，蔓荆子３０崐克，麻黄（去根节）３０克，当归３０克，肉桂（去粗皮）３０克，干蝎蛸１５克，崐麝香（别研）６克，白花蛇（酒浸去皮骨，焙干）６０克。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>上药为细末，炼蜜为丸，每３０克作８丸，朱砂７５克为衣。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>服法：每次服１丸，不拘时候，细嚼人参汤化下或茶酒送服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>三、癫闲丸&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>病症：癫痛出现突然昏倒，不少人事，牙关紧闭，两目上视，手足抽搐，口吐崐涎沫，移时苏醒，舌质淡红，脉实有力。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>取巴豆去外壳，巴豆仁挤压去油，得油尽取渣制成巴豆霜，再加入余药，共为崐细末，练蜜为丸如小豆粒大小，备用。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>服法：成人每次３粒，１日３次，饭后服，如服药过程中无不良反应，可逐渐崐加量，但每次不超过５粒，儿童酌减，孕妇忌服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>四、十枣汤&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>病症：精神分裂症出现神志呆滞，表情淡漠，沉默少语腹胀便结，体质壮实，崐舌苔白滑，脉沉弦有力。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：甘遂0.5克，大戟0.5克，芜花0.5克，大枣３０克。</div>\r\n<div>前三味研末，用大枣汤送服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>服法：每日１剂，顿服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五、消遗汤&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>病症：脑震荡，脑挫裂伤，脑干损伤等脑外伤后遗症出现头晕头痛，目眩耳鸣，崐神倦懒言，四肢乏力，恶心呕吐，夜寐不安，记忆减退。苔白，脉细无力。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：琥珀３克，辰砂３克，青龙齿１５克，木通３－６克，大腹皮１２克，崐桑白皮１２克，赤芍９克，桃仁１２克，党参２０克，枸杞子１５克，荆芥穗６克，崐柴胡６克，白芍１５克，制香附６克。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>服法：每日１剂，水煎２次，分服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六、冠心病验方&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>病症：缸血性心脏病用一般药物少效者。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：珍珠粉0.3克，参三七1.5克，川贝粉３克。</div>\r\n<div>服法：每日一剂，分２次，温开水送服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七、降压神枕&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>症症：原发性高血压出现头痛头晕，面红目亦，口干中苦。舌红苔黄，脉弦数。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：野菊花、淡竹叶、冬桑叶、生石膏、白芍、川芎、磁石、蔓荆子、青木崐香、蚕沙各适量。制成药枕。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>使用：代替日常睡枕使用，要求每昼液使用时间不少于６小时，平时应保持枕崐面清洁，经常翻晒，以利药枕气味散发，用药枕期间停用，一切降压药及其它疗法。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八、牙痛妙方&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：细辛３克，骨碎补９克，荆芥4.5克，薄荷4.5克，连翘９克，赤芍６克，崐牛蒡子６克，开麻4.5万，甘草3克，水煎２０分钟服用，齿痛可减一半。</div>\r\n<div>&lt;, SPAN lang=ZH-TW style=&quot;COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: 宋体; POSITION: relative; TOP: -1pt; mso-hansi-font-family: \\\\''Times New Roman\\\\''; mso-text-raise: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: ZH-CN&quot;&gt;服法：通常是每天１剂，煎服２次，２天即愈。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九、治阳痿验方&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：泥鳅2.5克，韭菜籽５０克。将泥鳅去内脏洗净，韭菜籽淘洗后用纱布崐包起来，同放锅中加水0.5公斤，盐少许共煮，水开后改文火煎者，至水剩250克时崐取出韭菜籽，吃泥鳅喝汤。</div>\r\n<div>服法：每日１次，１０天为一疗程（忌房事）１－２疗程见效。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十、肝炎奇疗&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：瓜蒂，秦芄各１０克，青熏、紫草、黄苓、丹参各３０克，铜绿１５克，崐冰片６克共研末。一次取1.５克。</div>\r\n<div>使用：将药散置脐孔，用胶布封严，每天换一次。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十一、夺命丹&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>病症：此方治疗跌打损伤，血淤阻滞，伤处肿胀坚硬，疼痛不止等症。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：全当归、炙草鸟、自然铜（酒淬）乳香、没药各５０克，血渴９克，以崐上药物研末混匀。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>使用：每次１－２克，黄酒送服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十二、治支气管炎特效方&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：白茯苓、川贝、杏仁、桑皮、甘草、五味子，京半夏、当归、陈皮各６崐克，用药３天后除根。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>使用：第１剂药，每１天下午５点熬，晚上９点服，第２剂药，第２天９点熬，崐第３天早上７点服；第３剂药，每４天早上６点熬，中午１１点服。最后，３剂药崐渣合在一起，第５天下午５点熬，晚上９点服下。每剂只熬１次，合冰糖１次服下。崐无论病情轻重，３剂药服完后除根。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>服药期间，不准吃烟、酒、茶、盐、葱、姜、蒜、辣椒等辛椒食物。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十三、引神丹&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>可达到使内气即快又强地集中贯注之效。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：麝香９克，硫磺３克，吴茱萸９克，阳起石９克，干姜６克。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>使用：上药共研成末，于练功时，取药末和蜜敷贴在欲需领气贯注之部位上。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十四、内壮丸&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>功效：强壮筋骨，增力补气经络，调和气摁练功加速进展。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：当时１５０克，川牛膝１５０克，鱼鳔胶１５０克，豹骨４５０克（酥崐炙），枸杞子１５０克，川续断１５０克，补骨脂１５０克（盐水炒）菟丝子１５崐０克，沙苑疾藜４０克，蟹黄２６０克（炒）远志４８克，牡蛎５０克，人参１５崐克，黄芪２０克。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>使用：以上诸药共研成细末，以蜜炼丸，每服９克（每丸可３克或９克为好），崐以练习前用黄酒服下，再喝开水半碗即可行功。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>第三章 炼丹术&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>医用丹药，在中医学中占有极端重要的地位，临床实践证实，有不少久不愈合崐的慢性顽固大症，而由丹药发挥其独有疗铲，得以解决的不少，只是在漫长的历史崐中，丹药被误解用未得到合理的应用和发展，同时，也由于丹药技术掌握者秘而不崐宜，致使这一技法长期处于停滞状态，给祖国医学带来了不可估量的损失。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>为了弘扬传统文化，挖掘整理提高传统中医药，让古老的&ldquo;丹药&rdquo;重新焕发青崐春，得以广泛的应用和发展，造福人类，特撰此章，以证吾辈爱情瑰宝之心，发扬崐光大之志，昭示天下。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>一、九龙丹&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：水银４５克，火硝１２０克，白矾６０克，明雄６克，朱砂６克，铜绿崐６克，明矾６克，扫粉６克，滑石１５克，皂矾６克。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>练法：配料按处方量准确称取药料，除水银外其他均需粉碎成粗粉，然后进行崐坐胎。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>生胎：可分为冷胎和热胎法，操作时采用其中一种即可。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>（一）冷胎法，先将处方中粗粉置于乳 内，加入水银共研至混合均匀，不见崐水银银珠为止，铺于锅底，用瓷碗覆盖，碗口与锅要吻合严密。或将处方中药料粗崐粉混匀，放锅中央铺开，再把水银酒在药料上面，覆碗。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>（二）热胎法：将药料粗粉置于孔置于孔休内研细，移入锅中中微火加热于有崐水分逸出，使其表面呈现蜂窝状时，将锅取下，待冷，再将水银酒表面（或用竹穿崐十余小孔，将水银倒入孔中，然后再瓷碗覆盖。）&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>封口：盖碗后要及时封口，约取4cm宽的皮纸用盐水湿润后，将锅与碗接触处崐的缝隙封２－３层，以严密为准，再将盐泥涂于纸上纺6cm厚按平筑紧涂严无隙，崐再用沙壅至碗2/3部位，使与碗口剂平。碗底中放大米数粒，以观察火候，碗底可崐压重物，以避免练烧时受气体作用而浮动。</div>\r\n<div>烧练：装置完毕，移置火焰上加热。先用文火烧炼约１h，再逐渐加大火力，崐以武火烧炼至大米呈老黄色，再以文火继续烧炼至火至黑色，共烧炼约５－１０h崐即可停火放冷。</div>\r\n<div>收丹：将丹锅放冷后，轻轻扫去河沙，再用小刀铲去泥块与纸，将碗轻轻取出，崐观察其色刮下碗内附着的丹药。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>去火毒法：&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>１、将丹药用细布包扎好，投入沸水中煮４h，取出沥干水分，低温干燥，研崐细备用。</div>\r\n<div>２、将丹剂用油纸或细布包好，置潮湿地上（或地上洒水）露放三昼夜，再用崐低温干燥，研细备用。在水中能微溶的丹剂，宜用露法。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>适应病症：一切疮疡均可应用，功能化腐，云绵，退管，出骨，托毒等极有效崐验。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二、伏虎丹&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：鸡极黄边１０克，吴萸子３克，血琥珀粉１８克，朱砂３克，肉桂1.5崐克，紫石英３０克。</div>\r\n<div>制法：先将吴萸子用淡盐汤浸泡２小时，滤出后加黄连再入百草露水浸透，水崐淹过药约一平指高。然后文火慢煮１－２小时，水干后不断拌炒，柳枝为等，炒尽崐水气，以沙沙作响不生烟，香脆为焦为度，候冷，研细末备用。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>后四味药，水鼎熬５－６小时，去渣留汁入蜂蜜１８０克，再熬至果子泡（起崐很多大泡）为度，以蜜和制黄连，吴萸子之散与琥珀粉，朱砂，肉桂之药渣（紫石崐英取出不用）为丸，梧子大。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>主治：左肋胀痛，肺燥心热之失眼（相火刑金不寐症），眩晕、谵语、 气吞崐酸等症。又主治练功出现偏差之白虎为痛，发生的手脚不动，身体摇摆的症候。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>用法：每服1.5-6克，日服一次。</div>\r\n<div>三、玉壶丹&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：硫黄0.5公斤（倭硫最佳）天生磺２４０克，桑紫灰汁一 孟，韭菜籽崐２００克，白罗卜若干。</div>\r\n<div>制法：将桑柴灰用水淋汁，取澄清后之精汁５大碗（约 孟），入研极细末之崐硫，砂锅文火开盖煮２小时。如无桑柴灰可以韭菜籽代（绢袋），入砂锅文火开盖崐煮２小时，用以伏硫，然后换清水再煮１－２小时（韭菜籽置入），再滤出水，药崐液冷后，装入切盖掏空一半的白罗卜内，仍以萝卜封口，竹签签好，入水鼎煮，以崐萝卜熟透为度，再依法换萝卜煮之，凡九转或十三转，如将萝卜入柴灰火中烘烤，崐萝卜熟透(或置柴灰为中一夜)，如此九转或十三转，更佳。从萝卜内取出药物，另崐以地浆水澄鼗精汁（掘地三尺，取泥捣浆澄清，取其水份谓地浆水），调和上药入崐陶质鼎文炼化如糊，令起蟹眼沸（小泡）为度（所炼之药如起焰火洒醋伏之）。同崐时别用铁锅炒沙沙半锅，热后锅下即用微火养之，再干沙上铺桑皮纸一张，候上述崐之药硫烊化加糊时，以竹勺不木勺从陶质鼎中取出一滴一滴地滴药汁于纸上，药即崐在桑皮上变色，以变白色如玉为度，候冷，阻干，再研极细末，水飞更佳。练蜜为崐丸，梧子大，朱砂衣。</div>\r\n<div>主治：能兴垂绝之阳（回阳救逆），回阳暖肾，止痛祛 ，治腰痛（肾阳虚）崐有神功。无病者久服驻颜美容，返老还童。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>用法，每日空心服７－９丸（日服一次），如长期服食，每日３－５丸。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>禁忌：不可过量服用，阳盛者不能服用。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>第四章：房中秘术&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>一、青蚕壮阳方&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>大晴蜒（青大者良，红者次之，余者更次，去翅足，微火米炒）２０对。原蚕崐蛾（去翅足，微火米炒）１５对，大蜈蚣（不去头足，酒润后，微火焙干）５条，崐露蜂房（剪碎，洒润，略炒至微黄），生枣仁、酒当归、炙首乌各２０克，丁香、崐木香、桂心各１０克，胡椒５克，共为细末，炼蜜为丸，如梧桐子小，每服１５丸，崐或为散，每服１０克，每日２－３次，空腹以少许黄酒送服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>此方已应用多年，&ldquo;每遇阳萎重症，诸药无效者，必用之，无不应手取效。&rdquo;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>二、回春丸&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>破故纸６０克，山萸肉６０克，枸杞子６０克（泡煨），生意２５０克，大枣崐１００个。将前三味研为细末，把妆捣烂同枣置锅内加水同煮，煮后去枣核，和药崐面共为丸，如绿豆大小，每日９克，早晚各服一次，桂圆肉煎汤后送服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>三、神蜒壮阳露&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>蜻蜒２只，锁阳、肉苡蓉各１５克，将晴蜒去翅足，微火大火少，加入镜阳，崐肉苡蓉煎汤，每日１次。取１０天为一疗程。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>四、雄宝丸&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>鹿角胶３克，鹿角霜６克，菟丝子１０克，柏子仁１５克，熟地２４克，黄精崐１０克，芡实１２克，山药１５克，山萸肉１５克。共研细末，炼蜜为丸，每丸９崐克，一日一丸，早晚分服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>五、亢萎灵&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>蜈蚣１８克，当时６０克，白勺６０克，甘草６０克，先将蜈蚣研细为末，再崐将后三味药晒干研细过筛混匀，分为４０包（也可制成小丸）每次服半包或１包，崐早晚各１次，空腥用白洒或黄洒送服，１５天为１个疗程。方中蜈蚣不去头足，以崐免减效。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>六、蛇阳通宝&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>蛇床子浓煎汤，浸洗男性生殖器，一日２－３次，每次２０分钟&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七、参蛤宝&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>干胎盘７０克，蛤蚧２０克，五味子６０克，高丽参２０克，上药共研细末，崐炼蜜为丸，每丸６克，每日两次，每次一日，温开水送服。适用于阳萎伴头晕，失崐眼，健忘，多梦，乏力。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八、不倒丸&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>制黑附子６克，蛇床子１５克，淫羊藿１５克，益智仁１０克，甘草６克，上崐药共研为细末，炼蜜为丸。一日两次分服。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>七、降压神枕&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>症症：原发性高血压出现头痛头晕，面红目亦，口干中苦。舌红苔黄，脉弦数。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：野菊花、淡竹叶、冬桑叶、生石膏、白芍、川芎、磁石、蔓荆子、青木崐香、蚕沙各适量。制成药枕。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>使用：代替日常睡枕使用，要求每昼液使用时间不少于６小时，平时应保持枕崐面清洁，经常翻晒，以利药枕气味散发，用药枕期间停用，一切降压药及其它疗法。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>八、牙痛妙方&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：细辛３克，骨碎补９克，荆芥4.5克，薄荷4.5克，连翘９克，赤芍６克，崐牛蒡子６克，开麻4.5万，甘草3克，水煎２０分钟服用，齿痛可减一半。</div>\r\n<div>服法：通常是每天１剂，煎服２次，２天即愈。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>九、治阳痿验方&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>处方：泥鳅2.5克，韭菜籽５０克。将泥鳅去内脏洗净，韭菜籽淘洗后用纱布崐包起来，同放锅中加水0.5公斤，盐少许共煮，水开后改文火煎者，至水剩250克时崐取出韭菜籽，吃泥鳅喝汤。</div>\r\n<div>服法：每日１次，１０天为一疗程（忌房事）１－２疗程见效。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>十四 窄阴方&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>女子阴道松宽，会使男女交合失去许多乐趣，在《洞幺子》中，记载了一种可以使阴道变得窄逼的药方：石硫磺2克，青木香2克，山菜黄2克，蛇床子2克。用这会味药捣碎成粉末，临交接时，将此药粉涂抹在阴道口处便可，此药不可以涂抹过多，否则会适得其反，使女阴无口。</div>\r\n<div>十五 长玉茎方&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>柏子5分，白蔹四分，白术七分，桂心三分，附子二分。上五物为散，食用服方七七，日再，十日、二十日长大</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('27','19','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>&nbsp;水火烫伤一妙方，有缘者当珍惜</p>\r\n<div>水火烫伤是比较常见的意外外伤。今供养大家一妙方有缘者当珍惜！&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;先说一下此方的来源。我老家有一高人，当地所谓&ldquo;打师&rdquo;，即有武功、医术的人。大概年轻时暴戾自负，与人挑斗，终被人挑瞎双目。故后来一般人谓&ldquo;陈瞎子&rdquo;，真名&ldquo;陈秀鹿&rdquo;还是&ldquo;陈秀六&rdquo;不清楚。后善根发露，性情大变，收徒授艺，众所钦敬。他去世时有一挽联云&ldquo;妙手医秀江，桃李满天下&rdquo;。一次，大姐陈虹岚所在的百货商场一职工被烫伤，众人慌乱之际，&ldquo;陈瞎子&rdquo;从容告知：&ldquo;赶快啊。弄些（&hellip;&hellip;下面是方法，买个关子，下面再说）。&rdquo;大姐有心之人，记住了此法。他的徒弟当中，反而无人知道。后来试之，无不效验如神！但，越简单的方，常人越不相信，医院也更不相信民间的&ldquo;野路子&rdquo;。80年代江西花炮事故爆炸，烧伤多人，医院不胜接待。换纱布时，皮肉撕裂，痛苦万状。姐恻隐之心，要告诉医院此法，医院哪里会听！后来我姐的火疮药在当地真是很有点名气！因此姐姐每年还会记得给&ldquo;陈瞎子&rdquo;烧些纸感恩。现在，她学了佛，号&ldquo;果德居士&rdquo;。发愿把此方供养给大家。希有缘者珍惜，勿因简单而忽视！&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;妙方：澄清的石灰水2份、山茶油1分，搅拌成白色油滑膏脂状。妙方即成！&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;用法（以下是姐姐在实践中总结出来的）：1，烧伤后即用此药最好，若先已用它药，应用盐水洗掉再搽此药。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;2，前5天不用包扎，时时用干净鸡毛沾药涂患处。5天后，烧灼感消除，可包扎。换药时用盐水洗掉旧药。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;3，重度烧伤可配合内服消炎药。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;4，忌煎炒酸辣、荤腥。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;注：山茶油很多地方没有，可用菜油等植物油代替。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;效果：&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;上药之后，烧灼感立马减轻。一楼说的病人中，有一在医院死了。另有一个不是这次事故中的伤者，烧伤程度差不多，采取此方迅速痊愈，不留疤痕。医院常规治疗，所费百千巨万，痛苦异常。此方所费无几而疗效神验。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;注意，轻、中度患者，单用此法既可。重度烧伤需配合医院的针剂、内服等。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;烧烫伤的处理有&ldquo;五字诀&rdquo;，也就是五个步骤：冲、脱、泡、盖、送。在家里用冷水冲及泡水各十五分钟表皮的温度，防止温度再向皮下组织漫延。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;1元钱速效治疗感冒奇方！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;是药也不是药，都在调味品店买便宜、质量好。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　桂皮1g，白芷12g，姜24g，饭后三味合熬汤，饮后蒙头发汗（或走膀胱尿多），半小时左右即好，百千人用过，特效！</div>\r\n<div>　　注意：切莫见风。</div>\r\n<div>风寒还行，风热就要出问题了。还有有些人是气虚，营卫不足尽量不要用。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;公开【祖传治癌秘方】治癌千余例，有效率100%</div>\r\n<div>癌症肆虐全世界，每秒死亡好几人，发病率和死亡率越来越高，但医学界束手无策！&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>为救拔病苦众生，为光耀如来家业，李清岩居士无私贡献祖传秘方，治疗各种癌症/肿瘤千余例，有效率100%</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;李家祖传治癌秘方&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;主治：各种癌/瘤</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;配方：生五灵脂１０克，生黑牵牛２０克，生香附子１０克，生广木香１０克．&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;用法：买药时加工成粉，加白醋调糊为丸，阴干．一次１０克．生姜汁送服，每天３－４次（小儿药量减半）．也可以不调糊，服药时加些醋．&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;注意：不得吃人参。孕妇不可用。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;说明：一般病例３０分钟见效，经千余例临验，疗效100%，被称为神方！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;本方前三味药是祖传秘方，第四味药是贡献人研究所加．&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;献方人：广东饶平县三饶镇西巷头民间医师 　李清岩&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;速治青春痘民间中医绝招</div>\r\n<div>青春豆为不少青春期的爱美的朋友们不少的烦恼，采用放血疗法固然有效，若不愿放血的我有一个非常简单的绝招献出，此方系一位民间老中医密传我的，试用过多人，确有奇效，一般今日服次日即见效，多两至三日也见效，先是痘疮变蔫、变小，然后消失，多服一段时间甚至连皮肤残留的暗疮痕迹也消失了，皮肤变白细嫩，不信吧？</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp;川贝母粉3～6克 &nbsp; 纯真蜂蜜一匙勺</div>\r\n<div>服法：上二味共调水服，一日两次。</div>\r\n<div>功效： 快速见效去痘，美白皮肤。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;治胃癌秘方</div>\r\n<div>处方:台党10克，云苓10克，甘草6克，砂仁5克，炮姜5克，鸡宝10克，白芨10克，霍香6克，干白6克，酒白芍10克，黄奉天10克，生苡仁30克，白花蛇舌草30克，孩儿喜食草30克。红糖30克为引子。</div>\r\n<div>用法：清水煎，一日分二次，每隔六小时一次，饭前温服。一日一剂，一般三剂见效，十剂一般可愈。</div>\r\n<div>疗效：经极重的胃癌都516位患者临床验证，能治愈。</div>\r\n<div>注：凡有缘得此秘方治愈后，要积德行善，多做好事，更不能用此方去非法敛财，切记，切记!</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>千人验证一次即效，永不牙痛奇方！！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>此方我师传来，师父说他治过一千多人，均一次见效！我也给十多个人用过均神效，无毒副作用，有感兴趣的朋友不妨一试：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;樟脑6克 龙骨3克 透骨草3克 甘草3克</div>\r\n<div>上药研细浸入高度白酒中(酒浸没药即可),然点燃酒,如酒度数低点不燃可先加热白酒后再点燃,待火自行灭燃后,酒稍冷却即口含药酒汁30分钟左右(浸泡痛牙)吐掉,最好晚饭后应用(药后不可吃东西,否则易损牙床,一次愈)</div>\r\n<div>------药汁不可吞下,含浸后吐掉！！！</div>\r\n<div>对牙龈炎、牙周炎、风火牙疼、虫牙、烂牙、智齿牙痛均有效，一次肿痛轻，最多二次愈！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;补充要点：含酒时务必令药液完.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;胃病特效药方</div>\r\n<div>三七粉3克，猪瘦肉2两。置一小碗中，加一点水，蒸熟后吃肉喝汤。隔天一次，轻者3-5次，重者10余次痊愈。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>治疗一切胃酸过多，胃下垂，胃神经痛，胃分泌少，消化不良，闷涨不适，胃疼痛不止，一切胃肠病有特效。（请勿收藏自秘，广传济世功德无量）</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>B型肝炎（乙型肝炎）绝症有一个奇方</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>B型肝炎是十大疑难杂症之一，医学界至今未找到一个彻底治疗的良方，一个奇特的因缘使这个良方被发现和传播，而且效果显著，以下为此方发现过程：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;大概在1990年，纽约的刘先生（是一个虔诚的佛教徒），不幸被诊断为B型肝炎，他浑身无力，无法工作，当时医生说此病无法治疗痊愈，只有慢慢静养。当时，刘先生很失望，（他一直都有抽烟喝酒）。其父得知其事后，怜惜其子，便召其回马来西亚静养，而后，其父的一个农夫朋友，得知此事，便慨然说：&ldquo;没事！我治过好多了！&rdquo;所以他便又去农田挖一些茄子（广东人叫矮瓜）的根，洗净切碎煎了给他做药吃！煎法如下：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;大概200-300（最多500）克茄子根，水适量，煎二次，分二日饮用，每日饮一次，然后休息二日，再煎一剂，如法饮用。如此二十剂后化验（约八十天后），病情便可全部转变，为保险起见，以后再零行饮用十剂左右！但千万注意，不能采用那些根部被杀虫剂污染过的，否则，治病不成，反为杀生！千万注意！千万注意！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;刘先生在马来西亚饮用二十剂以后验血，结果：B型肝炎已好，但抵抗力还差些！此后，他又返美，约每一二个月饮用一次，一年后，又到先前的诊所验血，医生大吃一惊！叹为一生未见之奇迹！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;刘先生已经介绍此方给别人治愈了四位朋友！其父在马来西亚也介绍治愈多人，刘先生至今烟酒未断，而B型肝炎则烟消云散！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;刘先生为利益别人曾登刊物介绍此方，真是功德无量！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;在一个因缘下，我认识了刘先生，并了解了此事的过程，他要求我帮助他介绍此方给别人。通过5.6年的交往，我相信他的为人，信其为真，便拟文简述其经过，以冀利益有情，不负刘先生初衷，亦示我佛慈悲精神！亦望大众勉力推广，功德无量！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;是为推荐缘起！</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>暖身神方--再也不用怕冷了</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>一、前言；</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 有位姓刘的青年，虽是个女同志，但却特别爱钻研．有</div>\r\n<div>一天，她从家里的一大堆老古董书籍中随手翻出一本书，是</div>\r\n<div>一本《砂盘点精》，她也不懂，随便看了看就放下了．但在</div>\r\n<div>放下的刹那，她觉得其中好象有几个字特别有吸引力．就重</div>\r\n<div>新翻开刚才看过的地方。原来是一篇关于冬天少穿衣服而不</div>\r\n<div>冷的方法介绍《暖身神方》．一般人看了不会当真，更不会</div>\r\n<div>将这本出版于民国的石刻印版书当真。但她不同，她当即抄</div>\r\n<div>下配方，找来材料(其实家家都有)，按说明制好后，用胶</div>\r\n<div>布贴在神阙穴(肚脐)上，居然真的特别管用，就是寒冷的</div>\r\n<div>冬天，穿很少的衣服(不是穿单衣)，神阙穴也有一股暖流</div>\r\n<div>冲向全身，让人红光满面，精神倍增。由于她家这一带冬天</div>\r\n<div>没有生暖气的习惯，她制作的这种粉以及用这种粉制作的药</div>\r\n<div>胶布根是好销．一年下来，收入居然是平时上班的好几倍。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 二、功能与原理：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 暖身神方能刺激神阙穴，调动人体功能，舒筋活血，让</div>\r\n<div>血液流速加快，增加人体热量，从而达到暖身的目的．</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 三、适用范围；</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 17岁以上的男女均可，对年老者效果稍差。(但绝不是</div>\r\n<div>指能在冬季穿单衣，也就是说，贴上后所穿衣服只比平时少</div>\r\n<div>一些．)</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 四、原料及配方：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 花椒、胡椒、医用橡皮胶布。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 配方：花椒1克，胡椒4克，医用橡皮胶布5X3厘米．</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 五、制作：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 将花椒、胡椒研成细粉，密封不漏气，备用。然后将医</div>\r\n<div>用橡皮胶布(如能用麝香虎骨膏更好)撕下纱布，将花椒、</div>\r\n<div>胡椒撒沾上去，即可使用。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 六、使用</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 将神阙穴(肚脐)周围洗干净，将胡椒粉，花椒粉撤在</div>\r\n<div>医用橡皮胶布上，一般贴一次在7天左右均有效。也可将胡</div>\r\n<div>椒粉、花椒粉直接撒在神阙穴(肚脐)内，再贴上医用胶布。</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; 七、注意事项：</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; (1)花椒、胡椒在当地农贸市场均有售，如没有可买花</div>\r\n<div>椒粉，胡椒粉代替，不过，效果稍差一点；</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; (2)根据每人的身体状况，饮食习惯等，在使用时，花</div>\r\n<div>椒粉，胡椒粉先取少量地撤在胶布上(注意，粉须集中放在</div>\r\n<div>神阙穴中)，待习惯后再适当增加用量，不可随意增加用量，</div>\r\n<div>以免难受。</div>\r\n<div>(3)本品对老年人效果稍差，建议您不要使用在儿童身</div>\r\n<div>(4)本品在冬季使用，效果较好，其它季节使用，效果</div>\r\n<div>较差．</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('28','19','','1','0','0','0','','','','<div>药功防身自卫术（1）</div>\r\n<div>　　一、配方：花椒15克，细辛5克，公丁15克，干姜20克，肉桂20克，附子20克</div>\r\n<div>　　二、配制方法：&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　1、把上述中药研碎，放进空的无水的热水瓶里；</div>\r\n<div>　　2、把95%的酒精二斤半倒进热水瓶内浸泡80天；</div>\r\n<div>　　3、完后，把热水瓶中的浸泡液用纱布过滤到葡萄糖瓶里，密封保存待用，15年不变质（热水瓶不能再食用）；</div>\r\n<div>　　4、使用方法：（一）把过滤后的浸泡液倒进医院用的皮冲里便可使用（医院商店有售，可买二个，一个大的，一个小的。（二）遇到歹徒时，用小的皮冲里面的浸泡液射向歹徒的面部，他就会失去任何反抗能力的力量，不能动弹，要过4至5个小时才能恢复行动。（三）遇到歹徒人多时，可把大、小两皮冲都用上，左右手各提一个，还要带上半瓶浸泡液以备使用；</div>\r\n<div>　　5、解救方法：①用冷水洗面部10分钟，再用牙膏擦面部15分钟，随后，用冷水再洗一次，就会慢慢地恢复正常。②一次口服生甘草片三片或生甘草30克煎服，（注此药对某些人不起作用）</div>\r\n<div>药功防身自卫术（2）</div>\r\n<div>　　（鲜）五步蛇头一个，（鲜）山峰七只，（鲜）雄鸡一个，（崭蛇）五爪虎（又称伏脚虎）15克，白醋30克，生天南星15克（中药店有售）</div>\r\n<div>　　制法：将上述药用酒精泡一斤浸15天，去药滓，另加五瓶风油精放入药汁内，即可使用。</div>\r\n<div>　　用法：用一种玩具枪（水枪）使用，也可用眼药水瓶或皮球使用。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　注意：千万不可乱传乱伤人，否则后果自负。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　解药：&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　草药：凤尾草30克</div>\r\n<div>　　芙蓉花叶：25克</div>\r\n<div>　　中药：防风15克</div>\r\n<div>　　雄黄：5克</div>\r\n<div>　　制法：将上述药物用2斤清水加火煮开，煎熬成1斤汁，用纱布过滤，另加甘油30克混合药水洗患处速解。</div>\r\n<div>药功防身自卫术（3）</div>\r\n<div>　　乙醚50克，95度酒精200克，红花油50克，川乌15克，天盘草15克，拉沙15克。把以上几种药物泡在一起，7天后就可使用。</div>\r\n<div>　　使用方法：用水冲气球放射，只要打到对方皮肤上5到8秒钟，就会全身麻醉，无力反抗。</div>\r\n<div>　　解药方法：樟脑15克，金银花15克，子叶15克，矮竹叶15克，深沙一起冲热开水口服下肚15分钟即可解掉。</div>\r\n<div>药功防身自卫术（4）</div>\r\n<div>　　用阿托品药粉30克（药也可用药片代），闹羊花粉（一味中草药粉）25克，溶于100毫升乙醚（一种化学药物，各地化学实验室皆有）中，装入可喷射容器中，遇歹徒时射其面部，即可迷倒，一小时苏醒。</div>\r\n<div>药功防身自卫术（5）</div>\r\n<div>　　第一种配方：&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　风油精2瓶，加清水1―2瓶，百空丹半瓶，，浓氨水半市斤，将以上各种药装进无色玻璃瓶内，半月内每天用手轻轻地摇一次，半月后发挥药效，5年内不失效。</div>\r\n<div>　　第二种配方：&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　乙醚2份，仙桃花草5份，蔓陀萝5份。</div>\r\n<div>　　将以上各药品碎成粉共装在无色玻璃瓶内，每天用手轻轻地摇一下，半月后即可发挥药效，5年内不失效。</div>\r\n<div>　　解药配方：樟脑1份研成粉，肥皂粉10份</div>\r\n<div>　　将上述药物研成粉，加入适量的酒精调成菜糊状备用，可装玻璃瓶内防风干变质。&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>　　使用方法：将以上配好的药物装进压力大的塑料喷具内，向歹徒的面部直接喷射，歹徒受药后会失去知觉，使用者自己面部没受药不会昏倒，歹徒受药后，需1小时苏醒过来。</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('29','21','','1','0','0','0','','','','<div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">习惯性错误发音：</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">target [\\\\''tɑ:ɡit] &nbsp;image [\\\\''ɪmɪdʒ] youtube [\\\\''ju:\\\\''tju:b]</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">practise----读作pratise &nbsp; /k/省略 &nbsp; 两个爆破音读一个即可</span></div>\r\n<div>address在美音中第一个是大嘴梅花音，节奏类似access的读音</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\"><br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">can和can\\\\''t &nbsp;通常以语调不同来区分他们</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">thirty 和 thirteen &nbsp;前者重音在第一个音节，后者在第二个音节 &nbsp; ty可读成dy</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">perfect 等词语 &nbsp;重音在前面的是名词或形容词，重音在后面的是动词</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">eyes 和 ice 前者/ai/后跟浊辅音，/ai/的发音长一点，后者跟清辅音，发音短一点 &nbsp; &nbsp;又如seat和seed等 都是这个规律</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">前辅后元要连读，加在两个元音之间的清辅音要浊化</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">he him her 等h发音开头词语的击穿</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">two apples中间连读成/ra/， three apples中间连读成/j/</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">big cake 连读时候第一个单词的末尾音省略</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">及物（transitive）和不及物（intransitive）区别在于及物动词后面要指定对象。 i like it 而不是 i like</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">content words 通常重音 &nbsp;包括名词、主要的动词、形容词、副词、this that these those、以及wh开头的单词如who what when how which等。</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">function words通常轻读 &nbsp;包括冠词a an the、 his my your、介词 in on of 等、连词 and but 等、i he she 、be动词am is are 等、do does did等。</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">具体上下文时会有特例 会根据需要重点表达的内容</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\"><br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">以下九个动词后跟to do或doing都可以,同时不改变意思：begin, start, continue, like, love, hate, prefer, can\\\\''t stand ,can\\\\''t bear</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">以下五个动词会改变意思：remember &nbsp;forget &nbsp; regret &nbsp; try &nbsp;stop</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\"><br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">失去爆破----http://blog.sina.com.cn/s/blog_634a7dfe0100g34u.html</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">什么是爆破音？</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">英语音标中共有20个元音，28个辅音。其中28个辅音中，[p] [b]、 [t] [d]、 [k] [g]这六个音标，两两一组，一共三组，发音是具有强烈的先蓄气之后快速摩擦嘴唇而出的所谓爆破感，于是被称为爆破音，是令英语读音铿锵有力的最佳元素</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">例词</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">Exactly &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 失去爆破部分ct</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">Absolutely &nbsp; &nbsp;失去爆破部分b</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">Technology &nbsp; &nbsp;失去爆破部分ch</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">Advance &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;失去爆破部分d</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">Advertise &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;失去爆破部分d</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">Absent &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;失去爆破部分b</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">例句</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">1}It&rsquo;s~a hot day.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">今天很热</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">2}Life~is~a high and low road.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">生活是条崎岖的路</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">3}I&rsquo;ll get there when~I get there.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">后会有期</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">4}It\\\\''s not that they like~it.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">（事情是）不是他们喜欢它</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">5}Don&rsquo;t do what should not be done.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">不要做不该做的事情</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">6}What I do know is that I will not let nobody get that.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">我知道的是我不会让任何人得到那个</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">7}I should let you know in advance.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">我应该事先让你知道</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">8}It&rsquo;s not what I do that counts.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">我所做的并不重要</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">9}It&rsquo;s the way I do it that matters a lot.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">我做事情的方式才重要</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">10}What do you need that for?</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">你要这个干嘛？</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\"><br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">击穿-------------------------</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">击穿的条件：</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">当前面单词结尾是辅音，后面单词开头是字母h所发的[h],之后是元音的时候，前面单词结尾的辅音可以穿透后面单词开头的[h]而直接跟后面的原因以连读的方式读在一起</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">例如：</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">Guess who?</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">Guess结尾是辅音[s]，who开头是[h]，[h]后面是元音 [u:]，于是当作[h]完全不存在，[s]与[u:]连读在一起构成[su:]，于是整句话的读音变成 [g?su:]</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">1}If you love him, send him to New York because it&rsquo;s heaven; if you hate him, send him to New York because it&rsquo;s hell.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">爱他就送他去纽约，因为那里是天堂，恨他就送他去纽约，因为那里是地狱</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">2}He&rsquo;s not what~I think he is, is he?</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">他并不是我所想象的那样</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">3}Tell him~about~it.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">告诉他这件事</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\"><br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">爆破音是指发音器官在口腔中形成阻碍,然后气流冲破阻碍而发出的音。这些音有6个,即/p/, /b/, /t/, /d/, /k/和/g/。但在某些情况下,发爆破音时,气流不必冲破阻碍,而只是发音器官在口腔中形成阻碍,并稍做停顿,(也就是说,做好要发出这个爆破音的准备,但不要发出音来),这样的发音过程叫作&quot;不完全爆破&quot;。&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">不完全爆破的详细情况&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">1. /p/, /b/, /t/, /d/, /k/, /g/这6个爆破音中的任何两个音素相邻时,前者发不完全爆破音,后者则要完全地。彻底地进行爆破。如:&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">1) He has a ba(d) col(d) today.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">2) You shoul(d) ta(k)e care of the children. Gla(d) to meet you.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">2.爆破音/p/, /b/, /t/, /d/, /k/, /g/在/tF/, /dV/, /W/, /T/的前面时不完全爆破。如:&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">1) Have you rea(d) the book abou(t) tha(t) child。&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">2) The thir(d) chair is broken.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">3.爆破音/p/, /b/, /t/, /d/, /k/, /g/在/m/, /n/, /l/, /s/的前面时不完全爆破。如:&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">1) Goo(d) morning, sir.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">2) Goo(d) night.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">3) They are very frien(d)ly to us.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">注意:不完全爆破可以发生在单词。短语或句子中。</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\"><br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">浊化 ------------------------------</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">1、[S] 后面的清辅音要浊化&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">Discussion： [k] 浊化成 [g]&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">Stand： [t] 浊化成[d]&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">Expression： [p]浊化成[d]&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">2、美音中：[t] 在单词的中间被浊化成[d]&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">如：&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">writer， 听起来和 rider 的发音几乎没有区别&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">letter&mdash;ladder&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">out of&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">美国人和加拿大人发音为了省事，习惯清音浊化，尤其是[t]在单词的中间一定会浊化成[d]， 但英国人发音不会这样，这也是英音和美音的一大区别。 了解这一浊化原则，会给听力带来一些帮助。</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">---------</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">清辅音加在两个元音之间要浊化。 &nbsp;make it &nbsp; &nbsp; wake up</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">-----------------------</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">一些网友总结</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">1两个清辅音相遇, 后一个要浊化 Sp-&gt;sb &nbsp; Sk-&gt;sg &nbsp; &nbsp; St-&gt;sd &nbsp; ????</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">2如果/st/等不在词首，但其前是常见的前缀，如dis, con, sub, in, re等，也要浊化。比如，construction。</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">3如果/st/在词尾，通常不要浊化。如cast。但有些人为了省力也喜欢轻微浊化。</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">4如果/st/等不在词尾，而是紧跟一个常见的后缀结尾，并且该后缀读音包含元音，如-stly，通常也不要浊化。如ghostly。但有些人为了省5力也喜欢轻微浊化。</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">6如果/st/等不在词尾，而是紧跟一个常见的后缀结尾，并且该后缀读音不包含元音，如-sty，通常要浊化。如dusty。</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\">7除以上情况外，当/st/等出现在词中间，如customer，pasture，sister, question，不需要浊化。但有些人为了省力也喜欢轻微浊化。</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('30','20','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>&nbsp;<span style=\\\\\"font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">第一焦点：句子就是一切！句子就是财富!</span></p>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">克立兹提倡的英语学习单位是句子，句子简单明确，容易掌握，并马上可以用于交流！感觉棒极了！味道好极了！</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">可悲的现实：从初中学英语到现在，辛辛苦苦学习了上百课精读，但结局如何？大家心里最清楚：学精读、分析课文的时候清清楚楚,充满成就感，好象是学到了很多知识、很多单词、很多语法、很多&quot;语言点&quot;，但在实际应用的时候却模模糊糊，似是而非，几乎说不出几个正确的句子！几乎全部还给了课本！</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">强烈的呼吁：学习精读的时候，一定要把课文中实用的句子总结出来，并脱口而出！这才是真正的学习语言！</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">冲天的信心：学习英语没有什么了不起！你的征服对象不过是一句话，最多也就是一、两条语法，十来个单词！任何人都可以学好英语！</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">疯狂的成就：从小学四年级开始学英文，如果每天脱口而出五句话，到上初中时，就已经可以脱口而出五千五百多句话，举一反三就可以拥有近两万个实用句子，两万笔英语财富，早已达成自由交流的境界！一个初一学生的英语能力将远远超过一个大学生，因为绝大多数苦读十年的人只会说：My English is poor!</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">第二焦点：三最口腔肌肉训练法！</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">学习外语就是训练口腔肌肉，使之轻松地发出陌生的外国声音，变以成灵活的国际肌肉；学习外语就是苦练脱口而出！只有这样才是真正地拥有语言！克立兹独创的&quot;三最&quot;口腔肌肉训练法将复杂、冷酷的外语学习变成了简单刺激的游戏！</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">作法：用最大声、最清晰、最快速的办法反复操练句子或小短文直至脱口而出。每次记录时间，争取打破上次成绩，也可互相比赛。</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">第三焦点：一口气训练法！&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">这个方法主要训练你说英语的底气。做法很简单，你只需要深呼吸，然后在一口气里尽量多读。经过一段时间的训练，原来需要换几次气的短文，一口气就能轻松读完！</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">第四焦点：五大发音要点！&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">李阳&middot;克立兹将复杂的语音规则总结成五大发音要点，使一般人都能迅速掌握。它们是：长元音双元音饱满；短元音急促；连音；略音和咬舌头。</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">下面举几个例子：</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">1、 I don\\\\''t-know what-to do.（两个辅音连接，只读后一个）</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">2、 I\\\\''m working on-it.（连音）</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">3、 Ask-Bob-to sit-behind-me.（略音）</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">4、Mike likes to write by the nice bright light at night(元音极其饱满)</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">5、 A：What are you planning to do? B: I\\\\''m hoping to go to China.</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">6、 Neither father nor mother likes this weather.（咬五次舌头）</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">第五焦点：口语实破语法!&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">语法是中国人最头疼的一个问题。李阳&middot;克立兹的解决办法是：一句话突破一条语法！英语中难的语法不过几十条，也就是说，只需要脱口而出几十句话就可以基本上掌握英语语法的精华，而且能脱口而出，活学活用，举一反三！没有用的语法暂时不要学，系统全面地学习语法只会系统全面地忘记，而且非常辛苦，因为人脑不是电脑。</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">1、 if she could help you ,she would help you.（如果她能帮你，她一定会的）</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">2、 John stopped studying. =John is not going to study anymore.</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">3、 John stopped to study. =John stopped doing sth. In order to study.</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">4、 I have just finished my work.（表示刚刚完成的动作）</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">5、 He has gone to America.（他去了美国。）（表示结果持续至今）</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">6、 He has been to America.（他曾去过美国。）（至示曾经有过的经验）</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">7、 He has lived here for a year.（表示持续到现在的行为）</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">8、 I enjoyed the movie very much. I wish I had read the book from which it was made.</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">（电影不错，我希望我读过原著）（选自国外权威考试）</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">语法：wish+主语+过去完成时=愿望之事在wish以前发生。</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">特别提醒：一定要用地道关用的句子来学习语法，这亲学习才能和语法建立深厚的感情，才能充满交流的渴望，</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">才能一鸣惊人！</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">1、 I sometimes stay up till midnight.(一般现在时)</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">2、 She\\\\''s always helping people.(现在进行时)</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">3、 He is going to change his job.（一般将来时）</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">第六焦点:口语突破单词！&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">坚决反对孤立地记忆单词！克立兹倡导用实用的句子记忆单词，只有这样才有意义，才能真正地建立感情，地久天长！请记住：人是用句子进行交流的！</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">第七焦点：口语突破听力！&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">你一定能听懂你能说出的东西！你只管去大量地练习说，只要发音纯正、用法地道，你的听力自然突破！而且采用的是超级三最法。比外国人说得还快，难道还怕听不懂吗？</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">第八焦点：口语突破考试！</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">把考试题总结成口语，用三最法脱口而出！你肯定会快速成为考试高手。更重要的是：你获得了真正的英语交流能力。这才是祖国改革开放和经济建设最迫切需要的能力。这是一个&quot;一举数得&quot;、&quot;利国利民&quot;的方法。</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">第九焦点：学一句算一句，说一句顶十句！&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">学一句就要一丝不苟地脱口而出一句，不懂只是一次不懂，糊涂只是一次糊涂！不再做学了忘、忘了学的无聊游戏！而且说一句就要字正腔圆，不是外国人而胜似外国人！气势压人，高人一等！说一句顶十句！而不是说了十句，别人还把你当初学者！</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">十焦点：一年的零碎时间足以攻克英语！</div>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"word-wrap: break-word; font-family: 微软雅黑, \\\\''Microsoft Yahei\\\\'', \\\\''Helvetica Neue\\\\'', \\\\''Hiragino Sans GB\\\\'', 宋体, simsun, 黑体, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\\\\\">大量地制作小纸条，这样可以语言环境随时身携带，可以反复剌激大脑，增强记忆，可以充分利用零碎时间，可以有效控制懒惰。一天轻轻松松脱口而出十句话，一年零零碎碎却真真正正攻克英语，英语变成了你的业余爱好。&nbsp;</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('31','33','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>\r\n	使用公司内部cms系统开发的在线考试插件。包含单选、多选和判断题。实现题目和选项动态读取，完成提交返回考试得分统计，个人信息提交等。\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img src=\\\\\"/e/data/ecmseditor/kindeditor/attached/image/20150305/20150305162105_20890.jpg\\\\\" alt=\\\\\"\\\\\" /> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img src=\\\\\"/e/data/ecmseditor/kindeditor/attached/image/20150305/20150305162218_76406.jpg\\\\\" alt=\\\\\"\\\\\" /> \r\n</p>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('32','10','','1','0','0','0','','','','<pre class=\\\\\"brush:php;toolbar:false\\\\\">\r\n&lt;?php\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/**\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;首先把用户提交的答案根据题目顺序组成一个数组,键值为用户的答案，同一题的选项用&ldquo;，&rdquo;拼接\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;正确答案也做同样处理&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;然后计算出焦急的个数即可计算每一题的得分\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;假设得分规则：全对得2分，选错一个不得分，若漏选，选对一个选项得0.25分\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*/\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\$rs1=array(&quot;a,c&quot;,&quot;a,b,d,f&quot;,&quot;c&quot;,&quot;b,c,d&quot;,&quot;a,d,e&quot;);//用户提交的答案\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\$rs2=array(&quot;a&quot;,&quot;a,b,d,f&quot;,&quot;c,b&quot;,&quot;b,,d&quot;,&quot;a,d,e&quot;);//正确答案\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\$score=0;//初始化得分为0\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;for&nbsp;(\$i=0;&nbsp;\$i&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;count(\$rs1);&nbsp;\$i++)&nbsp;{&nbsp;//循环每一道题目\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\$temp1=explode(&quot;,&quot;,\$rs1[\$i]);//每一道题目的用户答案做成数组\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\$temp2=explode(&quot;,&quot;,\$rs2[\$i]);//每一道题目的正确答案做成数组\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\$interacts=count(array_intersect(\$temp1,&nbsp;\$temp2));//计算数组交集的个数即为正确答案数\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if(\$interacts&lt;count(\$temp1)){//交集个数小于回答的个数&nbsp;则有选错&nbsp;不得分\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\$remark=0;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}else&nbsp;if(\$interacts&lt;count(\$temp2)){//交集个数小于正确答案个数并且不小于回答个数&nbsp;则漏选&nbsp;部分得分\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\$remark=\$interacts*0.25;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}else&nbsp;if(\$interacts==count(\$temp2)){//如果交集个数等于正确答案个数&nbsp;则全对\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\$remark=2;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\$score=\$score+\$remark;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo&nbsp;\$score;\r\n?&gt;</pre>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('33','20','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>1. above board &ndash; legitimate, legal. She knows it shouldn&rsquo;t be kept a secret. She wants to keep everything above board.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2. across the board &ndash; including everyone or everything. The company had a successful year. All salaries were increased by 10% across the board.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>3. air one&rsquo;s dirty laundry in public &ndash; discuss personal problems openly. He is a very private person. If he has a problem in his family he doesn&rsquo;t want to air his dirty laundry in public.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>4. all along &ndash; all the time. She was accepted into the university, but she knew all along that she&rsquo;d get in.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>5. all ears &ndash; eager to listen. I was excited to hear about her vacation. When she told me about it, I was all ears.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>6. all thumbs &ndash; clumsy, unable to fix things. Don&rsquo;t ask me to put that clock back together. I&rsquo;m all thumbs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>7. an arm and a leg &ndash; a large amount of money. It cost an arm and a leg to fix the stove.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>8. ants in one&rsquo;s pants &ndash; nervous, anxious. He wasn&rsquo;t sure if he would be chosen to win the award. He had ants in his pants.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>9. apple doesn&rsquo;t fall far from the tree, the &ndash; being similar to a parent or family member. He acts just like his father. You know, the apple doesn&rsquo;t fall far from the tree.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>10. apple of one&rsquo;s eye &ndash; someone special, usually a son or daughter. Although he loves his son, his daughter is the apple of his eye.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>11. at fault &ndash; responsible for making errors. He is at fault for all the errors on the computer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>12. at odds &ndash; in disagreement. He is at odds with his boss.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>13. at one&rsquo;s beck and call &ndash; always ready to do what is ordered. Whenever she calls him, he&rsquo;s always helping her. He is at her beck and call. The 800 Most Commo nly Used Idioms in America</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>14. at one&rsquo;s wit&rsquo;s end &ndash; anxious, frantic. I need to speak with him to finish the report by tomorrow but he&rsquo;s not available. I&rsquo;m at my wit&rsquo;s end!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>15. at the end of one&rsquo;s rope &ndash; desperate, with nowhere to turn. I&rsquo;ve tried every which way to figure out this problem but I can&rsquo;t. I&rsquo;m at the end of my rope!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>16. back on one&rsquo;s feet &ndash; financially or physically healthy again. Since sales improved, he is doing better and he&rsquo;s getting back on his feet.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>17. back out of &ndash; withdraw, end an obligation or promise. I made a deal with my friend to help him at work. When I became too busy, I had to back out of it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>18. back to the drawing board &ndash; rethink an idea, need to start over. When my supervisor told me that our idea would not work, we had to go back to the drawing board to come up with something else.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>19. backbone &ndash; courage. He has no backbone because he was afraid to reprimand her.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>20. backseat driver &ndash; passenger who tells you how to drive. I&rsquo;ll never drive Joe to the airport again. He kept on wanting me to take another road which I knew was wrong. He is such a backseat driver.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>21. bail one out &ndash; help. Thanks for picking me up when my car broke down. You really bailed me out of a bad situation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>22. ballpark figure &ndash; approximate amount. When I asked the contractor how much it would be to remodel the kitchen, he gave me a ballpark figure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>23. bang for the buck &ndash; value for the money spent. Newspaper advertising works well for us because we get the best bang for the buck.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>24. bank on it &ndash; be sure of, count on. I&rsquo;ll be there to help you. You can bank on it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>25. banker&rsquo;s hours &ndash; short work hours. He loves his job because on Friday, he gets to work banker&rsquo;s hours.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>26. bark up the wrong tree &ndash; make a wrong choice or a false assumption. If he thinks that I&rsquo;m going to help him paint his house, well he&rsquo;s barking up the wrong tree.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>27. bat a thousand &ndash; have a perfect record. He is so happy that everyone he invited to the party is coming. He&rsquo;s batting a thousand.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>28. bat an eyelash &ndash; show emotion. He was filled with emotion during his speech, but she didn&rsquo;t bat an eyelash.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>29. bawl out &ndash; reprimand. The team was bawled out after they lost the game.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>30. be beside one&rsquo;s self &ndash; be very upset. I was so mad when I heard that she was making up stories about me that I was beside myself.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>31. beat around the bush &ndash; avoid giving a clear answer. I didn&rsquo;t want to hurt his feelings and tell him that he wasn&rsquo;t selected for the team. So when he asked me if I had any information, I basically beat around the bush.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>32. beat someone to the punch &ndash; do something before someone else can. She was going to buy the last red dress that the store had, but I beat her to the punch and bought it first.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>33. beat the rap &ndash; escape punishment. There was not enough evidence to convict him, so he beat the rap and was set free.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>34. behind the 8-ball &ndash; in trouble. My department is late on its deadline. We are behind the 8-ball.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>35. bend over backwards &ndash; try very hard. He&rsquo;ll bend over backwards to help any of his friends.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>36. bide one&rsquo;s time &ndash; wait patiently for the right opportunity. I&rsquo;m just going to bide my time. I know that eventually a position will open.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>37. big shot &ndash; important person. Since he was given a promotion, he&rsquo;s been acting like a big shot.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>38. big stink &ndash; an angry and loud complaint. She made a big stink when her meal was served cold.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>39. birds and bees - facts about sex and birth. The girl&rsquo;s mother told her daughter about the birds and the bees during the summer holidays.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>40. bit off more than one can chew &ndash; trying to do more than one can physically and mentally handle. I told her I would help her in her job, but it seems that&rsquo;s all I&rsquo;ve been doing lately. I think I bit off more than I could chew.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>41. bite one&rsquo;s tongue &ndash; keep oneself from speaking. I had to bite my tongue in order not to tell him that he won the raffle.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>42. bite the dust &ndash; die, disappear. Our old TV didn&rsquo;t work yesterday. I guess it finally bit the dust.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>43. blab &ndash; talk too much. She is always blabbing about her supervisor&rsquo;s personal life to her friends.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>44. blabbermouth &ndash; person who talks too much and tells secrets. He is such a blabbermouth that there is no way Bob will be surprised for his party.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>45. black sheep &ndash; a family member with a bad reputation. John&rsquo;s way of life is so different from all of ours. He is known as the black sheep of the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>46. blind date &ndash; a date arranged for two people who don&rsquo;t know each other. Many married couples have met on a blind date.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>47. blow it &ndash; lose a chance, make a mistake. I knew I blew it when I forgot my lines in the play.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>48. blow over &ndash; end, pass. She knew her coworkers will eventually forget how she messed up the filing system in the office. She couldn&rsquo;t wait for the incident to blow over.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>49. blow the whistle &ndash; expose, betray. I just found out that he&rsquo;s been stealing from our company for the past year. I don&rsquo;t want it to continue and I&rsquo;ve decided to blow the whistle.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>50. boil down &ndash; make shorter, condense. This whole complicated situation just boils down to something simple&hellip;it&rsquo;s either a yes or a no.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>51. bomb &ndash; fail, be unsuccessful. The whole cast was very sad that the show bombed on Broadway.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>52. bone to pick with someone &ndash; complaint, argument. I heard that you have rejected my proposal. I&rsquo;m upset and have a bone to pick with you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>53. boob tube &ndash; television set. What is on the boob tube tonight?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>54. bookworm &ndash; person who reads a lot. The library is the perfect place for her to work because she is such a bookworm.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>55. booze &ndash; liquor &ndash; They kept bottles of booze behind the bar.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>56. botch up &ndash; make a mistake, ruin. I asked for her help with my watercolor painting. But when she decided to add some purple paint, I knew that she completely botched it up.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>57. bottom line &ndash; end result, ultimate cause. He never practiced the piano, so the bottom line is, he can&rsquo;t play very well.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>58. bounce &ndash; not acceptable because of insufficient funds in the bank. If your check bounces, I will need to charge you extra money.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>59. brain &ndash; intelligent person. She is such a brain, she will figure out how to solve the problem.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>60. brainstorm &ndash; very smart idea. I have got a brainstorm! Let&rsquo;s start giving out free samples of our products.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>61. bread and butter - basic needs of life (food, shelter, clothing). The voters are worried about bread and butter issues like jobs and taxes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>62. break one&rsquo;s neck &ndash; try very hard. She broke her neck last night trying to finalize the proposal.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>63. break the ice &ndash; overcome formality or shyness with others. He started the meeting by telling a joke. He was hoping the joke would break the ice.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>64. break the news &ndash; tell a surprising fact. She broke the news and told him that she was going to move to another city.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>65. break up &ndash; separate. They needed to break up their engagement because she fell in love with someone else.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>66. break even &ndash; have expenses equal to profits. The company did not make a profit this year. We just broke even.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>67. breathe a word &ndash; tell. Please don&rsquo;t breathe a word of this to anyone.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>68. breeze &ndash; easy. Last night&rsquo;s homework was a breeze.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>69. bring home the bacon &ndash; earn the family&rsquo;s income. He stays home and raises the children and she brings home the bacon.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>70. broke &ndash; having no money. I can&rsquo;t go to the restaurant tonight because I&rsquo;m broke.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>71. brown bag &ndash; bring one&rsquo;s lunch from home. For the meeting on Friday, we&rsquo;ve all decided to brown bag it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>72. buck &ndash; dollar. I&rsquo;m low this week on cash. Can I borrow a few bucks to get me through the week?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>73. buckle down &ndash; study or work very hard. Last semester his grades were very low, so this year he decided to buckle down.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>74. buddy-buddy &ndash; very friendly. She&rsquo;s gotten to be very buddy-buddy with her boss.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>75. bug &ndash; annoy, bother. It bugs me every time he asks to borrow a pencil.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>76. bulldoze &ndash; intimidate, coerce. I did not want to work on the fundraising committee, but I feel I was bulldozed into it&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>77. bum &ndash; worthless person. As long as I have known him, he never worked and always borrowed from other people. He is such a bum!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>78. burn a hole in one&rsquo;s pocket &ndash; money to be spent quickly. The bonus he received must have burned a hole in his pocket. He ended up buying a car the next day.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>79. bury the hatchet &ndash; make peace. Although we had gotten into a big fight last month, we decided to bury the hatchet and become friends again.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>80. butt in &ndash; interfere. Please don&rsquo;t butt in to our conversation, it&rsquo;s personal.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>81. butter up &ndash; flatter for selfish reasons. I buttered up my boss before I asked him off for the upcoming holiday.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>82. by hook or by crook &ndash; by any means necessary. Even though we have to fly to get to your wedding, we will be there by hook or by crook.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>83. by the skin of one&rsquo;s teeth &ndash; by a very small margin. Our team won by the skin of our teeth.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>84. call it quits &ndash; stop, finish. I have worked all day and am exhausted. I&lsquo;ve decided to call it quits.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>85. call off &ndash; cancel. The game was called off because of rain.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>86. call on the carpet &ndash; reprimand. He was called on the carpet for losing all the financial statements.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>87. call someone&rsquo;s bluff &ndash; have someone prove what he says. I don&rsquo;t think Bob knows as much as he says. I think we should call his bluff.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>88. call the shots &ndash; be in charge, give orders. We knew who the supervisor was because she called all the shots.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>89. can &ndash; fire, dismiss. I was canned and no longer am working for the company.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>90. can of worms - complex problem or complicated situation. It opened up a large can of worms when the company decided to talk about the union contract.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>91. carried away &ndash; adversely influenced by strong emotion. He was carried away by his effective sales approach and bought the remainder of his products.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>92. catch on &ndash; understand, figure out. I am beginning to catch on to this algebra.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>93. catch someone red-handed &ndash; find one in the act of doing something wrong. The police came and the bank robber was caught red handed&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>94. caught short &ndash; I didn&rsquo;t have enough money to pay the bill. I was caught short.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>95. chalk up &ndash; record, score. Chalk up another one for the team. They won the championship.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>96. change of heart - a change in the way one feels about something. I wasn&rsquo;t planning to spend the holidays with my family, but after speaking with my mother, I had a change of heart.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>97. chickenfeed &ndash; a small amount of money. Taking the whole family on that cruise is certainly not going to be chickenfeed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>98. chip in &ndash; contribute. We are all going to chip in and give the teacher a gift.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>99. chip off the old block &ndash; child who looks or acts just like his or her parent. He reminds me so much of his father. He&rsquo;s a chip off the old block.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>100. chip on one&rsquo;s shoulder &ndash; quarrelsome attitude, quick to anger. I was afraid to ask her for a favor. It looked like she had a chip on her shoulder.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('35','20','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>&nbsp;201. for the birds &ndash; terrible, awful. I work long hours and hardly get paid. This job is for the birds.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>202. for the time being &ndash; at the present time. For the time being, let&rsquo;s not make any changes to the report.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>203. free-for-all &ndash; mayhem, disorder. When the teacher left for a meeting, it was a free-for-all in the classroom.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>204. freeload &ndash; get things that others pay for. When my friend moved into my apartment, stayed for a year and never contributed any money, I knew he was a freeloader.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>205. from the bottom of one&rsquo;s heart - with great feeling, sincerely. My sister thanked me from the bottom of her heart for saving her dog&rsquo;s life.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>206. from the left field &ndash; unexpectedly, with an odd or unclear connection to the subject. We were in the middle of a business meeting when, out from left field, he asked about the weather.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>207. from scratch &ndash; from the very beginning, starting with raw materials. This chocolate was not made from a cake mix, she made it from scratch.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>208. fume &ndash; be angry. When I heard that she was talking about me to other people, I was just fuming.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>209. gall &ndash; shameless, insolent attitude. She spent all of her money on clothes and music, and then she asked to borrow money for groceries. She has gall.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>210. game &ndash; willing, ready. Okay, you want to make plans to go to China? Okay, I&rsquo;m game.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>211. get a grip on oneself &ndash; take control of one&rsquo;s feelings . When he lost the soccer game, he couldn&rsquo;t stop crying. I told him to get a grip on himself.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>212. get a kick out of &ndash; enjoy. I get a kick out of it every time I see her dance.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>213. get a load of &ndash; have a good look at. Get a load of those fancy cars driving down the street.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>214. get ahead &ndash; become successful. She is saving all her money, so that one day she can get ahead.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>215. get along &ndash; manage. He realized that he was able to get along quite well without his partner.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>216. get around to - finally find time to do something &ndash; I have put it off for months, but I finally got around to cleaning the windows.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>217. get at &ndash; mean, hint. You tell me that I am slow at work. What are trying to get at.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>218. get away with murder &ndash; not be punished for wrongdoing. &ndash; He&rsquo;s the boss&rsquo;s son and comes in late everyday, but we can&rsquo;t complain. He&rsquo;s getting away with murder.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>219. get cold feet &ndash; be afraid at the last minute, lose confidence. I was prepared to make a speech, but I got cold feet when I saw how many people were going to hear it.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>220. get down to brass tacks &ndash; begin important work or business. Get off the phone so that we can discuss business. Let&rsquo;s get down to brass tacks.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>221. get even &ndash; get revenge, settle the score. I was so upset when she insulted me last week. I want to get even with her.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>222. get the runaround &ndash; be sent from place to place without getting the information needed. It took me four hours to renew my driver&rsquo;s license. I was sent to almost every department and seemed to get the runaround.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>223. get in on the ground floor &ndash; start from the beginning so you&rsquo;ll have full advantage of any favorable outcome. He is a very wealthy man. He was one Microsoft&rsquo;s first employees and got in on the ground floor.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>224. get in the swing of things &ndash; adapt or adjust to a new environment. After working two weeks in the new department, I finally got into the swing of things.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>225. get off the ground - make a successful beginning, go ahead. He will finally take his project and get it off the ground in the coming year.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>226. get off one&rsquo;s back &ndash; leave someone alone, don&rsquo;t bother. She reminded me that I had to prepare for my trip out of town. I wish she would get off my back.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>227. get off on the wrong foot &ndash; make a bad start. Having a fight with a co-worker on my first day of work was not a good idea. I got off on the wrong foot.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>228. get off the ground &ndash; make progress, make a good start. I finally got my business off the ground.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>229. get one&rsquo;s goat &ndash; make someone disgusted, annoyed, angry. Sitting in traffic for 5 hours really got my goat.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>230. get out from under &ndash; end a worrisome situation. I am glad that I am working again and making money. I finally got out from under my bills.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>231. get out of &ndash; withdraw. I would really like to get out of going to the holiday party.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>232. get out of hand &ndash; lose control. The party really got out of hand when they started drinking alcohol.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>233. get something off one&rsquo;s chest &ndash; unburden yourself, tell what&rsquo;s bothering you. I feel better ever since I told him my problem and got it off my chest.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>234. get the ax &ndash; be fired. My company finally realized that he wasn&rsquo;t doing his job. They gave him the ax.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>235. get the show on the road &ndash; start a project or work. We have been discussing unimportant things all morning. Let&rsquo;s get the show on the road and start getting down to business.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>236. get to the bottom of &ndash; find out the real cause. After talking to my friend for an hour, I finally got to the bottom of why he was angry at me.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>237. get under someone&rsquo;s skin - annoy, bother, upset. He has a difficult and annoying personality and always got under my skin.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>238. get up and go &ndash; ambition, energy, enthusiasm &ndash; She always seems so excited and motivated at work. She&rsquo;s got a lot of get up and go.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>239. get up on the wrong side of the bed &ndash; be in a bad mood. My son has been cranky all day. I think he got up on the wrong side of the bed.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>240. get what is coming to one &ndash; what one deserves, good or bad. After stealing so much money from the charity, I really hope he gets what&rsquo;s coming to him.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>241. get wind of &ndash; find out, hear gossip or rumors about. I got wind of the fact that they will be closing down our department.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>242. give a hoot &ndash; care. I don&rsquo;t give a hoot who wins the election.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>243. give the cold shoulder &ndash; be unfriendly to, ignore. I was so mad at my cousin, that I gave her the cold shoulder at the wedding reception.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>244. give in &ndash; do as others want, surrender. I wanted to paint the room blue, my wife wanted yellow. I had to give in.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>245. give it one&rsquo;s best shot &ndash; try very hard. I gave it my best shot, but I still didn&rsquo;t make the team.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>246. give someone a break &ndash; give someone an opportunity or chance. The actor struggled for many years. Finally, someone gave him a break and put him in a movie.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>247. give someone a hand &ndash; help. I couldn&rsquo;t work my regular hours. A co-worker gave me a hand and switched schedules with me.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>248. give someone a piece of one&rsquo;s mind &ndash; say what you really think when angry. I was so mad that he was late for the wedding, I gave him a piece of my mind.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>249. give someone his walking papers &ndash; dismiss, fire, send away. She got her walking papers on Friday and won&rsquo;t be coming back to work.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>250. give someone the green light - give permission to go ahead with a project. We were finally given the green light to begin setting up the new project.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>251. go cold turkey &ndash; stop abruptly. My doctor really wants me to quit smoking. I decided to stop and go cold turkey.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>252. go Dutch &ndash; each person pay for himself. If we have dinner together, I insist that we go Dutch.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>253. go from bad to worse &ndash; deteriorate. Sales have been very slow this season, but this was the worst week of all. It seems like it&rsquo;s going from bad to worse.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>254. go out of one&rsquo;s way &ndash; make a special effort, do more than necessary. I went out of my way to make it easier for you.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>255. go over &ndash; examine. Before I submit the report, I want to go over it one more time for mistakes.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>256. go over big &ndash; be very successful. Do you think my idea to have a birthday party for our teacher will go over big?&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>257. go overboard &ndash; overact, be reckless. I&rsquo;ve never seen so many flowers at a wedding. Do you think maybe you&rsquo;ve gone overboard?&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>258. go steady &ndash; go out with only one person romantically. Who did you go steady with in high school?&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>259. go to bat for &ndash; assist, help. I have overheard that she may be fired from her job. I think she is a hard worker and I want her to stay. I&rsquo;m going to bat for her.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>260. go to pot &ndash; deteriorate, become undisciplined, unkempt. He has quit his job, gained weight, and I think may be abusing drugs. It looks like he&rsquo;s really gone to pot.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>261. go under the knife &ndash; have surgery. I&rsquo;ll be going under the knife next week for some minor surgery.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>262. go up in smoke &ndash; disappear, fail to materialize. She was going to go on a vacation, but her mother got sick. Her plans have gone up in smoke.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>263. go-getter &ndash; ambitious person. She is the most successful salesperson I&rsquo;ve ever seen. She&rsquo;s a real go-getter.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>264. goldmine &ndash; worth a lot of money, successful. His business is a major success and will only get bigger every year. He is sitting on a goldmine.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>265. goner &ndash; someone in a lot of trouble. His boss found out he has been stealing from the cash register. He&rsquo;s a goner.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>266. good sport &ndash; a person who loses well. Even though I beat you in the game, you still congratulated me. You are a good sport.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>267. goof off &ndash; not want to work, be lazy. I am tired of working so hard. I just want to stay home and goof off.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>268. grab 40 winks &ndash; I felt so sleepy after my lunch, I decided to grab 40 winks.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>269. grand - \$1000. It cost me a grand to stay in the luxury hotel.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>270. greasy spoon &ndash; inexpensive restaurant with mediocre food. I hated dinner last night. It turned out being a greasy spoon.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>271. gung ho &ndash; enthusiastic, eager. He thinks his team is the best in the league. He is really gung ho this season.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>272. guts &ndash; courage. He has a lot of guts to stand up to management.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>273. guy &ndash; man. That guy over there is my neighbor.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>274. half baked &ndash; foolish, silly. Opening up a store which sells only tape will not be successful. It is a half baked idea.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>275. hand it to someone &ndash; give credit, acknowledge. I&rsquo;ve got to hand it to you. Your idea to open a store in this location was great.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>276. hand over fist &ndash; rapidly. He&rsquo;s making money hand over fist.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>277. hand something on a silver platter - give a person something that has not been earned. His father is president of the university and his education was handed to him on a silver platter.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>278. hand to mouth &ndash; barely able to cover basic expenses. That family is struggling since the father lost his job. I hear that they&rsquo;re living hand to mouth.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>279. handful &ndash; a lot of trouble. My three year old runs around the house and often breaks things. He&rsquo;s a real handful.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>280. handle with kid gloves &ndash; be very careful, tactful. His wife gets upset very easily. He has to handle her with kid gloves.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>281. handy &ndash; can fix things, useful. She&rsquo;s very handy around the house. If anything breaks, she can fix it easily.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>282. hang in there &ndash; be patient, wait. I know you want to quit school, but hang in there. You only have 4 more weeks before your graduation.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>283. hard feelings &ndash; anger, bitterness. I know we had our differences, but I hope there are not any hard feelings.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>284. hard up &ndash; in desperate need of something. Everyone comes to her desk and takes supplies. I know she&rsquo;s hard up for pencils.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>285. harp on &ndash; dwell on the subject, repeat, persist. I know losing your job was awful, but don&rsquo;t harp on it. You are only making yourself more depressed.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>286. has-been &ndash; a person once popular but no longer in public favor. Since the movie star was found guilty of a crime, I haven&rsquo;t seen him in any motion pictures. He&rsquo;s a has-been.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>287. hassle &ndash; bother. Please stay home tonight. I don&rsquo;t want the hassle of having to bring you and pick you up from the party.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>288. have a ball &ndash; have a good time, enjoy one&rsquo;s self. She had a ball at her holiday party.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>289. have a crush on &ndash; be attracted to. I have had a crush on her since 5th grade.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>290. have a fit &ndash; become upset. She&rsquo;ll have a fit if she finds out you broke her watch.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>291. have a good head on one&rsquo;s shoulders &ndash; be smart or sensible. You have a good head on your shoulders and I&rsquo;m sure you&rsquo;ll do fine in college.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>292. have a mind of one&rsquo;s own &ndash; be able to think independently. Although we all voted one way, she voted in a completely opposite direction. She&rsquo;s really got a mind of her own.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>293. have a prayer &ndash; have a chance. He&rsquo;s not good enough to make it on the team. He doesn&rsquo;t have a prayer.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>294. have been around &ndash; to be experienced, sophisticated. She knows all about office politics. She has been around for awhile.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>295. have egg on one&rsquo;s face &ndash; be embarrassed. She called in sick to work yesterday, but when I saw her at the store she had egg on her face.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>296. have it coming &ndash; deserve a punishment. I didn&rsquo;t study for the exam and I failed. I had it coming.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>297. have it made &ndash; be sure of success, have everything. Ever since she won the lottery, she can do whatever she wants. She has it made.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>298. have it out with someone &ndash; discuss a conflict or misunderstanding with the other person involved. My friend and I had a big fight last week. This morning I had it out with him and now everything is okay.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>299. have one&rsquo;s feet on the ground &ndash; be practical, sensible, stable. She&rsquo;ll make a great wife and mother because she has got both feet on the ground.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>300. have one&rsquo;s hand in the till &ndash; steal from one&rsquo;s employer. The reason he has been buying such nice new clothes is that he&rsquo;s got his hand in the till.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('36','20','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>&nbsp;301. have one&rsquo;s head in the clouds &ndash; have unrealistic dreams, lost in thought. Even though she is a terrible actress, she thinks someday she will be a movie star. She has got her head in the clouds.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>302. have one&rsquo;s heart set on &ndash; desire greatly. The boy had his heart set on getting a puppy.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>303. have someone&rsquo;s number &ndash; know what kind of person someone is. He doesn&rsquo;t think anyone knows, but I know he stole the material for the book. I&rsquo;ve got his number.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>304. have something up one&rsquo;s sleeve &ndash; kept secretly ready for the right time. If the electricity goes out during the birthday party, don&rsquo;t worry. I&rsquo;ve got something up my sleeve.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>305. have the heart to &ndash; be thoughtless enough. I know there was just a death in her family. I don&rsquo;t have the heart to ask her when she is coming back to work.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>306. have two strikes against someone &ndash; be in a difficult situation with little chance of success. He wanted the job but he can&rsquo;t write and he has difficulty speaking on the phone. He&rsquo;s got two strikes against him already.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>307. haywire &ndash; broken, confused, awry. The plan was in place to surprise by boss on his birthday, but it all went haywire.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>308. heart-to-heart &ndash; intimate, honest. I needed to speak him about a problem I was having. We had a heart-to-heart talk.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>309. high and dry &ndash; alone, without help, stranded. After everyone left the party, I was all alone to clean up. I was left high and dry.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>310. high and low &ndash; every place. I can&rsquo;t seem to find my keys. I&rsquo;ve looked high and low.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>311. high-brow &ndash; intellectual, cultured person. Everyone seemed very high-brow at the cocktail reception.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>312. hit &ndash; a success. Her book was a hit and sold a million copies.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>313. hit below the belt &ndash; hurt someone cruelly and unfairly. I have been upset ever since she made that awful comment to me. It really hit below the belt.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>314. hit it off &ndash; enjoy one another&rsquo;s company, get along. Although we just met, we really hit it off and will probably see each other again.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>315. hit the bottle &ndash; drink alcohol. He hits the bottle every time he has some family trouble.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>316. hit the ceiling &ndash; get angry. I hit the ceiling when I found out that she broke my computer.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>317. hit the nail on the head &ndash; arrive at the correct answer, make a precise analysis. When you named the person who was responsible for our losses this quarter, you really hit the nail on the head.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>318. hit the sack &ndash; go to bed. I was so tired last night, that I hit the sack as soon as I got home.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>319. hit the spot &ndash; refresh or satisfy. We sat in the sun and hadn&rsquo;t had a drink all day. That cold glass of water really hit the spot.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>320. hogwash &ndash; nonsense. The idea that aliens landed in New York City is a bunch of hogwash.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>321. hold a grudge &ndash; not forgive someone for an insult or injury. Even though they broke up 10 years ago, she still holds a grudge and will not speak to him.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>322. hold back &ndash; conceal, hide. He held back his feelings and acted as if everything was alright.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>323. hold one&rsquo;s horses &ndash; wait. I can&rsquo;t leave the office yet. I&rsquo;m waiting for an important phone call. Just hold your horses.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>324. hold up &ndash; delay, postpone. Sorry I&rsquo;m late. I was held up in traffic.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>325. holy mackerel - used to express strong feeling of surprise. Holy Mackerel! Look at that man&rsquo;s motorcycle.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>326. hook, line and sinker &ndash; without question or doubt. I told a lie to my teacher. He bought it hook, line and sinker.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>327. hot1 &ndash; stolen. He bought a great television from a guy on the street for \$50.00. The television must have been hot.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>328. hot2 &ndash; in great demand. This was the hottest movie out this weekend.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>329. hot air &ndash; nonsense or exaggerated talk. I don&rsquo;t believe a word that man says. He is full of hot air.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>330. hound &ndash; continually bother. She hounded me until I finally agreed to say yes.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>331. hush-hush &ndash; secret. The birthday party is a surprise. Please don&rsquo;t tell anyone, it&rsquo;s hush-hush.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>332. hustler &ndash; person who gets money aggressively or unethically. He won&rsquo;t work. If he needs money, he&rsquo;ll hustle someone.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>333. hyper &ndash; very energetic, anxious, unable to sit still. It is impossible to bring that child to a restaurant. He is too hyper.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>334. ill at ease &ndash; I am shy. So when I go to a cocktail party I am ill at ease.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>335. in a bind. In trouble no matter what you do. She committed to help two different people at the same time. She is in a bind.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>336. in a jam &ndash; in trouble. He is in a jam and needs some help to get out of it.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>337. in a nutshell &ndash; briefly. She spoke to us for at least an hour and told us a long story. I would have preferred that we heard it in a nutshell.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>338. in a pinch &ndash; okay, when nothing else is available. If you don&rsquo;t have a needle to sew something together, a safety pin will work in a pinch.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>339. in a rush &ndash; in a hurry. I can&rsquo;t find my wallet and keys and I&rsquo;m late for a meeting. I&rsquo;m in a rush.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>340. in a rut &ndash; always doing the same thing. My job is very boring and uninteresting. I&rsquo;m depressed and think I am in a rut.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>341. in advance &ndash; ahead of time. Let&rsquo;s call the movie theatre in advance and see if they have any tickets left.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>342. in black and white &ndash; in writing. The salesman said that he would give me a 5 year warranty on my purchase. I told him to put it in black and white.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>343. in hot water &ndash; in trouble. I am going to be in hot water when she finds out that I dented her car.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>344. in nothing flat &ndash; quickly, in a short time. When he heard that I was taking him out to dinner, he got dressed in nothing flat.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>345. in seventh heaven &ndash; very happy. I begin my month long vacation tomorrow. I&rsquo;m in seventh heaven.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>346. in someone&rsquo;s shoes &ndash; in another person&rsquo;s place or position. You cannot pass judgment on someone until you&rsquo;ve stepped into their shoes.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>347. in stitches &ndash; laughing. He is the funniest person I know. He always keeps me in stitches.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>348. in the bag &ndash; certain, sure, definite. The job interview went very well and I think I will be hired. I am confident that it&rsquo;s in the bag.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>349. in the doghouse &ndash; in trouble. My wife and I had a big fight last night. I&rsquo;m in the doghouse.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>350. in the long run &ndash; in the end, as a result. If you study hard in school, in the long run you will be successful.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>351. in the market for &ndash; wanting or ready to buy. We are in the market for a new mattress.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>352. in the red &ndash; losing money. Our company is in the red and may be going out of business.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>353. in the same boat &ndash; in a similar situation. He can&rsquo;t pay his bills either. He is in the same boat as you.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>354. iron out &ndash; work out. Even though the two men do not get along, they are both willing to iron out their problems.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>355. jack up &ndash; raise prices. Last week the department store jacked up all their prices.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>356. jack-of-all-trades - person who can do many kinds of work. My friend is a jack-of-all-trades. He knows how to fix everything.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>357. jalopy &ndash; old car usually in poor condition. I finally sold my jalopy and bought a new car.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>358. jam-packed &ndash; crowded, full. My new computer can do so many different things. It&rsquo;s jam-packed with features.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>359. the jitters &ndash; anxiety, nervousness. She knew the test was going to be very difficult and she had the jitters all day.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>360. John Hancock &ndash; signature. The car salesman asked the customer to put his John Hancock on the bottom of the contract.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>361. jump down someone&rsquo;s throat &ndash; criticize angrily, hastily. He&rsquo;s very angry today. Every time I ask him a question he jumps down my throat.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>362. jump the gun &ndash; start before you should. You will need more facts before you go into business. Don&rsquo;t jump the gun.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>363. jump to conclusions &ndash; make quick but unjustified conclusions. Don&rsquo;t jump to conclusions and assume that all well-dressed men are rich.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>364. keep a stiff upper lip &ndash; have courage, be brave. Even though he thought he was going to be terminated from his job, he kept a stiff upper lip.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>365. keep in touch &ndash; communicate, talk or write to each other &ndash; Even though we won&rsquo;t see each other for six months, let&rsquo;s try to keep in touch.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>366. keep on &ndash; continue. If you are not hungry, don&rsquo;t keep on eating.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>367. keep one&rsquo;s fingers crossed &ndash; wish for good luck. His mother kept her fingers crossed so that her son would make the team.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>368. keep one&rsquo;s head above water &ndash; be able to exist on one&rsquo;s income, pay bills. Even though she only made a meager salary, she was still able to buy clothes, go to restaurants, and keep her head above water.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>369. keep one&rsquo;s nose clean &ndash; After he was released from prison he stayed out of trouble. His parents were glad that he kept his nose clean.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>370. keep one&rsquo;s shirt on &ndash; be patient, wait. I know it&rsquo;s taking me a long time to finish my work, but keep your shirt on.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>371. keep something under your hat &ndash; keep something a secret. She was given information which was meant to be private, so she kept it under her hat&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>372. keep tabs on &ndash; watch, check. My neighbor is always looking out her window and keeping tabs on me.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>373. Keep up with the Joneses &ndash; try to equal your neighbor&rsquo;s lifestyle. He works many long hours just so he can keep up with the Joneses.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>374. kick in the pants &ndash; rejection, criticism. Steve was always kind to someone who was poor and unfortunate. When that person made a lot of money, he ignored Steve. Steve got a kick in the pants.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>375. kick oneself &ndash; regret. I could kick myself for not buying that stock which tripled in value.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>376. kick something around &ndash; discuss, think about. We didn&rsquo;t know which way to direct the company, so we kicked some ideas around.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>377. kick the bucket &ndash; die. The old man kicked the bucket when he was 110 years old.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>378. kid &ndash; a young person. I have two kids. They are 10 and 3 years old.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>379. kid around &ndash; fool, play, joke. Don&rsquo;t kid around with Mary. She is in a very bad mood.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>380. kiss something goodbye &ndash; see something ruined or lost. When I saw the photo album fall off of the boat and into the water, I knew it was lost forever and I just kissed it goodbye.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>381. knock it off &ndash; stop. He wouldn&rsquo;t stop tickling me, so I told him to knock it off.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>382. knock one dead &ndash; greatly impress, surprise. When the actor was preparing to go on stage, I told me to knock them dead.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>383. knock one for a loop &ndash; surprise. I didn&rsquo;t expect the movie to have that sort of ending. It knocked me for a loop.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>384. knock one&rsquo;s head against the wall &ndash; waste time in futile effort to improve or change something. Teaching teenagers to drive responsibly is like knocking my head against a wall.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>385. knock oneself out &ndash; make a great effort. She worked many hours getting ready for the party and knocked herself out.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>386. knockout, a &ndash; a beautiful person or thing. That beauty queen is a knockout.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>387. know if one is coming or going &ndash; be able to think clearly, know what to do. There were so many students signing up at registration, I didn&rsquo;t know if I was coming or going.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>388. know-how &ndash; experience and knowledge. He has been building houses for many years and has a lot of know-how.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>389. kosher &ndash; true, authentic. The financial statements say that your business is making a lot of money. Are the amounts all kosher?&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>390. land on one&rsquo;s feet &ndash; come out of a bad situation successfully. She just came off of a terrible divorce. She&rsquo;s doing well now and it seems that she landed on her feet.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>391. last straw, the &ndash; the last insult or injury that one can endure. His son watched TV all day and didn&rsquo;t work. When he started to gamble, that was the last straw.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>392. lay out &ndash; spend or pay. Will you lay out the money for the meal and I will pay you back tomorrow?&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>393. learn the ropes &ndash; acquire special knowledge of a job. Now that you have started your new position with the company, it will probably take you a few months to learn the ropes.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>394. leave a bad taste in one&rsquo;s mouth - make a bad impression, make or feel disgusted. I thought the salesman was obnoxious. He left a bad taste in my mouth.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>395. leave someone holding the bag &ndash; put someone in an awkward position, leave someone else to take the blame. The children ate all of the cookies and ran away. Peter was the only one who remained and was left holding the bag.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>396. lemon &ndash; merchandise that doesn&rsquo;t work. My new car has needed repair four times since I bought it. I ended up buying a lemon.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>397. let bygones be bygones. &ndash; Forget differences that happened in the past. Even though my friend and I had a big fight, I told him we should let bygones be bygones.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>398. let it ride &ndash; continue without changing a situation. Don&rsquo;t say anything to him now. I don&rsquo;t want to hurt his feelings. Just let it ride.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>399. let on &ndash; reveal, inform, tell. She let on that she knew my secret.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>400. let one&rsquo;s hair down &ndash; be informal, relaxed. After the business meeting when our supervisor left, we spoke about our personal lives and let our hair down.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('37','20','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>401. let someone off the hook &ndash; excuse from a penalty or promise. Because this was his first criminal offense, he was let off the hook.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>402. let the cat out of the bag &ndash; tell a secret. His surprise birthday party was cancelled because someone let the cat out of the bag.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>403. Let the chips fall where they may. &ndash; Act regardless of consequences. The police were asking him about the robbery. He knew he had to tell everything he knew and let the chips fall as they may.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>404. like a ton of bricks &ndash; strongly, forcefully. When I was told that my favorite uncle died, it hit him like a ton of bricks.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>405. live high off the hog &ndash; have many luxuries, be very comfortable. When you see their new home, you&rsquo;ll know that they live high off the hog.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>406. live it up &ndash; pursue pleasure, have a good time. Now that school is over, I want to live it up this weekend.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>407. live wire &ndash; active exciting person. People always want her at their parties because she is a live wire.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>408. loaded &ndash; having lots of money. Ever since he started his new business, he appears to be loaded.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>409. loaded &ndash; drunk. I can tell by the way she spoke that she was loaded.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>410. look down one&rsquo;s nose at &ndash; think someone is worthless or unimportant, show contempt. She thinks she is better than everyone else. She always looks down her nose at others.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>411. look into &ndash; investigate, check. I&rsquo;m going to look into the possibility of getting a scholarship for college.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>412. look up &ndash; improve, getting better. Since he is putting in more hours at work, his financial situation is looking up.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>413. loony bin &ndash; insane asylum. I couldn&rsquo;t believe how crazy she acted last night. She belongs in the loony bin!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>414. loot &ndash; money. How much loot do you need to buy that fancy car?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>415. lose one&rsquo;s marbles &ndash; go insane, act irrationally. Anyone who insults his boss has lost his marbles.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>416. lose one&rsquo;s shirt &ndash; lose all one&rsquo;s money. He put his lifetime savings into the restaurant. When it failed, he lost his shirt.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>417. lose track of someone &ndash; lose contact, no know where someone is. I have lost track of him since high school and have no idea where he lives now.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>418. louse up &ndash; ruin. I&rsquo;ve worked on this painting for weeks, but when my paintbrush slipped out of my hand, I loused up the painting.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>419. lowdown &ndash; the true story. I heard that she was married before but didn&rsquo;t know why she divorced. Give me the lowdown.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>420. lower the boom &ndash; stop completely, punish strictly. When the father heard that the children were not doing their homework, he lowered the boom.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>421. make a bundle &ndash; make a lot of money. She made a bundle selling donuts to the construction workers.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>422. make a dent in &ndash; make progress. I have got a lot of work to do, but I made a dent in it last night.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>423. make a federal case out of &ndash; overreact, take strong measures for a minor problem. I&rsquo;m sorry for spilling some water on your desk, but you don&rsquo;t have to make a federal case out of it.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>424. make a go of &ndash; succeed, produce good results. Although this new business is risky, I&rsquo;m going to try to make a go of it.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>425. make a hit &ndash; be successful. People loved my new brownies and wanted the recipe. I guess I made a hit.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>426. make a killing &ndash; gain a large amount of money at one time. She made a killing in the stock market last year.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>427. make a monkey out of someone &ndash; cause to look foolish. The lawyer was shrewd and made a monkey out of his opponent&rsquo;s client.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>428. make a mountain out of a molehill &ndash; make a big problem out of a small one. It wasn&rsquo;t difficult, it was easy. Don&rsquo;t make a mountain out of a molehill.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>429. make ends meet &ndash; balance one&rsquo;s budget, meet one&rsquo;s payments. His expenses are so high, that even though he makes a lot of money, his family has difficulty making ends meet.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>430. make fun of &ndash; ridicule It&rsquo;s not nice to make fun of other people.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>431. make it up to someone &ndash; compensate for an unfulfilled promise. I am so sorry that we have to cancel our plans tonight, but I will try to make it up to you. [!--empirenews.page--]</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>432. make of something &ndash; interpret, figure out, think of. What do you make of his decision to drop out of college?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>433. make one&rsquo;s hair stand on end &ndash; frighten, horrify. The extreme poverty in that country would make your hair stand on end.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>434. make one&rsquo;s mouth water - look or smell very good, make one want to eat or drink something one sees or smells &ndash; The smell of garlic outside the restaurant made my mouth water.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>435. make one&rsquo;s own way &ndash; rely on one&rsquo;s own abilities. She had no help from anyone. She had to make her own way.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>436. make out &ndash; do, progress, succeed. How are you making out with your new responsibilities at the office?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>437. make sense &ndash; be comprehensible. What&rsquo;s the word in English that&rsquo;s spelled yrkszwa&hellip;it doesn&rsquo;t make sense.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>438. make sure &ndash; see about something yourself, check. We are leaving on our vacation, and I want to make sure that you locked all the doors.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>439. make the best of &ndash; accept a bad situation and do as well as possible under the circumstances. Even though our heating system broke, let&rsquo;s light a fire in the fireplace and make the best of it.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>440. make up one&rsquo;s mind &ndash; decide. She hasn&rsquo;t made up her mind as to what university she will be attending.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>441. make waves &ndash; upset the status quo, create a disturbance. He likes to avoid controversy and usually doesn&rsquo;t make waves.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>442. man-to-man &ndash; frank, direct. Don&rsquo;t discuss the problem with me. Go to your boss&rsquo;s office and talk about it man-to-man.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>443. mean business &ndash; be serious. He told his son that he had to finish all of his homework before he went out to play and he meant business.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>444. mess &ndash; disorderly, cluttered condition; bad or confused situation. There were clothes and food all over his apartment and it was a mess.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>445. miss a trick &ndash; take advantage of every situation. As soon as her boss left the building, she began to make personal calls. She doesn&rsquo;t miss a trick.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>446. miss out on &ndash; lose an opportunity, miss a worthwhile event. It is too bad you couldn&rsquo;t make it to the reunion because you missed out on a good time.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>447. miss the boat &ndash; lose an opportunity. It&rsquo;s too bad he didn&rsquo;t buy gold when it was cheap. Now, it is very expensive and he really missed the boat.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>448. mobbed &ndash; crowded. The shopping mall was mobbed the day before Christmas.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>449. mooch &ndash; borrow, beg, get without paying. She says that she doesn&rsquo;t smoke, but she is always mooching cigarettes from her friends.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>450. mouthful &ndash; a true and impressive statement. You said a mouthful when you admitted that she was the smartest girl in her class.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>451. mudslinging &ndash; making malicious remarks to damage someone&rsquo;s reputation. There is a lot of mudslinging going on in politics today.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>452. mum&rsquo;s the word &ndash; don&rsquo;t talk about what was said. I don&rsquo;t want you to say anything about our discussion. Mum&rsquo;s the word.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>453. murder &ndash; a difficult or painful ordeal. Getting her master&rsquo;s degree while she worked full-time was murder.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>454. nag, a &ndash; a persistently urging person. He complains that his wife is always nagging him to do things around the house.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>455. name someone after &ndash; give the child the name of an admired person. My son is named after my grandfather.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>456. nest egg &ndash; extra money saved. They have a small nest egg saved up for their vacation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>457. nightcap, a &ndash; last drink one has before leaving or prior to sleeping. She ordered some brandy as a nightcap.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>458. nincompoop &ndash; a stupid person, a fool. He doesn&rsquo;t know how to act well around other people. He&rsquo;s a nincompoop!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>459. nip in the bud &ndash; prevent at the start. When she saw that her little boy was snacking between meals, she decided to nip it in the bud.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>460. nitpick &ndash; look for very minor errors or problems. Every time she reads one of his reports, she is always nitpicking on the most minor points.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>461. nitty-gritty &ndash; the essence or important part. We&rsquo;ve been discussing your problem for an hour, but we finally got down to the nitty-gritty.</p>\r\n<p>[!--empirenews.page--]</p>\r\n<p>462. nitwit &ndash; idiot. He messes up everything in our department and is such a nitwit.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>463. no bed of roses &ndash; uncomfortable, unhappy situation. Their marriage is no bed of roses. They seem to always be fighting.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>464. no dice &ndash; no, certainly not. I like living in this area. When my children wanted to move, I said &lsquo;no dice&rsquo;.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>465. no picnic &ndash; not pleasant. He works very hard at the factory. He says it is no picnic.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>466. nobody&rsquo;s fool &ndash; smart competent person. She&rsquo;s very smart. She&rsquo;s nobody&rsquo;s fool.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>467. not on your life &ndash; definitely not, no way. There is not a chance I am going to drive 4 hours to go to that party&hellip;not on your life.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>468. not so hot &ndash; not very good. She boasted about her pumpkin pie, but I thought it was not so hot.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>469. nothing to sneeze at &ndash; something not trivial, to be taken seriously. They offered him a lot of money to take this new position. He was going to give it a lot of thought because it was nothing to sneeze at.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>470. nuts about &ndash; in love with, enthusiastic about. I&rsquo;m nuts about our new neighbors.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>471. odds and ends &ndash; miscellaneous items. I have some odds and ends around my house that I would like to sell.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>472. off and on &ndash; occasionally. We are not very good friends anymore. I see him off and on.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>473. off base &ndash; inaccurate. If you think I paid one thousand dollars for this coat, you are way off base.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>474. off color - in bad taste, rude, dirty. He told an off-color joke at the party that embarrassed my wife.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>475. off one&rsquo;s rocker &ndash; crazy. He is off of his rocker if he thinks I&rsquo;m going to help him decorate for the party.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>476. off the hook &ndash; out of something, freed from an embarrassing situation. I don&rsquo;t want to have dinner with him. Let&rsquo;s tell him that we will be out of town so that we will get off the hook.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>477. off the record &ndash; privately, unofficially, not for public announcement. I need to tell you about one of my accounts, but it needs to be off the record.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>478. off the top of one&rsquo;s head &ndash; from memory, spontaneously. Off the top of my head, I think her last name begins with an &lsquo;M&rsquo;.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>479. old flame &ndash; former boyfriend or girlfriend. She bumped into an old flame at the shopping mall.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>480. on a shoestring &ndash; with very little money. We are trying to decorate our home on a shoestring.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>481. on easy street &ndash; having a pleasant, secure life. Ever since his mother won the lottery, they have been on easy street.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>482. on guard &ndash; careful, wary. It is a very important meeting and we must think before we speak. We must be on guard.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>483. on one&rsquo;s last leg &ndash; at the end of one&rsquo;s strength of usefulness. My car is over ten years old and it&rsquo;s on its last leg.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>484. on one&rsquo;s shoulders &ndash; one&rsquo;s responsibility. The president has a lot of problems on his shoulders.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>485. on pins and needles &ndash; nervous, excited. When I found out that the movie star was coming to the party, I was on pins and needles.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>486. on shaky ground &ndash; unstable. The buyers aren&rsquo;t sure if they really want to buy the car. I think the sale is on shaky ground.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>487. on the ball &ndash; paying attention and doing things well. She always gets her paperwork submitted on time. She is always on the ball.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>488. on the blink &ndash; not working. The ice is melting in our freezer. I think it is on the blink.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>489. on the edge of one&rsquo;s seat &ndash; in nervous suspense. I have wanted to see this movie ever since I read the book. Now that it is about to start, I am on the edge of my seat.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>490. on the fritz &ndash; not working correctly, out of order. The ice is melting in our freezer. I think it is on the fritz.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>491. on the go &ndash; busy running around. I won&rsquo;t be home all day. I have many errands to run and will be on the go.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>492. on the house &ndash; provided free by a bar or restaurant. Since I am good friends with the owner of the restaurant, dinner was on the house.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>493. on the level- honest. They are not telling you the whole story. They are not on the level.</p>\r\n<p>[!--empirenews.page--]</p>\r\n<p>494. on the q.t. &ndash; secretly. I was just told that I will be promoted to vicepresident but nobody knows about it yet. Please don&rsquo;t tell anyone and keep it on the q.t.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>495. on the rocks &ndash; breaking up, ruined. The couple is always fighting and I wasn&rsquo;t surprised to hear that their marriage is on the rocks.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>496. on the same wavelength &ndash; communicating, thinking similarly. They didn&rsquo;t understand each other. They were not on the same wavelength.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>497. on the spot &ndash; in a difficult or embarrassing situation. I was put on the spot and expected to make a toast at the anniversary party.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>498. on the wagon &ndash; abstaining from liquor. He used to drink a lot of beer and wine, but now he is on the wagon.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>499. on the warpath &ndash; very angry, looking for trouble. When Mary saw John with another woman, Mary went on the warpath.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>500. once in a blue moon &ndash; occasionally. He doesn&rsquo;t watch television often. Only once in a blue moon.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('41','33','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>&nbsp;基于帝国cms的内容管理和投票系统。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\\\\\"/d/file/projects/2015-03-06/e9ce6eddfd4b32a8fa060fb0d239b495.jpg\\\\\" alt=\\\\\"y1.jpg\\\\\" width=\\\\\"1438\\\\\" height=\\\\\"1449\\\\\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\\\\\"/d/file/projects/2015-03-06/f79bbfd23460d54a1573f868d35b0d18.jpg\\\\\" alt=\\\\\"y2.jpg\\\\\" width=\\\\\"1438\\\\\" height=\\\\\"1224\\\\\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\\\\\"/d/file/projects/2015-03-06/6ece55bbfc6ea295ad4ac1cce7890c13.jpg\\\\\" alt=\\\\\"y3.jpg\\\\\" width=\\\\\"1438\\\\\" height=\\\\\"1431\\\\\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\\\\\"/d/file/projects/2015-03-06/619077c628582dbebea26db3d5266af1.jpg\\\\\" alt=\\\\\"y4.jpg\\\\\" width=\\\\\"958\\\\\" height=\\\\\"429\\\\\" /></p>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('42','10','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>实现对列表页和文章页的投票按钮点击进行投票，这里mervyn用&ldquo;顶&rdquo;的功能来修改实现。</p>\r\n<p>投票规则是：每个ip每天最多可投三票，提交需要输入验证码。</p>\r\n<p>一 、/e/下建立一个个人文件夹，此次我建立的文件夹名称是mervyn。把/e/public/下的digg文件夹复制进去。</p>\r\n<p>二、建立三个文件用于实现验证码。ckcode.php、code.php、showcode.php ;</p>\r\n<p>相关文件：mervyn.rar</p>\r\n<div style=\\\\\"padding:6px\\\\\"><fieldset>\r\n<table cellpadding=\\\\\"0\\\\\" cellspacing=\\\\\"0\\\\\" border=\\\\\"0\\\\\">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><img src=\\\\\"/e/data/images/downfile.jpg\\\\\" alt=\\\\\"文件类型: .rar\\\\\" border=\\\\\"0\\\\\" style=\\\\\"vertical-align:baseline\\\\\" /></td>\r\n            <td><a href=\\\\\"/d/file/web_dev/php/2015-03-06/f699b29d624f1b43b0e3fc76bdbbfdb3.rar\\\\\" title=\\\\\"mervyn.rar\\\\\" target=\\\\\"_blank\\\\\">f699b29d624f1b43b0e3fc76bdbbfdb3.rar</a>&nbsp;(3.35 KB)</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</fieldset></div>\r\n<div>三、开始前台调用</div>\r\n<div>文章列表：</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<pre><p>&lt;ul&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">	</span>[e:loop={9,4,0,1,\\\\''\\\\'',\\\\''diggtop DESC\\\\''}]</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">	</span>&lt;li&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">		</span>&lt;div class=&quot;indexMainListPic&quot;&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">			</span>&lt;a href=&quot;&lt;?=\$bqsr[\\\\''titleurl\\\\'']?&gt;&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">				</span>&lt;img src=&quot;&lt;?=\$bqr[\\\\''titlepic\\\\'']?&gt;&quot; /&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">			</span>&lt;/a&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">		</span>&lt;/div&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">		</span>&lt;h3&gt;&lt;?=\$bqr[\\\\''title\\\\'']?&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">		</span>&lt;div class=&quot;indexMainListTool&quot;&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">			</span>&lt;p&gt;票数：&lt;span&gt;&lt;?=\$bqr[\\\\''diggtop\\\\''];?&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">			</span>&lt;a href=&quot;javascript:void(0)&quot; name=&quot;tou&quot; aid=&quot;&lt;?=\$bqr[\\\\''id\\\\'']?&gt;&quot; classid=&quot;&lt;?=\$bqr[\\\\''classid\\\\'']?&gt;&quot;&gt;投一票&lt;/a&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">		</span>&lt;/div&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">	</span>&lt;/li&gt;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\\\\\"Apple-tab-span\\\\\" style=\\\\\"white-space: pre;\\\\\">	</span>[/e:loop]</p>\r\n<p>&lt;/ul&gt;</p>\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>jquery代码：</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<pre class=\\\\\"brush:js;toolbar:false\\\\\">\r\n\$(function(){\r\n	\$(&quot;a[name=\\\\''tou\\\\'']&quot;).each(function(){\r\n		\$(this).click(function(){\r\n			var diggs=\$(this).parent(&quot;.indexMainListTool&quot;).find(&quot;span&quot;);\r\n			var curdiggs=diggs.text();//当前票数\r\n			var aid=\$(this).attr(&quot;aid&quot;);//文章id\r\n			var classid=\$(this).attr(&quot;classid&quot;);//栏目id\r\n			var t=\$(window).scrollTop();\r\n			var h=\$(&quot;#floater&quot;).height();\r\n			var newt=t-h/2;\r\n			\$(&quot;#cover&quot;).show();//遮罩层\r\n			\$(&quot;#floater&quot;).css(&quot;margin-top&quot;,newt+&quot;px&quot;).show().load(&quot;[!--news.url--]e/mervyn/showcode.php&quot;,&quot;&quot;,function(){//验证码窗口\r\n				\$(&quot;#floater .sub&quot;).click(function(){\r\n					var code=\$(&quot;input[name=\\\\''code\\\\'']&quot;).val();\r\n					var d={&quot;code&quot;:code};		\r\n					\$.ajax({\r\n						type:&quot;post&quot;,\r\n						url:&quot;[!--news.url--]e/mervyn/ckcode.php&quot;,\r\n						data:d,\r\n						dataType:&quot;json&quot;,\r\n						success:function(data){\r\n							var msg=data.msg;//yes or no\r\n							if(msg==&quot;no&quot;){\r\n								alert(&quot;验证码错误&quot;);\r\n								return false;\r\n							}else if(msg==&quot;yes&quot;){//验证码正确 执行投票\r\n								var dd={&quot;aid&quot;:aid,&quot;classid&quot;:classid};	\r\n								//alert(aid);  2\r\n								//alert(classid); 6\r\n								\$.ajax({\r\n									type:&quot;post&quot;,\r\n									url:&quot;[!--news.url--]e/mervyn/digg/index.php&quot;,\r\n									data:dd,\r\n									dataType:&quot;json&quot;,\r\n									success:function(data){\r\n										// alert(data);\r\n										if(data.valid!=&quot;yes&quot;){\r\n											alert(data.msg);//投票失败\r\n											\$(&quot;#floater&quot;).empty().hide();\r\n											\$(&quot;#cover&quot;).hide();\r\n										}else{\r\n											alert(&quot;感谢您的支持&quot;);\r\n											//更新投票数\r\n											var newdiggs=parseInt(curdiggs)+1;\r\n											diggs.text(newdiggs);\r\n											\$(&quot;#floater&quot;).empty().hide();\r\n											\$(&quot;#cover&quot;).hide();\r\n										}\r\n									}\r\n								})\r\n							}\r\n						},\r\n						error:function(){\r\n							\r\n						}\r\n					})\r\n				})\r\n			});\r\n		})\r\n	})\r\n})</pre>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!--2800;\$i++)<-->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!--\$len;\$i++){<-->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!--?php<-->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!--?php<-->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');");
E_D("replace into `cn_ecms_news_data_1` values('38','20','','1','0','0','0','','','','<p>&nbsp;501. once-over &ndash; quick look or examination. I didn&rsquo;t have time to read the contract, so I gave it a once-over.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>502. one for the books &ndash; very unusual, remarkable. She hates to be around children and she&rsquo;s an elementary school teacher. That&rsquo;s one for the books.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>503. one&rsquo;s cup of tea &ndash; something one enjoys, special interest. I don&rsquo;t like going to the opera. It&rsquo;s not my cup of tea.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>504. one&rsquo;s hands are tied &ndash; one is unable to help. I would like to lend you money, but we just bought a car and a house. My hands are tied.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>505. one&rsquo;s heart is in the right (wrong) place - kindhearted, sympathetic or well-meaning. Although she makes a lot of mistakes, her heart is in the right place.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>506. one&rsquo;s heart is in one&rsquo;s mouth &ndash; one is nervous, fearful, or anxious. I&rsquo;m speaking in front of 200 people tonight and am very nervous. My heart is in my mouth.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>507. one-track mind &ndash; mind focused on a single idea. All he ever thinks about is football. He has a one-tracked mind.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>508. out of line &ndash; not usual, incorrect, unacceptable. She tells her husband what he can and cannot do. I think she is out of line.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>509. out of sorts &ndash; in a bad mood, irritable. I haven&rsquo;t&rsquo; been feeling very happy lately. I am out of sorts.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>510. out of the blue &ndash; unexpectedly, by surprise, from nowhere. I haven&rsquo;t&rsquo; heard from my college roommate in 10 years. Last week, out of the blue, he called me.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>511. out of the woods &ndash; no longer in danger, in the clear. The doctors say she no longer has the disease. Her prognosis is very good and she is now out of the woods.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>512. out of this world &ndash; wonderful, terrific. This chocolate cake is the best I have ever had. It&rsquo;s out of this world.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>513. out on a limb &ndash; in a dangerous, exposed position, one&rsquo;s ideas are openly known. By speaking up against her boss, she is putting herself out on a limb.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>514. over a barrel &ndash; in a helpless, trapped position. He saw me cash my paycheck and then asked me for a loan. I could not refuse. He had me over a barrel.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>515. over one&rsquo;s dead body &ndash; under no condition, never. I work six days a week. Only over my dead body will I work another day.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>516. pad the bill &ndash; add false expenses. The insurance company found out that the dentist had padded the bill.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>517. pain in the neck &ndash; bothersome, annoying thing or person. My little brother is a pain in the neck.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>518. pan out &ndash; happen favorably. This new business is risky, but hopefully it will pan out.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>519. pass away &ndash; die. I miss the neighbor who passed away last year.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>520. pass out &ndash; faint. I haven&rsquo;t eaten all day, and I think I am going to pass out.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>521. pass the buck &ndash; shift responsibility to others. I called their customer service line, but everyone kept on passing the buck.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>522. patch up &ndash; fix. Even though we had a fight, let&rsquo;s try to patch things up.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>523. pay through the nose &ndash; pay too much. I had to pay through the nose to stay at that fancy resort.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>524. peanuts &ndash; small amount of money. It only cost peanuts to fix the scrape on the car.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>525. pep talk &ndash; a talk to arouse enthusiasm. The coach gave the players a pep talk before the game.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>526. perk up &ndash; emerge from a depressed or uninterested mood. When the owner of the company walks into the office, try to perk up.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>527. pick up &ndash; obtain, get. Please pick up a gallon of milk when you go to the grocery store.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>528. pick up the tab &ndash; pay the bill. Since he came into a lot of money, he always picks up the tab whenever we go out to dinner.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>529. pick-me-up, a &ndash; a drink or snack taken to refresh oneself. &ldquo;You look tired. Drink this, it&rsquo;s a good pick-me-up&rdquo;.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>530. piece of cake, a &ndash; easy. She has also been good at mathematics. She thinks algebra is a piece of cake.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>531. pile up &ndash; accumulate, put things on top of each other. Try not to let the work on your desk pile up.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>532. pill &ndash; an annoying, disagreeable person. She is always mad about something and unpleasant to be around. She is such a pill.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>533. pin someone down &ndash; make someone tell the truth or agree to something. He needed to pin her down as to the date for the meeting.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>534. pinch pennies &ndash; be thrifty, careful how you spend money. If you spend your time pinching pennies, eventually, you&rsquo;ll have a lot of money.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>535. pink slip &ndash; notice of dismissal. He was fired and received a pink slip on Friday and will not be showing up for work on Monday.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>536. pinpoint &ndash; find exact location or cause. We need to pinpoint the cause of the problem.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>537. pitch in &ndash; help. Everyone needs to pitch in so that we can get the work done and go home.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>538. pits, the &ndash; the worst, anything that is very bad. Having to clean out my basement is the pits.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>539. play hooky &ndash; stay away from school or work without permission. He played hooky from work so that he can do things around his house.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>540. play it by ear &ndash; make your decision according to the situation. I&rsquo;m not sure when I will arrive at the restaurant, so let&rsquo;s play it by ear.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>541. play the field &ndash; go out with many people romantically. She is not dating anyone seriously and is still playing the field.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>542. play up to someone &ndash; flatter or please for selfish reasons. He is playing up to his boss because he is hoping to move up in the company.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>543. play with fire &ndash; invite danger, trouble. You are playing with fire if you drive with your car on &lsquo;empty&rsquo;.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>544. plenty of &ndash; a lot of, abundance. She had plenty of food at the party, so everyone ate a lot.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>545. point out &ndash; explain, show, call attention to. Let me point out the problem with your plan.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>546. pop the question &ndash; ask to marry. He popped the question and asked her to marry him when they were scuba diving.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>547. pound the pavement &ndash; look for a job. It took him 3 months of pounding the pavement before he landed a job.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>548. pour it on thick &ndash; flatter profusely, exaggerate. He poured it on thick to his boss, because he wanted to get a raise.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>549. pull a fast one &ndash; cheat, deceive. She pulled a fast one when she got away with stealing all the company&rsquo;s profits.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>550. pull punches &ndash; hide unpleasant facts or make them seem good. She told him why she wouldn&rsquo;t date him anymore, and she didn&rsquo;t pull any punches.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>551. pull someone&rsquo;s leg &ndash; trick, playfully tease, fool. If you think I believe that you won the lottery, your pulling my leg.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>552. pull something off &ndash; accomplish something remarkable. He never thought he would be able to put on a show, but he pulled it off.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>553. pull strings &ndash; secretly use influence and power. I&rsquo;ll see if I can pull strings so that you can get an interview.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>554. pull the rug out from under &ndash; spoil someone&rsquo;s plans, withdraw support. I felt like someone pulled the rug out from under me when he said he wouldn&rsquo;t pay my tuition.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>555. pull the wool over one&rsquo;s eyes &ndash; deceive, mislead. He pulled the wool over her eyes and married her just for her money.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>556. pull up stakes &ndash; move to another location. They pulled up stakes last year and moved to another state.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>557. push someone around &ndash; boss, make a person do what you want. I don&rsquo;t like it when she pushes me around.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>558. put a damper on &ndash; discourage, spoil a person&rsquo;s fun. I hate putting a damper on the party, but it is getting late and everyone has to go home.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>559. put anything past someone &ndash; be surprised by what someone does. I wouldn&rsquo;t put it past her to talk about me behind my back.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>560. put down &ndash; make someone look bad, criticize. He embarrassed her by putting her down in front of her family.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>561. put in one&rsquo;s two cents &ndash; give one&rsquo;s opinion. I put in my two cents, so that everyone knew how I felt.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>562. put one&rsquo;s cards on the table &ndash; be frank, tell everything. She put her cards on the table and told everyone what she really thought.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>563. put one&rsquo;s finger on &ndash; find precisely, remember exactly. She didn&rsquo;t know what was causing the problem, but she finally put her finger on it.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>564. put one&rsquo;s foot down &ndash; object strongly, take firm preventative action. I cleaned the whole house. When she told me that I had to clean the garage too, I finally put my foot down.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>565. put one&rsquo;s foot in one&rsquo;s mouth &ndash; speak carelessly, make a rude or insensitive comment. I said something that embarrassed my friend, and really put my foot in my mouth.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>566. put our heads together &ndash; confer, discuss. Let&rsquo;s put our heads together and figure out a way to solve this problem.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>567. put someone in his or her place &ndash; scold someone for rude, improper behavior. When she embarrassed me in front of my friends, I angrily answered her back and put her in her place.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>568. put someone on a pedestal &ndash; idolize, worship. He has great respect for his coach, and has put him on a pedestal.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>569. put something out of one&rsquo;s mind &ndash; try not to think about it. I&rsquo;m worried about next week&rsquo;s test, but I am going to relax and put it out of my mind.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>570. put through the wringer &ndash; cause severe stress. The attorney asked me many questions and put me through the wringer.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>571. put two and two together &ndash; make a conclusion knowing the facts. She put two and two together and realized that he was stealing from the company.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>572. put up a good front &ndash; pretend to be happy, fool people about one&rsquo;s status. Even though she is upset about the fight she had with her friend, she put up a good front and smiled the whole time they were together.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>573. put up with &ndash; patiently accept, endure. He has had to put up with her terrible disposition if he wanted to remain married to her.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>574. quack &ndash; an ignorant or fraudulent doctor. The man paid the doctor \$1000.00 to fix his problem, but he still had a lot of pain. I think that doctor is a quack.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>575. rack one&rsquo;s brain &ndash; try to hard to think or remember. I racked my brain to remember who I was supposed to call back.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>576. racket &ndash; easy, well-paying job, business that cheats customers. That company is running a racket. They take money from people, but never provide them with a service.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>577. raise eyebrows &ndash; cause surprise or disapproval, shock. It raised some eyebrows when the mother hit the little child in the store.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>578. rake it in &ndash; make a lot of money. Since business has improved, he is really raking it in.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>579. rake over the coals &ndash; scold, reprimand, blame. My boss raked me over the coals for losing the big account.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>580. rat race &ndash; endless, competitive striving; hurried material existence. Working in the big city can sometimes feel like a rat race.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>581. raw deal &ndash; unfair treatment. I was the lowest paid worker in the office. I believe I was given a raw deal.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>582. read between the lines &ndash; understand things that are not said, find a hidden meaning. If you read between the lines, you will see that this contract only protects the company and not the customer.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>583. real McCoy &ndash; the genuine thing. This artifact actually came from the Titanic. It is the real McCoy.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>584. red tape - excessive formalities in official business. Many businesses have been complaining about the amount of red tape that they must deal with in order to get anything done with the government.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>585. right off the bat &ndash; in the beginning, immediately. Before anything else happened, right off the bat he welcomed everyone to the meeting.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>586. right under one&rsquo;s nose &ndash; in an obvious nearby place. Even though I never to my eyes off of the jewelry counter, someone stole a watch right under my nose.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>587. ring a bell &ndash; remind one of something familiar. I&rsquo;m sure I&rsquo;ve seen that man before. His name rings a bell.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>588. rip off &ndash; cheat, rob. This product I bought doesn&rsquo;t work and is made poorly. I was ripped off.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>589. road hog &ndash; person who takes too much room on the road. That road hog is driving between two lanes and I think may cause an accident.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>590. rock the boat &ndash; upset the status quo. If you tell everyone in the office about the company&rsquo;s plans to close, you may cause a lot of problems. Don&rsquo;t rock the boat.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>591. roll out the red carpet - greet a person with great respect, give a big welcome. When the King of Jordan visited Washington, they rolled out the red carpet and gave him a great welcome&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>592. rope into &ndash; trick, persuade or pressure. She got roped into going to the meeting even though she doesn&rsquo;t work in that department.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>593. rough &ndash; approximate. This computer sells for roughly \$1000.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>594. rub one the wrong way &ndash; annoy, bother, make angry. There is something about his personality that just rubs me the wrong way.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>595. rub something in &ndash; constantly refer to a mistake or fault. She used to rub it in that I was fired from my job. She is no longer my friend.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>596. rule out &ndash; decide against, eliminate. You will need some medical tests because your doctor needs to rule out whether or not you may have a virus.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>597. rule the roost &ndash; be the dominant one in the family. Although she is very quiet and soft-spoken, I was told that she rules the roost in her family.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>598. run around in circles &ndash; act confused, do a lot, but accomplish little. I had so much to do that I was running around in circles.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>599. run out of &ndash; finish the supply, use up. The car&rsquo;s gas tank was empty and I was afraid that we were going to run out of gas.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>600. run ragged &ndash; tire, exhaust. I haven&rsquo;t had a 